title: rhubarb pie deluxe
directions: Mix and cook slowly until like jelly.
Bake shell.
Pour in mixture and cover with meringue, made from egg whites.

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, salt, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 egg.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Combine remaining eggs, sugar, vanilla and syrup.
Pour over pecans.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes until center is firm.

title: barbecued brisket of beef
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.
Wash beef; trim off excess fat.
Blend remaining ingredients in shallow roasting pan. Add beef.
Roast in preheated oven for 2 hours, allowing 30 minutes per pound. Baste meat frequently during cooking with pan juices.
If sauce gets too thick, thin with a little consomme.

title: cheesy green bean casserole
directions: In large skillet saute onion in margarine and stir in flour slowly.
Add all other ingredients (except beans) and heat until velveeta is melted.
In 2 qt. casserole dish alternate layers of beans and mixture.
Top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cucumber rice salad
directions: Combine rice, cucumber, onion and salt.
Stir in dressing.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 30 minutes. Turn onto serving tray and top with glaze.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Slice cheeses and melt to soft (not liquid) stage.
Add pimentos.
Mix well.
Add mayonnaise, salt, pepper and vinegar to taste.
Makes approximately 2 quarts for sandwich spread.
For dip, make thinner with more mayonnaise and vinegar.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and chill.

title: swiss bliss
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put foil in large pan.
Cut steaks into strips; put on foil.
Sprinkle with soup.
Place mushrooms, bell pepper and tomatoes.
Mix A.1., cornstarch and juice; pour on top. Seal foil.
Cook for approximately 2 hours.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Cool Whip together.
Stir in jello powder until well mixed.
Drain fruit very well, then stir into orange mixture.
Refrigerate until served.
Best if made the day before serving.

title: sal's eggplant parmigiana
directions: Dip sliced eggplant into egg mixture, then into bread crumbs. Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Layer fried eggplant in casserole dish.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese and tomato sauce. Repeat layers, ending with eggplant, Mozzarella cheese and tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 20 minutes; uncover and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix sugar, water and syrup; bring to a boil.
Add peanuts and cook to 260°.
Add food color and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into foil-lined pan.
Cool.
Then break into small pieces.

title: quick chicken pot pie
directions: Mix soup and milk into bowl. Stir in peas and carrots. Microwave on High for 6 minutes. Stir in cubed chicken.
Form 1 piece of pie crust into deep dish casserole;
pour chicken mixture into deep dish. Place the other pie crust on top and make 4 slits. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Stir and heat the first 3 ingredients.
Add cheese; melt.
Add pineapple.
Stir and mix.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole. Crumble crackers on top.
Drizzle melted margarine on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, saute potatoes, onion and celery in butter until just tender.
Add clam juice and bay leaf.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: devil dogs
directions: Drop by heaping spoonfuls 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 425° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: bonnie's swedish apple pie* * * * *
directions: Moravian Rice is from a Virginia friend who had been stationed with us in South Carolina and Germany.
When I say Virginia, that is where she was living at the time, although, she was originally from Michigan.
Bonnie is our Texas neighbor.

title: paula's meat soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix all ingredients in one soup pot.
Simmer for 2 hours.

title: bakeless oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal and peanut butter; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients; boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Mix with oatmeal and peanut butter mixture.
Drop onto greased waxed paper with spoon; let cool until hardened.
Remove and store.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken and broccoli in 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; pour over chicken/broccoli; top with cheese/bread crumbs.
Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook very slowly at 250° about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: date and nut bars
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and spices.
Be sure to sift 3 times.
Add to creamed mixture the flour mixture and the buttermilk.
Add vanilla, nuts and dates.
Spread in greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Test for doneness.
When cool, invert on cutting board and cut into bars. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: old-fashion meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix hamburger with bell pepper, onion, 2 eggs, milk, ketchup, bread (in small pieces), salt, pepper and mustard and mix all ingredients well together.
Bake in large pan at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 or more.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well and roll into 1 1/2-inch balls. In double boiler, melt together paraffin wax with chocolate morsels.
Dip balls into mixture and place on wax paper until hardened.

title: barbecued chipped ham
directions: Put all ingredients in large skillet, except meat, and mix well.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes over medium heat; add meat.
Continue cooking 10 to 15 minutes.

title: ground beef stew
directions: Add onion to water and bring to a boil.
Add ground beef and seasonings.
Simmer until onion is thoroughly cooked.
Serve on mashed potatoes.

title: carrot kugel *
directions: Stir together all dry ingredients except sugar.
Beat the oil, brown sugar and egg whites.
Stir in the flour mixture.
Stir in the water, lemon juice and grated carrots.
Bake at 350° in greased 8-inch baking dish or in ring mold for 45 minutes.
Can be frozen after baked and cooled.

title: fancy lime jello
directions: Dissolve jello using 1/4 cup less water and set in fridge until half set.
Whip cream per instructions and add cream cheese. Fold in pineapple and pecans.
Then add all to jello, mixing well.
Put into mold or bowl and chill until set.
Everyone likes this one!

title: nine day pickles
directions: First Mixture:
One cup of salt to 1 gallon water.
Bring salt water mixture to a boil.
Remove from heat and pour hot liquid over cucumber slices until they are covered.
Let stand 24 hours.
Pour old water mixture out.
Repeat process with fresh salt water (3 days).

title: chicken carolina
directions: In a buttered casserole put first 4 ingredients, then pour dressing, butter and chicken broth over (don't mix).
Spread over the top.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: white rolled cookies
directions: Cut shortening into first 3 ingredients as for pie crust. Using rotary beater, beat eggs and add sugar gradually, continuing to beat thoroughly; add to first mixture.
Knead until smooth. Chill for several hours or overnight.

title: baked italian haddock
directions: Place the haddock into a baking dish.
Dice the onion and place it on top of the fish.
Top with the spaghetti sauce.
You may add additional seasonings at this point if you like.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Add the cheese and bake for 15 minutes.

title: creamy chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, soups, and sour cream. Cover the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch baking pan with tortilla chips; add chicken mixture over the top. Combine crushed crackers and margarine; sprinkle over chicken mixture. Bake uncovered for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skin.
Peel and grate.
In saucepan, combine cheese and butter until melted.
Remove from heat and add sour cream, onion and seasonings. Fold in potatoes and turn into greased baking dish.
Dot with butter and paprika.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Have margarine, butter and cream cheese at room temperature. Cream all three together until creamy.
Add sugar and cream again. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour a little at a time.
Add flavoring; beat again.
Pour into a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done.

title: california orange carrots
directions: In a saucepan, cook carrots in salted water until crisp-tender. Drain.
Return carrots to pan and add orange peel, butter, orange pieces and onion, if desired.
Heat through.
Serve immediately. Yield:
6 servings.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix together the pork, ham, eggs, 1 cup milk and bread crumbs. Make into a loaf.
Cover thickly with dry mustard, then cover with brown sugar.
Pour 1 cup milk around the loaf in a pan.
Bake slowly for 2 hours.
Do not cover or baste.

title: "philly" cheese ball
directions: Combine cold pack cheese food and softened cream cheese (mixing well).
Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Line small bowl with plastic wrap.
Place into this.
Chill until firm.
Roll into bowl of chopped pecans, if desired.
To make a softer ball, I use a small jar of pimento cheese in the cheese mix.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: mini ham sandwiches
directions: Slice entire package of dinner rolls, forming a top and bottom.

title: ice ring
directions: In 2-quart nonmetal container, combine lemonade and water; mix well.
Pour mixture in a 6 cup mold.
Freeze until slushy, about 2 to 3 hours.
Place strawberries in slush, allowing tops of strawberries to show.
Freeze until firm or overnight.
Remove ice from mold; wrap in plastic wrap and store in freezer until ready for use.

title: rice - quick and easy
directions: Melt in a saucepan 2 tablespoons butter.
Add and stir until golden brown the 1/2 chopped onion.
Add and shake until the grains are coated.
Add hot chicken stock.
Cover the pot and simmer the rice or bake it in a 375° oven until the liquid is absorbed.
Add 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Toss the rice with a fork to distribute it.

title: d p g potato salad
directions: Boil washed potatoes until cooked through; peel.
Cube potatoes and mix with other ingredients.
Chill; serves 30 to 40.

title: old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Soak vanilla and raisins together for 1 hour.
Cream shortening, sugars and eggs.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and raisins.
Roll cookies into balls and place onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten cookies with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: caramel chocolate squares
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine the caramels and half of the evaporated milk.
Cook on low heat until caramels are melted; set aside.
Combine dry cake mix, oleo, remaining milk and nuts.
Stir by hand until dough holds together.
Press half of the dough into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle chocolate pieces over the baked crust.
Spread caramel mixture over the chocolate pieces.
Crumble (spread) the other half of the dough over the mixture.
Return to the oven and bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool, then refrigerate for 30 minutes to set the caramel mixture.
Makes 36 squares.

title: hot picante dip
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature.
Mold onto bottom and sides of round casserole dish.
Mix chill and picante sauce and pour into casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Heat in oven or microwave until cheese melts.
Serve with taco chips.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown
ground
meat
and
onion.
Stir	in flour, salt, garlic,
pepper, mushrooms and soup.
Simmer on low heat until noodles
have
been cooked according to directions on package. Drain
noodles
and add poppy seed and margarine.
Just before serving, stir sour cream into meat mixture.
Heat slightly but do not boil. Serve over noodles. Makes 6 servings.

title: chunky pecan muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine egg, milk, syrup and 1/2 cup butter; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Fill paper-lined muffin pans two-thirds full. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Saute onion in bacon fat.
Add flour and brown.
Add tomatoes and their juices.
Stir as gravy thickens.
Add water, a little at a time, and cook longer until gravy is of desired consistency. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice or biscuits.
This gravy is also good as a casserole sauce.

title: southern chicken pie
directions: Dumplings:
Sift flour into large bowl.
Makes nest in center.
Pour cooking oil into nest.
Pour boiling water into nest and mix with a spoon to blend flour, oil and water.
Make into a thick paste.
When cool enough, knead dough and slap with hand 8 or 10 times to bond.
Pinch or break off 3-4 inch portions, slap and transfer to floured cutting board.
Roll with rolling pin until it reaches the thickness you desire.
Cut into strips. Break into 1 1/2 to 2 inch pieces.
Drop into boiling chicken broth at low heat.
May add water, if needed, to add all the dumplings. Salt and pepper to taste.
When all the dumplings desired have been made, the last wad of dough will be for the top crust.
Roll just like dumplings.
Cut into strips.

title: foolproof chicken
directions: Mix soup, wine and rice and let stand several hours.
Put in casserole dish.
Arrange chicken on top.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, then uncover and bake another hour.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Cook 3 hours or until tender.

title: banana cake-pie
directions: Combine flour and melted margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch dish or pan and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely. Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup whipped topping. Spread over pastry in pan.
Add a layer of 2 or 3 bananas, sliced. Top with prepared instant pudding.
Sprinkle on the 1/2 box of crushed vanilla wafers.
Top with whipped topping.
Chill.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt. Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add sour cream alternately with flour mixture. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake in tube pan at 300° to 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Turn out of pan immediately. Serve plain or with frosting.

title: west texas fruit cake
directions: Blend eggs, sugar and butter until fluffy.
Mix in cocoa, 4 tablespoons sugar and water; melt over low heat.
Grind fine dates, coconut and pecans.
Add vanilla, flour and baking soda. Add all ingredients.
Mix well until smooth.
Bake in three 9-inch pans until firm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Cool.
Pull chicken off the bone.
Layer, starting with sauce as a bottom layer.
Then add chicken and cheese and continue to layer chicken, sauce and cheese.
Then bake until cheese has melted and sauce bubbles.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth, then beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla, then fold in whipping cream.
Spoon into crust and refrigerate.

title: kyla's treats
directions: Using one tube of refrigerator biscuits, cut into fourths. Drop each piece into hot oil and brown.
Remove; drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with sugar cinnamon mix.
One tube makes 32 bits.

title: crab and shrimp casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; blend in flour and mix well.
Stir in water and evaporated milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Drain crab meat well; remove bones and flake.
Add celery, green pepper, pimento and salt to sauce.
Pour into casserole. Top with crumbs and cheese.
Bake in a 300° oven for 35 minutes. Garnish with eggs.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pickled hot peppers
directions: First wash squash; cut ends off.
Slice 1/8 inch thick. Dice it, not too thick.	Every
layer
put
salt
on top.
Let squash stay for 18 hours in a
basket
with a weight on top to drain
the water
out.
Boil 1 gallon of white vinegar.
Then throw
in squash
for 1 1/2 minutes.	Take squash out and put back
in
the basket and let it stay all night with the weight on
top
to drain the vinegar out.
Take the squash out of the basket
and
put
in a
pan
and fix it with garlic, parsley, oregano,
Mazola oil and hot or sweet peppers.
Put the squash in
a
jar;
pack
it
up to the collar in the jar.
Make sure there
are
no bubbles in the jar or it will spoil.
Then fill top with oil.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
(I usually add chopped nuts and chocolate chips.)
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.
The more the better.

title: chili
directions: Put the lard in a pan.
When hot, slice the onion in it.
Let brown a very little, then add the ground beef.
Fry until meat is almost done, then add the kidney beans, tomatoes, potatoes, salt and pepper.

title: best ever coffee cake
directions: Place rolls in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Mix together brown sugar and pudding mix.
Sprinkle over rolls.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over pudding mixture, then sprinkle the pecans. Pour butter over mixture.
Place on counter and cover with paper towel.
Let rise overnight.

title: vegetable hot dish
directions: Boil together in same kettle first 3 vegetables; drain.
Heat onions, Cheez Whiz, soup and mushrooms until cheese is melted. Add sauce to drained vegetables.
Pour in casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be topped with flavored croutons.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni as directed on box.
Do not overcook.
Butter a large bowl.
Put cooked macaroni in bowl and mix in cheeses.
Add salt; stir and mix all ingredients together.
Cover with milk. Put butter on top with pepper to cover macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chops ole
directions: Place chops in casserole; cover with onions.
Mix tomatoes, chili powder, cumin, chilies and cayenne.
Pour over chops. Cover.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Sprinkle cheese on top; return to oven and melt.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and stick of melted oleo.
Pack into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs, 2 sticks oleo and powdered sugar together for no less than 15 minutes.
Very fluffy.
Spread this over the unbaked crumb crust.
Add sliced bananas and pineapple. Add layer of whipped topping.
Top with cherries and chopped nuts. Chill several hours or overnight.

title: easy peanut butter candy
directions: Put butter, sugar and milk in a large saucepan, at least 5 quarts.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 6 minutes. Take from heat; add vanilla and peanut butter.
Let set for 5 minutes, then add marshmallow cream and stir or mix with mixer until marshmallow cream is dissolved.
Pour into buttered large pan.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except the chips together in a large bowl.
Roll into balls and place on tray.
Freeze the balls for 20 minutes.
Next, melt the chips and add the paraffin if available. Use toothpicks to dip the balls into the heated chocolate.
Be sure to leave a peanut butter top.
(Hence the Buckeye.)

title: creamy baked potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine pie filling and lemon juice.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1-quart casserole.
Combine flour, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender or fork until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in oats.
Sprinkle mixture over pie filling.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with ice cream, if desired.

title: rhonda's red sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.

title: spoon bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy and combine with sugar until smooth as you can make it.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add this and 3 cups of sweet milk to egg mixture.
Combine cornmeal, flour and salt.
Mix well.
Add to the first mixture and beat until smooth.
Melt the butter in an oblong pan.
Add the remaining batter and pour remaining cup milk over the top.
(Do not stir.)
Bake at 400° until knife in center comes out clean (about 40 to 45 minutes).
Serve from pan in which it was baked with plenty of butter.

title: chocolate delight
directions: 1st Layer: Mix flour, butter and nuts. Press in Pyrex dish. Bake at 325° about 12 minutes.

title: shrimp and broccoli linguine
directions: Simmer shrimp in melted butter and olive oil.
Meanwhile, cook broccoli according to package directions.
Broccoli should be firm, not mushy.
Cut broccoli apart; add to shrimp.
Chop garlic and add to shrimp.
Simmer until shrimp are pink.
Do not overcook.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to molasses mixture.
Form into small balls; roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put green beans in casserole dish; put in soup and 1/2 of the fried onions.
Put Cheez Whiz in microwave.
After it is soft, pour in and mix everything together.
Heat oven to 350°; bake for 20 minutes.
Pour the other half of fried onions on top, then bake 10 more minutes.

title: white & cinnamon cookies
directions: Using tablespoon, roll into balls, dip into:
4 Tbsp. sugar mixed with 4 tsp. cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 10-15 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Top with butter.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: apple puffed pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a blender or large bowl, mix eggs, milk, flour, granulated sugar, vanilla, salt and cinnamon until blended.
If using a mixer, batter will be slightly lumpy.

title: moo goo gai pan(chicken with mushrooms and pea pods)
directions: Marinate chicken in wine while you are cutting the vegetables. Using a wok or large skillet, "stir-fry" onion, celery, pea pods, mushrooms and water chestnuts in the oil.
Stir constantly.
This will only take a couple of minutes.
Vegetable are done when they reach a bright color and are still crisp.
Remove from wok or skillet to an additional bowl.

title: jenny's dip
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature before starting.
Mix until well blended.
Serve with raw vegetables for dipping.

title: spinach salad with bacon dressing
directions: Wash spinach; remove any tough ribs.
Store in refrigerator with paper towel in a plastic bag to crisp.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage 8 minutes in small amount of water.
Put in casserole dish and add mushroom soup, grated cheese and almonds. Crush about 15 saltine crackers, mix with melted stick of margarine. Put over casserole.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: mediterranean chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken and cut into bite-size pieces.

In bowl, mix together mayonnaise, lemon juice, Tabasco, black pepper and basil. Mix in chicken, capers, celery, tomatoes, cheese and olives. Slice top off mini loaves lengthwise and hollow to form boats. Brush with melted butter, garlic and parsley.
Broil until golden and toasty.
Fill with salad mixture; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix together drained corn, chopped onion and chopped bell pepper.
Combine vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and pepper and bring to a boil.
Combine vegetables with liquid; refrigerate 24 hours.
May add tomato just before serving.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add egg.
Blend in flour, tartar, soda and salt.
Chill dough 2 hours.
Roll into small balls.
Roll balls into a sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes or until they are light brown.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: shipwreck
directions: Place cooked ground beef in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Add onions, 3 layers of potatoes, pork and beans, tomato soup and onion soup mix. Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; stir until crumbly.
Drain well.
Put bread cubes in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay cheese on top of bread.
Put sausage on top of cheese.
Beat eggs; add 2 cups of milk and seasoning as desired.
Pour liquid mixture over layered ingredients.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken pie
directions: Stew fryer until tender; cool.
Remove meat from bones.
Cook potatoes, carrots and celery together in a small amount of salted water.
Heat soup in saucepan with 1/2 cup milk.
Add peas and chicken to other vegetables.
Pour soup over this and mix slightly.
Pour into casserole.

title: peanut butter crispies
directions: Mix corn syrup and sugar in large pot.
Bring to boil over moderate heat while stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Mix in chocolate chips and peanut butter until blended.
Add Rice Crispies.
Mix and press into 13 x 9 pan.
Refrigerate to cool. Cut into bars.
Recipe easily doubles.
Enjoy!

title: tex mex dip
directions: 1st layer:
Cook taco meat like you were making tacos and place in pan for bottom layer.

title: german cabbage rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients except cabbage, tomato sauce and water together; make small balls.
Separate cabbage leaves and place in boiling water to soften.
Place one ball of meat in center of cabbage leaf; roll and secure with toothpick.
Place in Dutch oven; add tomato sauce and water.
Bring to boil and simmer about 1 1/2 hours.
Skim off fat as it is cooking.

title: "eggless" egg rolls
directions: Saute the onion, carrots and celery in small amount of oil. Add the cabbage, vegeburger and garlic powder.
Add water as needed to prevent sticking.
Set aside for at least an hour or prepare the night before.

title: baba ghamouj(eggplant dip)
directions: Broil eggplant with skin on, turning it frequently.
Or, you may cook eggplant in microwave for 6 minutes.
(Ensure the use of fork to make small holes in eggplant before it is placed in microwave.)
When cool, remove skin and mash like a potato.
Mix other ingredients; add to eggplant and blend well. Garnish with parsley and olive oil.
Serve with pita bread.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and pull stems from mushrooms.
Finely chop stems and add to remaining ingredients; mix well and stuff caps with mixture. Drizzle olive oil over top and bake at 475° for 12 minutes.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Cook chicken in water; pull off bone.
Saute onions and celery in 2 tablespoons of margarine.
Make roux from flour and oil.
When brown add a little water.
Add roux to chicken broth.
Then add crabmeat, chicken, shrimp, sauteed ingredients, hot sauce, Worcestershire sauce, gumbo file, salt and pepper, okra and tomato sauce.
Simmer for about 1 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread cherry filling in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add pineapple. Add raw cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut over cake mix. Drizzle melted butter over and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cherry-o-cream cheese pie
directions: In medium size bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Gradually add sweetened condensed milk; stir until well blended. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate (not freeze) for 2 to 3 hours.
Garnish with chilled pie filling before serving.

title: crustless quiche lorraine(microwave)
directions: Crisply cook and crumble bacon.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onions in bottom of a 9-inch glass pie plate or quiche dish.
Beat together remaining ingredients.
Pour over bacon mixture.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Mix in
double boiler, cook over heat for seven minutes. Beat with mixer while cooking.

title: my chicken supreme
directions: Mix soups, margarine and rice.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay cleaned and drained chicken on top. Sprinkle with paprika lightly.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: cinnamon peach cobbler
directions: Place sliced peaches in a row at bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle lemon over peaches.
Sprinkle cinnamon also.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and beaten egg.
Spread over peaches.
Pour melted butter over batter.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes. Top with whipped cream to serve.
Excellent served warm.

title: fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In double boiler, melt chocolate and butter, stirring. Cool slightly. Stir in sugar.
In a large bowl, beat eggs. Stir in chocolate mixture, then nuts, salt and vanilla. Pour into well-greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes. Refrigerate.
Serve with ice cream, if desired.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, milk and vanilla.
Pour over butter. Dribble the juice from the peaches over the batter, then add peaches.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar over the top and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: saucy tarragon chicken
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then coat the chicken with it.
Heat butter until hot.
Cook chicken until light brown (approximately 5 minutes each side).
Add carrots, tarragon, salt and wine.
Heat until boiling.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add zucchini and mushrooms.
Simmer for approximately 10 minutes until chicken is cooked.
Remove meat and vegetables.
Stir 1 tablespoon flour into water and add to skillet.
Boil and stir 1 minute. Serve over chicken.

title: ham and black-eyed pea soup
directions: In a 3 quart saucepan bring 4 cups water and black-eyed peas to boiling for 10 minutes; drain and rinse.
In a 4 quart electric crockery cooker, combine broth, water, ham, carrots, celery, onion, sage, thyme, salt and pepper.
Stir in peas.
Cook in slow cooker 6 to 7 hours.

title: creamed potatoes and peas
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add milk; stir and cook until thick and bubbly.
Add cooked potatoes and peas to hot mixture; heat through.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Add eggs and milk; beat.
Let stand 2 hours; beat again.
Pour out of measuring cup onto buttered, small, nonstick frying pan.
Turn and fry until light brown.
Serve with powdered sugar, syrup or fruit.
Serves 3 people.

title: potatoes chantilly
directions: Place potatoes in a steamer basket over boiling water.
Cover saucepan and steam 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain potatoes and mash in same saucepan.
Stir in cream over medium heat until heated throughout.
Add butter and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving.

title: banana pudding
directions: Slice banana into thin slices.
Cook other ingredients, except banana and wafers, until thickened.
Pour mixture over sliced bananas and wafers.

title: layered dip
directions: Mix seasoning and beans.
Layer the other ingredients however you wish.

title: peaches and cream crescent dessert
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate crescent dough into 2 long rectangles.
Place on ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press dough to cover pan.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and extract until smooth. Spread over dough.
Spoon fruit filling evenly over cream cheese mixture.
Combine flour, brown sugar and margarine.
Mix until crumbly.
Stir in almonds.
Sprinkle over fruit filling.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cream, cocoa and butter in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Continue stirring on medium to high heat until mixture makes a soft ball when dropped into a cup of cold water.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and pecans.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Pour into pan coated with margarine or butter and let cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until done.
Fry	hamburger
and onion in skillet until brown.
Drain
off fat.
Mix hamburger and onion with potatoes.
Add mushroom
soup.
Add cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add beef broth, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer, covered, about 15 minutes.
Put a slice of bread in each oven-proof bowl.
Pour soup into bowls; cover with cheese.
Bake in a 425° oven until cheese melts, 15 minutes.

title: bachelor broccoli
directions: Prepare broccoli and cut tomatoes in small chunks (1/2 inch size).
Steam broccoli and when it is soft, the last 1 1/2 minutes of steaming, add tomato chunks.
Put broccoli and tomato mixture in bowl.
Add desired amount of lemon pepper and stir.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Mix cake mix, eggs and oil.
Beat 4 minutes on high.
Add jello mixture and beat another 4 minutes. Bake in tube pan 1 hour at 325°.
Mix frozen lemonade and sugar well; pour over cake while hot.
Let stand 1 hour before removing from pan.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage; drain.
Cook meat, then add onion, olives, tomatoes, salt and pepper to taste and simmer.
Place cabbage leaves in baking dish and pour on meat mixture, just enough to cover cabbage.
Put layer of cheese on top, then another layer of cabbage, then another layer of meat mixture and then another layer of cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and hot.

title: bean pot
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and green pepper.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: pizzelles
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Batter will be thin.
Use about 1 tablespoon of batter per cookie.
Cook on hot pizzelle iron (ungreased) for about 35 seconds.

title: cranberry-oatmeal cookies
directions: Grease or line baking sheet with parchment paper.
In a large mixing bowl, beat margarine until smooth.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, honey, vanilla and salt; beat well.
Add flour; beat until well mixed.
Add oats and work with hands until well combined.
Add cranberries, walnuts and orange peel.
Stir well.
Shape into ball the size of small egg.
Place 3 inches apart on baking sheets.
Press each ball into 3-inch rounds.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until desired doneness.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes approximately 30 cookies.
Great for Christmas.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix together dry pudding, Cool Whip, pineapple and juice until well blended.
Stir in apples, marshmallows and peanuts until thoroughly combined.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 8.

title: frozen cranberry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Whip cream until soft peaks form.
Beat in sugar and vanilla.
Gradually add whipped cream to cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Fold in cranberry sauce. Spoon into crust and freeze overnight.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in a 350° oven for about one hour, or a little longer.
Test with toothpick.

title: cheese ball or log
directions: Mix cheeses with 1 teaspoon horseradish and 1 small onion, grated.
Roll in parsley or nuts or sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 3.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender. Excellent for pork, beef or chicken!

title: red beans and rice
directions: Saute diced turkey sausage, peppers and onion in just enough olive oil to coat the bottom of the pan. Add squash, mushrooms and creole seasoning to taste. Add tomatoes and red beans, including juice from both. Add Sea Legs and rice. Let simmer until juice is absorbed.

title: potato supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients (except corn flakes) in bowl.
Pour in baking dish.
Top with crushed corn flakes. Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Makes a lot.
Cut in half for smaller amount.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Put
oil
in
pot.
Cut
garlic
into
small pieces and brown. Leave garlic in pot.
Add puree and 2 cups water, then paste, basil, salt, oregano, pepper, parsley flakes and sugar. Bring sauce
to a boil and turn down to simmer.
Stir every 15 minutes. Brown
hamburger.
Add
to sauce and simmer 3 hours. Serve over spaghetti.

title: cheery cherry punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice, concentrates and cold water.
Mix well and freeze.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and mix well.

title: quick southwestern pizza
directions: Place oven rack on lowest position.
Heat oven to 450°. Grease cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Mix baking mix and water vigorously (about 20 strokes).
Turn onto floured surface.
Knead until dough is no longer sticky.
Press into cookie sheet.
Pinch edge to form 1/2-inch rim if making a circle or just press in pizza pan.
Mix chicken and salsa.
Sprinkle crust with 1 cup of cheese.
Top with onion, chicken mixture and bell pepper rings. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until crust is brown and cheese is bubbly.

title: seven layer dip
directions: In 9 x 13-inch dish, layer bean dip, then avocado dip.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning mix; layer on top of avocados.
Chop tomatoes and layer top of sour cream mixture, then green onions. Layer olives top of onions.
Top with cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Shred lettuce and add 2 chopped tomatoes, 2 boiled eggs (chopped) and 1 pound shrimp.
Toss together with 2 tablespoons mayonnaise.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt oleo, add flour and blend.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Add some cheese.
Cook until thick.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Yolk of one egg, one cup sugar, one tablespoon cornstarch, one-half teaspoon lemon extract, two tablespoons vinegar and one cup boiling water.
Cook until thick.
Beat the white of one egg until stiff, and add one tablespoon sugar.
Spread on top of pie and slightly brown.

title: clam chowder
directions: Mix together and heat.

title: bombay turkey salad
directions: Cut meat in 1/4 to 1/2-inch cubes and season with salt and pepper.
Blend all other ingredients into the mayonnaise.
Toss meat with mayonnaise and chill for at least 1 hour in refrigerator. Serves 4.

title: roasted garlic
directions: Place whole garlic pod in foil.
Pour over this the oil. Roast in a 350° oven for about 30 to 45 minutes.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to use and take off as many cloves as needed.
This will squeeze out like a paste.
May be used with mashed potatoes.
Rub over roast beef before cooking or any other place that you need garlic or mix with oleo for garlic butter spread.
Spread garlic with mayonnaise for sandwiches.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburg and onion; drain off fat.
Sprinkle mixture with flour; mix well.
Add tomato sauce.
Add garlic salt to taste, then add chili powder, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Serve hot with Doritos!

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate chips.
Mix in peanut butter.
In a large container empty cereal and pour chocolate mixture over them. Gently stir until coated.
Place powdered sugar in a large container; add cereal mixture.
Gently toss until well coated.

title: braised swiss steak
directions: Pat steak with damp paper towel to remove excess liquid. Combine bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Place steak on wooden board; sprinkle with half bread crumb mixture and pound with wooden mallet.
Repeat on other side; cut into 6 pieces.
Melt butter in Dutch oven.
Brown meat over medium heat.
Add tomatoes, onions, Worcestershire sauce, celery and garlic; bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 2 hours.

title: seafood salad
directions: Chop celery and onion, then combine with seafood.
Add lemon juice, Tabasco Sauce, white pepper and mayonnaise.
Stir well and serve with crackers and a green salad.

title: tomato teasers
directions: Cut out small hole in top of each tomato.
Combine bacon with Tabasco sauce; sprinkle mixture into tomatoes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together until mixed good.
You can put it on chicken, spareribs, make Sloppy Joes or whatever you want to put it on.
What you don't use can be kept in the refrigerator.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients, ending with flour.
Drop with spoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork or spoon.
Let cook at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pasta with vodka sauce
directions: Brown 1/2 cup olive oil with the cut up cloves or garlic.
Also add basil.
Let brown.
Shut off, then add vodka.
Wait 1 minute. Turn flame back on.
Add the whole tomatoes, heavy cream and salt and pepper to taste.
Pout over one pound of your favorite pasta.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread into pieces in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Blend in half the milk.
Add sugar and egg substitute.
Mix well.
Dice oleo on top and stir in vanilla, remaining milk and pineapple. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until firm.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients and put in 12 x 13-inch pan (approximately).
Sprinkle sugar, cinnamon and nuts over it. Bake at 350°.
Needs no frosting.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook first three ingredients until tender.
Saut butter and onions.
Then add flour, milk, salt, pepper and cheese.
Heat to boiling point; stir often.

title: coconut ice cream
directions: Blend flour with 2 tablespoons milk.
Add 1 cup milk and syrup.
Beat egg whole; add.
Cook over hot water, stirring until thick.
Cool.
Add top milk, vanilla and coconut.
Freeze to mush, using 8 parts crushed ice to 1 part ice cream salt.
Remove dasher.
Cover.
Pack in 4 parts ice to 1 part salt for 3 hours. When serving, sprinkle toasted coconut over top.
Makes 1 quart. May be frozen in electric refrigerator, stirring once after mush has formed.
Serves 8.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together, sugar, butter and peanut butter.
Form into small 1-inch balls. Melt chips in microwave.
Dip balls by toothpick or fork. Let cool on buttered sheet.

title: toasted cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix above together and spread on bread.
Assemble bread in stacks of 3.
Remove crust, spread in between slices and on sides and top of bread stacks. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
These can be made ahead and frozen.
Place in cookie sheets until well frozen, then place in freezer bags.

title: panocha
directions: Combine sugars and salt in saucepan; add 1/2 cream.
Cook, stirring until sugars dissolve.
Cover sugar mixture and cook 2 minutes.
Remove cover.
Stir constantly and add remaining cream gradually so sugar mixture never stops boiling.
Cook panocha syrup until soft ball forms in icy-cold to lukewarm water.
Add flavoring and beat until panocha is creamy.
Pour panocha into shallow 8-inch pan; mark into squares when almost cool.

title: charlie's barbecue ribs
directions: Parboil ribs 1 hour (2 tablespoon salt in water).
Drain and place in flat pan.
Mix other stuff and simmer 20 minutes while ribs boil.
Pour over ribs.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Smoke for 4 hours turning every 1/2 hour in a smoker where pecan or mesquite fire is not directly under meat.
Keep temperature between 225° and 300°.
Baste with remaining marinade on final turning.
Serve 4 along with slaw and potatoes.
Fat grams 65; calories 400.

title: easy salmon croquettes
directions: Add the egg and flour into the drained can of salmon.
Just before frying, stir the baking powder into the 1/4 cup salmon liquid and stir until frothy.
Now add to first mixture.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil.
Turn once.

title: button mushrooms (marinated)
directions: Use 1-quart canning jar with lid.
Add ingredients; drain mushrooms.
Shake well and refrigerate for day or so before using. I usually shake about once a day.
These keep up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: molasses icebox cookies
directions: In a pan, heat molasses and shortening, stirring, on low heat. Remove and add sugar. Cool.
Add unbeaten egg, stirring well. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Form in rolls and chill for 4 or 5 hours.
Slice and bake in a 375° oven.
Very good!

title: carefree chicken casserole
directions: Combine peas and carrots, soup, water and milk in a medium sized saucepan.
Bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer 3 minutes. Spoon half of the mixture into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Spoon the cooked rice over the vegetable mixture.
Layer the chicken over the rice and top with remaining vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: heavenly delight chocolate cake
directions: Mix Crisco, eggs and soda to flour.
Then add flour and buttermilk alternately.
Bake in 3 layer pans at 350°.
Use the other half for icing.

title: angie's magic pie
directions: Put 1/2 of the softened ice cream into the graham cracker crust.
Spread crushed cookies onto the ice cream.
Squirt about 1/2 of the Magic Shell on top of the cookies.
Spoon the rest of the ice cream on top and smooth it out.
Squirt the remaining Magic Shell on top.
You can make a design with it or just smooth it over the whole pie.
Place the pie in the freezer until it becomes firm again (about 2 or 3 hours).
Cut and serve and put a little whip cream on top, if you like.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Gradually add the sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine the flour and baking powder.
Add this to the creamed mixture, alternating with the milk and mixing well after each addition.
Stir in the vanilla and lemon flavorings.
Pour the batter into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each.
Add lemon extract and flour, one cup at a time.
Add soda, nuts and raisins.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Makes 2 loaf pans, greased and floured.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Add biscuits; stir well. Spoon mixture into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put the coconut and pecans on bottom of pan (mixed).
Fix cake mix per directions, put on top of mixture.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Let cream cheese soften, then beat with eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Place wafer cookies in midget paper cups.
Add cheese filling 3/4 full. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let cool, then add toppings.
Makes 30.

title: asian beef noodles
directions: In medium bowl, combine beef and oil; toss to coat.
Break noodles into 4 pieces; reserve seasoning packet.
Cook noodles as directed on package and drain.
Stir-fry beef in hot skillet until no longer pink.
(Do not overcook.)
Remove beef and keep warm.
In same skillet, combine noodles, steak sauce, carrot, cilantro and reserved seasoning.
Cook over medium heat until hot.
Return beef to skillet; mix lightly.
Sprinkle with peanuts.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa.
Pour in milk and melted butter.
Stir. Put in microwave on High for 2 minutes. Take out and add vanilla and nuts. Stir up good.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish and let firm.

title: oven baked chicken and rice
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chicken on top. Cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: orange tea cookies(makes 4 to 5 dozen)
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Blend in next 3 ingredients.
Add next 2 ingredients.
Mix.
Using 1/2 teaspoon of mixture, shape into balls.
Roll in unbeaten egg white, then roll in chopped walnuts.
Place on well-greased cookie sheet.
Pat down to thin cookie and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chicken reuben
directions: Line an oblong baking dish or pan with aluminum foil.
Lay the chicken on the foil.
Squeeze the juice from the sauerkraut and spread over the chicken.
Lay cheese slices over the sauerkraut. Spread Thousand Island dressing over the cheese.
Seal with aluminum foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix whipping cream and brown sugar well (may warm in microwave). Add pecans and coat well. Spread out onto a well-greased cookie sheet. Bake 20 minutes or until just slightly browned.

title: blueberry squares
directions: Mix well, adding eggs one at a time.
Blend mixture except for blueberries.
Batter will be thick.
Put most of the batter on the bottom of greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add blueberries over batter, then add the rest of the batter by spoonful over blueberries.
Place in a 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls in hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Makes about 35.

title: delicious rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in 2 1/2 cups water until dry, about 30 minutes. Scald milk in another pan.
In another container, place sugar, eggs, cornstarch and evaporated milk; mix well.
Add to heated milk.
Stir continuously; when mixture starts to boil lightly, remove from stove.
Add rice and vanilla.
Place in large bowl. Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Yield:
20 servings.
May add raisins.

title: 24 hour cole slaw
directions: Shred first 3 ingredients.
Then sprinkle sugar over mixture. Let it sit.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Pour over cabbage mixture; mix and cover.
Let set in refrigerator 24 hours.

title: sunday best corn
directions: In a skillet cook bacon over medium heat until crisp. Remove to paper towels and drain reserving 1 Tbsp. drippings. Saute mushrooms and onion in drippings until tender. Stir in corn, cheese sauce and bacon. Cook and stir for 2-4 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: *Substitute peanut butter chips for peanut butter fudge.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients real well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Then pour a little ketchup over the top.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: If mushrooms are not clean, gently rinse and dry on paper towels.
Slice in half.
In a bowl, combine other ingredients, except endive, and toss well with mushrooms.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 to 2 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef with diced onion.
Drain grease.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Wash, peel and grate potatoes.
Add sugar, butter and nutmeg. Cook over low to medium heat, stirring often, for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: one pot pork chop dinner
directions: Brown chops; pour off fat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover and cook for 45 minutes to an hour, until tender.

title: taco soup(sante fe soup)
directions: Chop up tomatoes in blender. Cook on medium for approximately 45 minutes. Brown and drain ground chuck and add to tomatoes. Add all other ingredients,
using all juices. Garnish with sour cream and shredded cheese. Serve with taco chips.

title: corn pie
directions: Combine ingredients and place in 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: *If fruit you choose has syrup, you may use syrup and milk combined to form 3/4 cup.

title: bite-size corn dogs
directions: Cut the sausages into small bite-size pieces.
Mix all the ingredients together and stir them well.
Dip the sausages in the batter and let the excess drain off.
Drop the batter-dipped sausages into the hot cooking oil.
Drain well on paper towels before serving.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Place on cookie sheet and cook in 200° oven until oil is absorbed about 20 minutes.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Combine crumbs and butter.
Firmly press into bottom and up sides of a 9-inch pie plate. Chill.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown together the ground beef and onion; drain off grease. Add remaining ingredients.
Season as desired; simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add water, if needed.

title: vegetable medley casserole
directions: Butter a 1-quart casserole dish. Cook vegetables until tender; put in buttered dish. Add the cooked rice and gently toss with the vegetables.

title: flour tortillas from scratch
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt through your fingers.
Add corn oil or bacon drippings.
Mix thoroughly.
Dough will be ready to knead when it does not stick to your hands.
Knead for 1 minute.

title: gramma's gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and egg; beat well. Add combined dry ingredients; mix well.
Roll in 1-inch balls; roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
They are done when they are no longer "puffed" and the cracks appear dry.

title: pink lady punch
directions: Slowly add cranberry juice to sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add pineapple juice, then ginger ale.
Stir to blend. Add frozen block of strawberries, if desired.

title: frozen green peas
directions: Shell and wash peas.
cover with water; boil on top of stove until color changes a little.
Take off; drain water and rinse with cold water.
Put into freezer bags.
(Butter beans may be frozen the same way.)

title: salmon patties
directions: Heat Crisco in skillet over medium-high heat.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Spoon into oil; brown on both sides, about 5 minutes on each side.

title: puffed-up pizza casserole
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, cook the ground beef until brown.
From the meat, drain off the fat and discard it.
Stir in the tomato sauce, chopped onion, chopped green pepper, water, spaghetti sauce mix, oregano, minced garlic and bottled hot pepper sauce.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer the mixture, covered, for 10 minutes.

title: asparagus chicken bake
directions: Melt butter in an 8-inch square pan; drain asparagus, reserving 1/2 cup asparagus liquid.
Arrange asparagus in butter; add chicken.
Sprinkle with the cheese.
Prepare muffin mix according to package directions.
Carefully spoon mixture on top of cheese.
Bake in a 400° oven 30 minutes or until muffin top is brown.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: In medium bowl, toss meat cubes with flour to coat.
In Dutch oven or 5-quart saucepan, brown meat in hot oil.
Add onions, paprika, salt, pepper and beef broth.
Mix well.
Cover.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Shortly before serving, cook noodles to desired doneness as directed on package.
Drain.
Toss with margarine and poppy seed.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine
flour,
coconut,
sugar
and	salt.
Stir
in unbeaten egg
whites
and
almond extract.	Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls
onto	greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes, until edge is brown.
Remove at once with spatula and cool on wax paper or paper towel.
Store, covered, until completely cooled.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.
(Keeps well.)

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: The success of this cake is beating well.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add sour cream.
Add sifted flour a little at a time.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in a tube pan.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine and mix thoroughly all ingredients; refrigerate overnight.
Serve with sliced radishes, sliced cucumbers, raw cauliflower buds, cherry tomatoes and carrot, celery and green pepper sticks.

title: rhubarb cream, pie
directions: Mix rhubarb 1 cup sugar, egg yolks and flour.
Pour into crust.
Bake slowly as for custard pies. Beat egg whites and add 2 tablespoons sugar.
Beat
until stiff peaks form.
Put meringue on top of pie and brown at 350°.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add salt and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in flour.
Mix well.
In a 10-inch tube cake pan that is greased and floured, place nuts on bottom.
Add cake batter. Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: christmas punch
directions: Blend bananas; add other ingredients.
Put in freezer.
Stir every hour until makes a slush.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: chicken monterey
directions: Rub chicken breasts with salt.
In skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, brown chicken on all sides.
Arrange in 3-quart casserole.
Spoon off all but 2 tablespoons drippings from skillet.
In skillet, cook onion until tender.
Stir in flour until blended. Gradually stir in milk, water until smooth.
Stir in catsup, rosemary, bouillon and 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Cook stirring constantly until sauce thickens slightly.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Stir in artichoke hearts and green beans.
Bake 20 minutes longer.
Skim excess fat from casserole.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning.
Roll chicken pieces in cheese mixture to coat lightly. Set remaining cheese mixture aside.
Arrange pieces in a baking dish.

title: bonnie's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 2 minutes; drain.
Put in a small casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream together; pour over broccoli.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and soup.
Combine all other ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: no cook fruit balls
directions: Using a food processor or food grinder with a coarse blade, grind together dried prunes, whole dates, dried apricots, almonds and raisins.
Turn ground mixture into a mixing bowl and add frozen orange juice concentrate and honey or molasses.
Stir until well combined.
Shape mixture into balls and roll in coconut. Store tightly covered in refrigerator.
Yields 36 balls.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well and add the next 6 ingredients.
Mix well and add remaining ingredients.
Pout into 3 (9-inch) greased and floured (or sprayed) cake pans.
Bake about 20 or 25 minutes.
Frost with Seven Minute Frosting and 2 cups of black walnuts.

title: oyster stew
directions: Drain "liquor" from oysters
and put "liquor" in saucepan. Bring to a boil and
skim.	Add oysters and simmer until edges begin to curl.
Slowly
add milk, butter and seasonings. Be careful not to boil!

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs.
Sift flour and spices. Add applesauce to sugar and margarine, then add gumdrops (cut into small cubes).
Add raisins and nuts that have been floured.
Add flour to mixture.
Last, add soda and hot water and mix well.
Add soda to hot water and mix well before adding to mixture.

title: chicken fajita - chi chi style
directions: Marinate chicken in Margarita mix (has no tequila) for a few hours.
Cook on grill.
Cut into thin strips.
Grill onion and green pepper in margarine.
Add a few drops of Margarita mix. Place some of the ingredients on tortilla, roll up and enjoy! Serve with Spanish rice or Cajun rice.

title: jane's peanut butter pie
directions: Blend the cream cheese and peanut butter.
Fold in Cool Whip and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill for several hours.

title: broccoli casserole(microwave)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover; cook on High for 10 minutes.
Stir.
Cook, uncovered, for 2 minutes on High.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and thinly slice potatoes; arrange in 3-quart glass casserole.
Sprinkle on flour, salt and onion.
Pour milk over all.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with lid or plastic wrap. Microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Stir.
Re-cover and continue cooking on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Let stand.

title: beef sandwiches
directions: Place all ingredients
in
crock-pot.
Cook
all day or bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Will fill around 20 large buns.

title: spicy rice
directions: Saute celery, onions and green pepper in butter until tender. Toss vegetables together with sausage, sage, salt, rice.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: best ever congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water, add pineapple.
Refrigerate until soft jelly.
Mix cream cheese, salad dressing and milk. Spread over Jell-O.
Add pecans and chill until firm

title: chili
directions: With constant stirring, thoroughly brown meat in melted fat. Add seasonings, garlic, onion, celery, green pepper and tomatoes. Cover and simmer over low for about 1 hour. Add kidney beans and cook an additional 10 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: In covered saucepan, cook carrots, onion and celery in butter over low heat until tender.
Stir in flour and add broth and salt. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in cream or milk and cheese until cheese melts and soup is heated through.
Do not boil.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: dressing for salad
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Add egg with juice.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add butter and cool. Spread over firm gelatin.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese. Refrigerate.
Serve in squares.

title: vegetable "pizza"
directions: Cut up all vegetables.
Flatten; roll dough in a pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 7 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and dressing.
Mix together.
Spread mixture over cooled crust (it will be thick). Sprinkle vegetables over it.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Keep refrigerated until served.

title: quiche
directions: Fry and crumble sausage patties or use 4 bacon strips (crumble after cooking them).
Line casserole with cubed bread squares.
Add meat on top of bread, then add cheese on top of meat.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard.
Then pour over cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Boil for 2 minutes first 5 ingredients, stir in peanut butter and vanilla, then stir in oatmeal.
Stir fast and drop on wax paper with teaspoon.
Let cool until you can pick them off.
If double recipe, use 5 cups oats.
If desired, add 1/2 cup nuts.

title: fried green beans
directions: Cut up bacon in pieces and fry.
Drain off most of the grease, leaving about 1 tablespoon in skillet.
Add green beans and diced onion.
Let cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes.
Add water and cover.
Let simmer over low heat, about an hour, stirring about every 15 minutes.
Remove lid and let brown a little before serving.
Salt and pepper as desired.

title: taboli
directions: Add water to taboli mix.
Salt and pepper; set aside.
Finely chop green onions, tomato and cucumber; add to taboli mix.
Add oil and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Make a day ahead.
Stir and serve.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Combine cream cheese, half and half and butter in a heavy bottomed saucepan.
Stir over low heat until cheese mixture is soft, creamy and butter is melted.
Blend in the frosting mix and stir to blend well.
Add peppermint extract and food coloring of your choice.
You may divide the whole batch to make 2 to 3 different colors.
Roll mixture into balls or drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Press with fork or stamp with cookie stamp for decorative design, if desired. Let mints stand, uncovered, at room temperature until firm and outside is dry.
Inside should still be creamy.

title: aunt lela's creole carrots
directions: Slice and drain carrots.
Saute green peppers in oleo (we use just enough to saute pepper).
When tender, add brown sugar and catsup.
Stir to mix and melt sugar.
Pour over carrots and reheat.
Can be served hot or cold.
Can be made ahead.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Spread the ingredients in order in pizza pan.
Dip with plain tortilla chips.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: hot oil pasta dish
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
On low heat, cook garlic and olive oil; do not allow to brown.
It will turn bitter. Add red pepper flakes.
Turn off heat and allow to sit and cool (around 15 minutes).
Add 1/2 cup water.
Toss over pasta.

title: karen's marinara sauce
directions: Saute garlic and parsley flakes in oil.
Add the can of sauces, then sugar.
Add tomato paste.
Blend good, then heat thoroughly.
Serve with French bread or noodles.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in 10-inch skillet until brown; drain.
Stir in taco sauce, refried beans and 1 cup cheese. Heat, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted.
Pour into serving dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese on top.
Use Bugles to dip in sauce.

title: strawberry icebox cake
directions: Dissolve jello, sugar and salt in 1 1/4 cups boiling water. Remove from heat and add strawberries.
Stir until ice is melted and strawberries are soft.
Mixture will almost be set.
Add whipped cream and mix slightly.
Put in cake in pieces and set in icebox at least 6 hours before serving.
Also, use Strawberry Frosting.

title: garlic roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Cut the potatoes in half or quarters and place in a bowl with the olive oil, salt, pepper and garlic; toss until the potatoes are well coated. Transfer the potatoes to a sheet pan and spread out into one layer. Roast in the oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until browned and crisp. Flip twice during cooking with a spatula in order to ensure even browning. Remove from the oven; toss with the parsley. Season to taste and serve hot.

title: olive dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread, the day before.
Cover; refrigerate.
Cut out center of bread to form a bowl.
Place dip in bowl (bread); cut remaining bread into cubes for dipping.

title: jello salad
directions: Use juice drained from fruit and add enough water to make 1 cup.
Bring to a boil and add jello.
Chill until syrup.
Whip milk and add fruit, nuts and milk to jello.
Mix thoroughly and chill until set.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Spray oblong pan with Pam.
Sprinkle pecans and coconut in bottom.
Mix cake mix by box directions.
Pour on top of nuts. Melt margarine and blend with confectioners sugar and cream cheese. Beat vigorously until creamy.
Spoon onto top of cake mix.
Bake in a 300° to 325° oven for 1 hour or longer.
Do not overbake.

title: sand art brownies(brownies in a jar)
directions: Pour into greased 9 x 9 pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Place the beef roast in a roasting pan.
Pour the chili sauce over it.
Put in
enough
water
to make 1/4-inch in the pan. Cover and roast at 225° for 4 to 6 hours.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add fruit, nuts and chocolate bits. Beat eggs and add sugar slowly.
Mix well with rest of ingredients.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix well in a large punch bowl.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Cream the cream cheese and add salsa.
Spread lightly on tortilla shell and roll secure with toothpick.
Chill.
To serve cut in 3/4-inch pieces.

title: ambrosia crumble
directions: In a large bowl, mix the pineapple, oranges, bananas, coconut, lemon juice and sugar.
Set aside.

title: baked bean medley
directions: Brown onions and add to beans.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over beans.
Sprinkle bacon on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: broccoli nut casserole
directions: Cook broccoli with salt according to package directions; drain.
Add soup, mayonnaise and pecans.
Add eggs and onion. Pour into greased 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Mix well.
Add nuts last.
Roll into rolls.
Bake at 300° until firm.
Cool and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Sift flour and measure to equal 2 1/2 cups; sift again with salt.
Add a small amount of the chopped pecans to flour and salt mixture.
Combine with the batter mix; fold in the apples and remaining pecans.
Bake in a prepared Bundt or angel food cake pan at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Blend flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nuts.
Set aside. Combine egg with lemon peel and beat well.
Combine with remaining liquid ingredients in order.
Beat well.
Add the liquid mixture all at once to the dry ingredients and stir until just moistened. Turn into 2 buttered loaf pans.

title: chocolate cherry fruitcake
directions: Mix
ingredients
with	wooden	spoon
until moistened. Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cheese wheels
directions: Spread each slice of ham, roast beef or turkey with about 2 teaspoons cream cheese.
Starting at short end, roll up.
cut into 2-inch pieces.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix cornstarch and water; set aside.

Using clean wok, put vinegar and sugar in and cook until sugar is dissolved. add tomatoes, pepper and pineapple chunks. Cook 3 minutes, stirring. Add cornstarch and cook 3 to 4 minutes, stirring until mixture is clear.

title: ham rolls
directions: Cream together room temperature cream cheese and enough garlic salt to taste.
You don't want too much.
Spread diagonally across meat wafers.
Roll; cut in half.
Then garnish with toothpick and olive.

title: tangy vegetable salad
directions: Mix all together (dressing and vegetables); marinate overnight.
Stir several times after placing in refrigerator. Drain well
1 hour before serving.
(With steak and baked potato, WOW, what a meal!)

title: mexi bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix lightly. Seal bowl and chill for several hours.

title: valentine strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, flour and gelatin.
Add oil. Beat in eggs.
Add water and strawberries.
Mix well. Bake at 350° in greased tube pan for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost with the following icing.

title: spinach and pasta casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and rinse macaroni.
Melt Velveeta cheese, milk and margarine.
Mix macaroni and cheese mixture thoroughly.
Add well drained spinach, mushrooms and Parmesan cheese.
Mix.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cover with cheese slices.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
If it is to be served later, cover with lid and reheat in oven or microwave.
This makes a casserole for a large group.
Halve the recipe for a smaller group.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and add milk until crackers are soaked and real moist.
Dab with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: relish
directions: Put vegetables through medium food chopper or chop in food processor.
Put in crock with 1/2 cup pickling salt mixed with one gallon water.
Let stand overnight.
Drain and squeeze water out. Boil together sugar, vinegar, turmeric, mustard and celery seed. Simmer for 1 hour.
Add ground vegetables.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes. Mix 3 tablespoons cornstarch in a little water and cook a few minutes.
Put in sterilized jars.

title: chicken biscuit stew
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In ovenproof 10-inch skillet, melt margarine.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add chicken broth and milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add chicken, onion, peas and carrots.
Simmer until hot and bubbly.
Arrange biscuits over top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 or 25 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: lemon dream pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip as directed on package, using 1 cup milk in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining 1 3/4 cups milk to pudding mix. Whip, then beat at high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook pasta shells and drain.
Thaw broccoli and drain well. Mix in a large bowl all ingredients except shells.
Fill each shell with mixture and place in baking dish.
Top with tomato sauce and bake at 350° until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: apple quiche
directions: Melt butter in pot.
Add apples and vanilla and cover.
Cook until soft, but not mushy on moderate heat, shaking pan occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar, adding more if needed.
Place apple filling in the pie shell.
Blend the beaten eggs with the cream and pour over the apples.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes or until custard is just set.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Serves 6.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed until smooth; gradually add sugar and vanilla and beat well.
Stir in candy coating and pecans.
Spread into a buttered 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: butterscotch picnic bars
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar, remove from heat and cool 10 minutes.
Add eggs, beat until smooth.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into butter mixture. Add butterscotch morsels and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread evenly in greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven about 25 minutes. Cool.
Makes 50 bars.

title: yogurt herb biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients until soft dough forms. Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Gently smooth dough into ball on floured cloth-covered board.
Knead 5 times.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured 2-inch cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: dannica's banana tea bread
directions: Cream shortening until light; add sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients, then bananas.
Spoon into two greased bread pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool on wire rack.

title: italian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in 1 (14 x 20-inch) Reynolds oven cooking bag (large size); place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add spaghetti sauce to bag.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
Add chicken and green pepper to bag.
Turn bag to coat chicken with sauce.
Arrange chicken in even layer.
Close bag with nylon tie; cut 6 (1/2-inch) slits in top.
Bake until tender, 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve over hot pasta.
Serves 4.

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat; place noodles over meat.
Pour juice over noodles with some Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer 1/2 hour.
Mix in sour cream just before serving.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients into a bowl.
With 2 knives or a pastry blender, cut in butter until the mixture is the consistency of coarse cornmeal.
Add milk and stir briefly until dough leaves the side of the bowl.
Turn out on floured board and knead gently and quickly about 20 seconds.
Pat out dough to 1/2-inch thick. Cut with biscuit cutter and place on lightly oiled baking sheet. Brush tops with milk and bake in preheated oven at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound flour into slice of beef.
May cut beef into cubes, if desired.
Brown beef; add salt after browned.
Add vegetables. Pour tomato sauce or soup over all.
Cover pan.
Simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: country cobbler
directions: Spray an 8 x 8-inch pan (glass) with Pam.
Melt margarine or butter in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix together flour, sugar and milk. Pour over butter; do not stir.
Add 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 cups fruit (peaches, berries, apples or cherries).
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Serve hot with ice cream.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Drain off broth and pour tomato sauce over meat.
Top with shredded cheese (any kind).
Bake another 1/2 hour.

title: texas tortilla soup
directions: In large pot, saute onion, garlic and ground meat in oil.
Add remaining ingredients, except chips and cheese.
Simmer 1 hour. Place chips in bottom of bowl, then soup and top with cheese.

title: heath bar cookies
directions: Cover large cookie sheet (jelly roll pan) with aluminum foil, shiny side up.
Grease well with butter.

Arrange 40 to 48 saltine crackers, one by one, on cookie sheet until pan is covered. Combine in saucepan, sugar and butter; boil 2 1/2 minutes only. Pour over crackers and bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Will turn light golden.
Remove and sprinkle chocolate chips over top. Spread over as frosting.
Cut and score before they are set up.

title: creamy walnut cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together into a bowl. Add brown sugar, shortening and 3/4 cup milk.
Mix enough to dampen flour, beat 2 minutes (if using electric mixer, use low speed). Add eggs, 1/4 cup milk, flavoring, nuts and beat 1 minute.
Bake in 2 greased 8-inch layer cake pans in 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: chicken gumbo file
directions: Rinse and prepare the chicken.
Cut the ham into 1/2-inch cubes.
In a 6-quart Dutch oven, saute the chicken in butter for approximately 20 minutes.
Remove the chicken.
Add the ham until brown (approximately 5 minutes).
Remove.
Stir flour into remaining fat in Dutch oven; cook over medium heat, stirring, until flour is browned.
Add onion and garlic and cook, stirring, until onion is tender.
Add salt, pepper, thyme, red pepper, parsley, bay leaf, tomatoes and 1 cup water; bring to boiling.
Add chicken and ham and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Next add shrimp and green pepper, simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove the ham, chicken and shrimp. Bring mixture in Dutch oven to a boil.
Stir in the file, cook until it thickens.
Pour sauce over chicken mixture.
Serve over white rice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all pie ingredients in large bowl and mix on low speed for 1 minute.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: taco salad
directions: Start with lettuce and layer vegetables in large bowl.
Put tomatoes on top.
Fry ground meat and drain.
Add taco mix and spread on top of tomatoes.
Add cheese.
Crush chips and sprinkle on top just before serving.
Mix taco sauce and mayonnaise to make dressing for salad.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Place diced
chicken
in
10 x 2-inch covered casserole dish (Corning Ware skillet).
Dissolve bouillon in 1/4 cup hot water. Spread
onion
over chicken; add noodles and seasoning package. Add cheese.
Pour
bouillon
and
soup over the top. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Mix
eggs,
oil, sugar, squash and vanilla together and beat. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° in 2 loaf pans for 1 hour.
Use a powdered sugar icing.

title: nancy's fancy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy 2 1/3 to 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a full, rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching. Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: clubhouse sandwich
directions: Butter	toast.	Cover
one
slice
of toast with turkey slices and
lettuce
leaf,
then place another slice of toast with mayonnaise on top.	Add bacon and tomato slices and cover with last
piece
of
toast.
Fasten
with
toothpicks.	Cut sandwich diagonally	into 4 triangles and stand them upright. Serve with olives, pickles and potato salad.

title: mary's marvelous macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt in a mixing bowl.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract.
Stir in almonds.
Mix well. Drop from teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Garnish with candied cherry halves (if desired).
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes (or until edges of the cookies are golden brown). Remove from baking sheets immediately.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: swedish cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add egg yolk and mix well.
Add vanilla and sifted flour.
