Roll dough into small ball and dip into egg white which has been slightly beaten.
Roll in walnuts.
Put on greased baking sheet and press down center with handle of knife.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until light brown.
While still warm, put apple jelly in each center.

title: apple pancake
directions: Mix real well.
Heat oven to 425°.
In a large Pyrex pie plate, put in 1/2 stick of butter and put in oven while warming it.
Pour batter into pie plate when heat is at 425° and bake for 20 minutes.
Peel 2 large apples and slice as for pie and cook for 5 to 7 minutes (until soft) in 1/2 to 3/4 cup of orange juice. (Do this while pancake is baking.)
Spread cooked apples over pancake and put in oven for 5 minutes more.
Slice, eat and enjoy!

title: chicken-spanish style
directions: Salt and pepper chicken lightly; flour.
Melt butter in large skillet; add onions and cook until transparent.
Add shortening and fry chicken until brown.
Add green peppers, olives, parsley, tomatoes and seasonings.
Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: smoked mullet appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pack into bowl to mold.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: everyday casserole
directions: Cook 2 cups dry noodles in salt water.
Drain noodles.
Toss in 1/3 cube margarine.
In casserole alternate layer of Campbell's soup and drained noodles.
Top with seasoned croutons.
Bake or heat in microwave only to warm all ingredients.
Serve immediately.

title: chocolate crunch pie
directions: Prepare pudding mix as directed with 1 cup milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Stir 1 cup cookies and the "rocks" into pudding mixture. Spoon into pie crust.
Sprinkle with remaining cookies.
Freeze until firm, 4 hours.
Garnish with gumdrop flowers or gummy worms. Let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes before serving.

title: monterey cod
directions: Can be made in any portion size desired.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Can add 1 can mixed vegetables.

title: tastier tuna
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, tuna, pecans, celery, onion, pepper and water chestnuts, mixing well to evenly distribute and coat with mayonnaise.
Adjust seasonings to taste. If salad is dry, add a bit more mayonnaise.
Serve as a sandwich filling or as a salad on a bed of lettuce.
Yields 8 servings.

title: shrimp salsa
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours to allow flavors to blend.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks thoroughly.
Mix
sugar and cocoa with flour and add to eggs.
Mix, then add milk.
Cook over medium heat until boiling.
Stir often.
Add vanilla, then pour into browned pie crust and bake at 350°.
When done, cover with meringue.

title: hoe's micro-chicken wings
directions: Cut tips off chicken wings; cut wings at joint and arrange on a 9-inch round glass baking dish.
Combine in an 8-cup glass measure, white wine, soy sauce, honey, pineapple juice, garlic powder and ginger root.
Pour over wings and refrigerate overnight.
Cover with wax paper; microwave on High for 4 minutes. Turn wings over; brush with marinated sauce.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until no longer pink.
Stand 5 minutes, covered.

title: rice, corn and cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except paprika.
Pour into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: 20 minute chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken into egg and then coat with bread crumbs.
Melt margarine in large frying pan on medium heat.
Place chicken in frypan and brown on each side for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to low setting.

title: curry's special
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Dump into large pot. Cook macaroni according to directions; drain. Dump into pot with hamburger. Add remaining ingredients and heat until hot.
Serve with garlic toast and have a complete meal.

title: tyvola's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water.
Drain.
Add macaroni layer to casserole dish, then layer of cheese and layer of butter.
Repeat until casserole dish is full.
Then add milk.
Bake in microwave on High for 6 to 10 minutes.
After 3 minutes, stir.

title: fruity cherry punch(serves 24)
directions: Blend bananas and strawberries together.
Mix with next 5 ingredients; chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cook roast until tender; pull apart.
Mix meat with rest of ingredients in heavy pan.
Stir and cook over low heat about 45 minutes.
Serve on kaiser or sourdough buns.
Venison works very well instead of beef.

title: lamb sauce for lamb on the rod
directions: Put in blender and blend until foamy.
Can add pepper rings.

title: peace pudding
directions: Blend all ingredients together until smooth, then you make the world a better place.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Combine flour and baking powder.
Cream butter and sugar; add flour mix and mix until smooth.
Work in chopped almonds.
Add gin and almond extract and mix well.
Roll in small balls and set on lightly floured cookie sheet; flatten balls to 1/4-inch and push blanched 1/2 almond into center of each cookie.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until faintly browned.

title: baked lipton soup and potatoes
directions: Coat potato chunks in oil.
Place Lipton mix in bag and add potatoes; shake.
Put all in a pan and bake at 450° until potatoes are tender.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Heat and let simmer in pot on stove or in slow cooker and the aroma will fill the house.
Serve to guests when they arrive.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans.
Pour into pie shell. Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat, onion, celery and pepper in skillet.
Combine ingredients.
Place 2 slices bacon on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: low-fat meat loaf
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into a baking dish and bake at
for
1 hour.
Drain off fat while baking.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Cook oats in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Let stand 20 minutes. Cream oleo, 1 cup brown sugar, white sugar, eggs and vanilla. Beat until real creamy.
Add oats; stir in flour, nutmeg, soda and cinnamon.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
When cool, add topping.

title: snickers cookies
directions: Cut dough into 1/4-inch thick slices. Place a candy bar on each slice and wrap dough around it. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool on wire racks. Yield: 2 to 2 1/2 dozen.

title: apple crisp
directions: Pour 1 can of Eagle Brand milk over all.
Bake approximately 30 minutes.
When cool, cut in small squares.
Very rich!

title: hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix all together well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: glorified pork chops
directions: In skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, cook chops 1/2 at a time with onion for 10 minutes, or until browned on both sides. Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup and water.
Reduce heat to low. Cover; simmer for 10 minutes, or until chops are fork-tender, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine macaroni, pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Stir well. Cook pineapple and mandarin orange juice with eggs, sugar, salt and flour.
Cook until like gravy.
Pour over macaroni mixture and chill.
Fold in
Cool Whip before serving.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all together in bowl.
Pour into greased baking dish (9 x 12-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until golden brown.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water until tender.
Melt butter in large kettle; add carrots and onion.
Cover and cook until tender.
Remove from heat; add flour.
Stir in milk.
Add 1/2 of the potatoes.
Mash the rest of the potatoes and add with rest of ingredients.
Heat until steaming, but not boiling.

title: nutty orange coffee cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a small bowl; set aside. Place about 3/4 teaspoon cream cheese in center of each biscuit; fold biscuit in half over cheese, pressing edges to seal. Dip biscuits in melted butter and dredge in sugar mixture; place biscuits, curved side down, in a single layer in curves of a lightly greased 23 cup Bundt pan, spacing evenly (do not stack). Place any remaining biscuits around center of tube of pan, filling in spaces, if necessary. Drizzle any remaining butter over biscuits: sprinkle on any remaining sugar mixture. Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes or until done. Immediately invert onto a serving plate. Combine powdered sugar and orange juice, stirring well: drizzle over warm coffee cake. Serve immediately.

title: dinah's carrot cake and cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat together sugar, oil, eggs and carrots.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to first mixture.
Blend until smooth. Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan or 2 (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 300° for 55 minutes, then at 325° for 10 minutes longer.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Combine above ingredients and press with fingers into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until barely colored.
Cool.
Top with filling.

title: bread
directions: In a large bowl place shortening, sugar, salt and boiling water.
Let this cook to lukewarm; then add yeast that has been dissolved in 1/2 cup lukewarm water, eggs and cold water.
Beat with a mixer until all is blended.
Add 2 cups flour and mix well; then add 4 more cups flour and stir until all blended.
Put dough in a large, well greased bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap and place in refrigerator until doubled in size.

title: poppy seed bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 3-quart fluted tube pan or Bundt pan.
In large bowl with an electric mixer, blend flour, sugar, salt and baking powder on low until all ingredients are distributed equally.
Add butter, sour cream and 3 of the eggs and mix on medium until the dry ingredients are moistened.
Beat on high for 2 minutes, then scrape bowl.
Add remaining 3 eggs, one at a time, alternating with the sherry.
Beat well after each addition.
Blend in poppy seed on low speed.
Pour batter into prepared pan and bake 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted into the center of cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then invert cake onto a rack to cool.
When cake has cooled completely, lightly dust top with confectioners sugar.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: borscht(russian soup)
directions: Cover spareribs with water, salt, pepper and 1 whole onion. Boil and simmer 1 hour and a half.
Remove onion.
Chop one small head of cabbage.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 20 minutes more.
Add additional vinegar, salt and pepper if needed.
Finally add as much sour cream as you wish.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, oil and milk.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture.
Add in vanilla, almond and poppy seed.
Pour into 2 greased and well floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Watch carefully the last 15 minutes.
While still hot, mix together orange juice, powdered sugar and butter.
Poke holes in loaves with toothpick and pour glaze over top.
Cool in pans.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and instant pudding, then add Cool Whip and sour cream.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding.

title: cheddar-pasta toss
directions: Cook rotini according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain again.
Cook peas according to package directions; drain well.
Combine pasta, peas and next 5 ingredients in a large bowl; toss gently.

title: baked one-dish chicken dinner
directions: Put all ingredients in a medium to large roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: venison chops mushroom gravy
directions: Wipe chops clean with damp cloth and trim off any strong smelling fat.
Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper.
Use a skillet with tight-fitting cover.
Brown chops slowly, uncovered, on both sides in heated butter.
Add 1/4 cup of water; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup more water and, again, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Next, add the rest of the water and the soup.
Cover and continue cooking very slowly for half an hour or until fork-tender. Add Tabasco or hot sauce.

title: almond pastry
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut 1/2 cup butter into 1 cup flour. Sprinkle water into mixture and mix with fork.
Round into a ball and divide in half.
On ungreased baking sheet, pat each half into a 12 x 3-inch strip.
Strips should be 3-inches apart.
In medium saucepan, heat margarine and water to rolling boil.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in extract and flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball (about 1 minute).
Remove from heat.
Beat eggs and add to mixture until smooth.
Spread mixture evenly over strips, covering completely.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Combine flour, pudding, margarine, egg and milk or juice.
Mix on medium speed of mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into a well-greased deep dish pie plate.
Place sliced peaches on top of mixture evenly.
Mix cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and juice together; pour over peaches.
Mix together 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on top.
Bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: meat loaf
directions: Crumble bread and add milk. Combine meat, egg, onion, celery, parsley and salt. Set aside 1 tablespoon of the seasoning mix. Add remaining mix, bread and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into loaf. Sprinkle with reserved seasoning mix. Place in ungreased shallow baking pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oatmeal thins(5 dozen)
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugar in large mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour and oatmeal.
Refrigerate, covered, until firm.

title: venison salami
directions: Mix
dry ingredients well, then add honey, liquid smoke, tap water,
venison
and beef fat.
Mix all well.
Roll in two loaves. Wrap
in
aluminum
foil.
Bake
at 175° to 200° for 2 hours. Open
foil and bake for 30 more minutes each side.
The last baking is good in smoker.

title: mystery bread
directions: Combine water, corn meal and salt.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Cool until thick.
Add molasses and shortening.
Cool until lukewarm.
Soften yeast in warm water in mixing bowl; add mush and blend well.
Add flour gradually to form stiff dough. Knead until satiny, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease all sides.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Place dough on surface covered with corn meal.
Work down and divide into 2 portions.
Place in greased baking dishes.
Cover and let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: biscochos
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs; mix well. Measure and sift flour twice.
Add baking powder and salt.
Add gradually to shortening mixture, mixing well.
Add cinnamon. Shape into roll about an inch in diameter.
Wrap in wax paper. Chill thoroughly.
Slice; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture while still hot.

title: fruit salad
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add sour cream and sugar. Blend well.
Add fruit and marshmallows.
Refrigerate.

title: a different kind of cabbage
directions: Brown ground meat and drain off excess grease.
In 4-quart boiler, add cut up cabbage and thin sliced onion.
Pour in canned tomatoes (be sure you mash tomatoes and use all juice).

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the peanut butter and jelly in a bowl.
Stir in milk powder and 1 cup bran or corn flakes.
Mix well.
With your hands, roll the mix into small balls.
Roll the balls in the crushed flakes.

title: escalloped oysters
directions: Mix bread crumbs and cracker crumbs.
Add salt, pepper and three tablespoons of butter.
Mix in well and line the bottom of baking dish with 1/3 of the mixture.

title: swiss steak stew
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine in a large electric skillet or Dutch oven until barely tender.
Add Swiss Steaks and G. Washington broth.
Dissolve cornstarch in water and add to vegetable mixture.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Season to taste. Serves 6.

title: cinnamon chocolate cake
directions: Combine water, oleo, shortening, cocoa, cinnamon and vanilla in double boiler.
Bring to a boil then add to dry ingredients. Bake 15 minutes at 350° (on flat cookie sheet).

title: slaw dressing
directions: Mix awhile before using.

title: german goulash
directions: Peel potatoes and
carrots;
parboil 20 minutes.
Brown hamburger with onions and
drain.
In a greased dish alternate the layers
of
potatoes
and	carrots with the hamburger and onions. Before second layer mix 2 tablespoons of ketchup with each
can of	mushroom
soup.
Pour
over hamburger and onion layer, then repeat again until completed.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in oatmeal.

title: pine nut salad
directions: Toast almonds and pine nuts. Cool. Add cole slaw and green onions. Crunch up Ramen noodles and add. Mix oil, vinegar and seasoning together. Pour over mixture. Serve immediately.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 2 cups graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick butter.
Spread in sheet pan.
Mix together 1 (8 ounce) package cream cheese, one square butter and 2 cups powdered sugar.
Spread on graham cracker crumbs, then add in layers 3 to 4 bananas, 1 (20 ounce) can crushed pineapple and 1 package frozen strawberries.
Add one container (large) Cool Whip to top and spread chopped walnuts on top of Cool Whip.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar and water until forms hard ball in cold water.
Add cream, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown, drain and cool sausage.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish with bread.
Mix sausage and cheese and spread over bread. Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over casserole. Refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: squash pickles
directions: Soak squash in ice water with 1/3 salt for 2 hours.
Drain squash well.
Bring other ingredients to a boil.
Put squash in and boil for 3 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
Makes 3 or 4 pints.

title: poppy seed pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients well and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato surprise balls
directions: Peel, slice and boil potatoes until done.
Drain well and mash until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients (except marshmallows) in oil and mix well.
Chill for easier handling.
Mold sweet potatoes around marshmallow halves; shape each into a ball and roll in additional crushed corn flakes.
Refrigerate briefly to set.
Fry in deep fat at 375° for about 3 or 4 minutes or until lightly browned.
Drain well.
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin custard
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a round Pyrex dish.
Place filled dish in a pie plate and fill the pie plate with water until it is 3/4 of the way full.
(This steam makes the custard creamy.)
Place pie plate with filled dish in the oven.
Cook 1 hour or until a toothpick, inserted in the middle, comes out clean.
Be careful removing from the oven. Let cool.
Eat.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into greased 4-quart casserole dish. Cover with 1 cup crushed corn flakes (or Ritz crackers) with 3/4 cup melted oleo.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: seven minute icing
directions: Put sugar, water, unbeaten egg whites and salt in upper part of double boiler.
Beat constantly over hot water for seven minutes or until frosting is almost thick enough to spread.
Add flavoring.
Remove from hot water and continue beating until frosting is of the consistency to spread.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies by aunt lynn
directions: In a large bowl, combine margarine, sugars, vanilla and eggs. Beat until creamy.
Set aside.
Mix flour and oats together. Slowly add to egg mixture, beating well.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Put dough in an airtight container and refrigerate.
Make as many or as few cookies at a time as you like.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: macaroon candy
directions: In a large bowl, mix the powdered sugar, coconut and nuts. In double boiler, heat butter and sweetened condensed milk.
Pour over mixture in bowl; mix and stir well.
Press into a cookie sheet; let sit in a refrigerator for 24 hours.
Cut into squares. Melt wax and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Dip into chocolate.

title: mystery canapes
directions: Blend together first 5 ingredients. Spread on bread slices. Broil 3 minutes or until bubbly.

title: pina colada wedges(creative ideas)
directions: Beat the cream cheese with sugar.
Add rum until smooth.
Fold in 2 cups of the whipped topping, pineapple with syrup and 2 cups of the coconut.
Spread in an 8-inch layer pan lined with plastic wrap.
Invert pan onto serving plate.
Remove pan and plastic wrap.
Spread with remaining coconut.
Freeze until firm, about 2 hours.
Cut into wedges.
Garnish with pineapple and cherries, if desired.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop the corn.
Cook molasses, sugar and butter to a soft ball stage on candy thermometer.
Add baking powder and vanilla.
Pour over corn and form into balls.

title: baked chicken nuggets
directions: Mix first ingredients.
Dip chicken in melted butter, coat with ingredients.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Serve with barbecue or honey mustard, etc.

title: split pea supreme
directions: Cook all ingredients except pork chops in a large container of water for 3 hours.
Take the pork chops and chop and cook for 1 1/2 hours on slow heat.
Add salt to taste.
Makes a delicious soup.

title: mystery cake
directions: What gives this cake its pretty color and rich flavor?

title: rhubarb squares
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add egg; beat.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt; add with sour cream.
Mix well together and blend in rhubarb.
Turn into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chuckwagon beans
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight; drain.
Place in a large kettle or Dutch oven and cover with water.
Add remaining ingredients, except for salt.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add salt to taste and more water if needed.
Cook another hour or until beans are tender.

title: grilled ham sandwich
directions: Combine cream cheese, mustard and horseradish, mixing until well blended.
For each sandwich, cover one bread slice with cream cheese mixture, process cheese spread, ham and second bread slice. Spread sandwich with margarine.
Grill until lightly browned on both sides.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put bread in 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.
Beat eggs in a bowl.
Add milk, sugar, salt, vanilla and butter; stir.
Pour over bread and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: applesauce oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oats, flour, cinnamon, baking powder, soda and brown sugar.
Make a well within the dry ingredients.
Add applesauce, egg, oil and milk; stir until just moistened.
Spoon batter into muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: cheesy broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, drain well, and cool.
Combine mayonnaise, soup, egg, and grated cheese; stir in cooked broccoli.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish, and sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 325 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: herb and garlic bites
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Separate each biscuit in half.
Gently stretch dough to form 3-inch circles.
Stir together cream cheese and pepperoni in small bowl until well blended.
Spoon 1 1/2 teaspoons of cream cheese mixture onto center of each circle. Fold in half; press edges together to seal.
Place on cookie sheet.
Brush with egg.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Preparation time: 10 minutes.
Cooking time: 10 minutes.
Makes 40 appetizers.

title: ants on a log(a healthy snack)
directions: Clean celery and remove leaves.
Cut in approximately 4-inch slices.
Spread peanut butter along indented side of celery. Arrange raisins along the peanut butter to resemble ants.
Enjoy.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: In large bowl combine all ingredients except for cranberries and nuts.
Stir until blended.
Stir in berries and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pan (1 large loaf or 2 to 3 mini loaves). Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon drops onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, or until lightly browned around edges.
Makes a bunch.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and let set until firm. Combine next 5 ingredients and cook on low, stirring all the time, until thick.
Remove from heat and let cool completely.
Add 1 small container Cool Whip to cooled mixture and spread on jello.

title: nutty chocolate bars
directions: Place margarine in 9-inch square baking dish.
Microwave on High 45 seconds to 1 minute, or until margarine melts.
Stir in graham crackers, press into bottom of dish.
Pour milk over crust. Sprinkle with morsels and coconut.
Top with nuts.
Lightly press mixture down and microwave on level 7 for 8 to 9 minutes, rotating dish every 2 minutes, 1/4 turn each time.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: walking tostado dip
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, taco mix, and set aside. Chop onions, chop tomatoes and olives. Layer bean dip, avocado dip, taco mix, green onions, tomatoes,
olives, shredded cheese.

title: meat patties
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into round balls or patties.
Cover thoroughly with bread crumbs.
Fry in pan with 1 inch of oil. Drain on paper towels.

title: chicken cheese souffle
directions: In large flat casserole dish (9 x 13-inch), place bread, sliced chicken breasts, then sliced cheese.
Cut to fit pan.
Beat eggs and milk until blended.
Pour over bread, chicken and cheese in casserole dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour until eggs are set and nicely browned.

title: liverwurst spread
directions: Mix liverwurst with cream cheese.
Add mayo and chopped onion. Serve with crackers or party bread.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: Brown ground round with onions and bell pepper.
Drain and rinse with hot water.
Add remaining ingredients and cook.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Bring to a boil the first 5 ingredients and cook 5 minutes; set off stove and stir in baking soda.
Pour over popcorn that's been spread on a cookie sheet, bake for 1 hour.
Stir a couple of times while baking.

title: toasted asparagus roll-ups
directions: Blend well.
Spread cheese mixture on each slice of flattened bread.
Roll 1 spear (jelly roll fashion) in each bread slice. Fasten with toothpicks.
Dip rolls in melted butter.
Freeze.
When frozen firm, slice in thirds.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°, until brown.

title: brownies for a crowd
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Boil macaroni and chill by running cold water over it.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix squash, onions and peppers and let stand in salt water for 1 1/2 hours.
Mix vinegar, sugar, mustard seed, celery seed and turmeric.
Bring to boil and add squash.
Let boil 1 minute.

title: cake in a cup
directions: Make cake mix and fill Comet cups 3/4 full.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: economical cream cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, beating well. Then add flavoring.
Add milk, alternating with flour.
Beat well. Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake in moderate oven.
This makes a two layer cake.
Use your favorite icing.

title: strawberry pop cake
directions: Bake the cake; let it cool.
Stir the 1 cup of pop and the jello mix together.
Fix the pudding mix as directed.
Poke holes in the cake and then slowly pour the jello and pop mix on the cake, then put the pudding on top.
And then top it with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to eat at least 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut patties
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients to soft boil stage.
Remove from heat and add food color and powdered sugar.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Cool, wrap and enjoy!

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix egg and buttermilk in a shallow dish.
Mix flour, cornmeal and salt in a shallow dish.
Working in batches, dip tomato slices into egg mixture, allowing excess to drip back into dish.
Coat with flour mixture.
Fry in hot bacon drippings at 375° in a large, heavy skillet until browned, turning once with tongs. Transfer to a colander to drain.
Yields 6 servings.

title: lemon melts
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into small balls.
Put several balls in bag with 10x sugar.
Shake until coated.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 14 minutes.
Cool and serve.
Will melt in your mouth.

title: yum yum cookies
directions: Cream shortening and cream cheese; add flour.
Chill.
Roll out into thin rounds (I don't wait to chill it).
Place small quantity of filling on half and cover with other piece, wetting edges of bottom one with milk.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla. Mix well.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, cinnamon, soda and salt. Add to mixture and mix well.
Add nuts.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 325° for one hour or until done.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix tea, with cloves; strain.
Add fruit juices and sugar. Serve Hot.

title: ham bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a medium size bowl.
Add well beaten egg, corn oil, dill seed, minced onion and deviled ham. Now add hot roll mix.
Mix and knead well.
Let rise 45 minutes. Form 2 regular loaves or 4 small loaves.
Let rise 45 minutes. Bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: tiger butter
directions: Combine white chocolate and peanut butter in the top of a double boiler.
Bring water to a boil and reduce heat to low.
Cook until chocolate and peanut butter melt, stirring constantly. Spread mixture onto a wax-paper-lined cookie sheet.
Pour semi-sweet chocolate over peanut butter mixture and swirl with a knife.
Chill until firm and cut into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces. Store in refrigerator.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: sesame tofu
directions: Cut tofu into 1/4-inch thick or 3/4-inch cubes.
Mix soy sauce, onion, sesame seed, oil and almonds into small bowl.
In a dish, put sliced tofu and mixed sauce on the top of tofu; make layer. Cook in microwave about 4 to 5 minutes.
If you want to bring it to boil, use stainless pot or pan.
Cook about 3 minutes on medium-high temperature.
Serve with rice.

title: coconut pie
directions: Place egg yolks into 2 three-quart cooking pans. Beat yolks well. Add sugar, flour and salt. Mix again. Add milk, water, vanilla and coconut. Mix again.
Place on heat and cook until mixture becomes thick. Stir constantly to prevent scorching. Pour into pie shells. This recipe makes 2 large pies.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine sugar, water and orange juice in saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Pour over combined fruits in a freezer-safe bowl.
Cover and freeze.
Thaw until slushy before serving.

title: chicken-cabbage stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken breast halves into strips.

Heat oil in frypan. Add chicken strips; stir-fry over moderately high heat, turning pieces constantly, until lightly browned, about 2 or 3 minutes. Add cabbage; stir-fry 2 minutes, until cabbage is tender-crisp. Mix cornstarch and seasonings; add to water and soy sauce, mixing until smooth.
Stir into chicken mixture.
Cook until thickened and pieces are coated, about 1 minute.
Serve over vermicelli, pasta or rice.

title: no cholesterol chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients. Pour into pan.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Mix all other ingredients and pour boiling mixture over them.
Cover and refrigerate.
Will keep up to 2 weeks.

title: ham ring with cherry sauce
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Mix well.
Pat and lightly grease ring mold or loaf pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour for ring mold or 1 1/2 hours for loaf pan.

title: white chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl; blend well. Press onto bottom and 2-inches up sides of a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Combine cream cheese and 1 cup sugar in a large bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until fluffy.
Add sour cream and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in white chocolate.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) in a large bowl at high speed of an electric mixer until foamy.
Add cream of tartar, beating until soft peaks form. Add powdered sugar and continue beating until stiff peaks form. Fold egg whites into cream cheese mixture.
Spoon mixture into crumb crust.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Turn oven off.
Leave cake in oven for 30 minutes.
Open door and leave cake in oven an additional 30 minutes with door partially open.
Cool.
Chill 8 hours.
Remove from pan.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: quick apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place apples in lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry mix and sugar mixture over apples. Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: cauliflower and green bean casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables.
Mix with remaining ingredients and bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: inside-out pizzas
directions: Spread out 5 tortillas on a large sheet of wax paper. Sprinkle with a small handful of both kinds of cheese (1/4 cup total).
Cover with 2 slices of turkey.
Top with tomato slices and cover with 1 tablespoon of sauce.
Sprinkle with another handful of both kinds of cheese and top with tortilla.
Heat a teaspoon of oil in frying pan on low heat.
Gently set a pizza in pan.
Cook 2 minutes or until little brown spots appear on the bottom of tortilla.
Flip with a spatula and cook another 2 minutes.
Remove to a plate.
Repeat until all pizzas are made. Cut in 1/4-inch square and serve.

title: lemon holiday cake
directions: Cream oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add sugar a little at a time.
Add flour a little at a time.
Add baking powder.
Fold lemon flavor and cherries in.
Put in a tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake 4 1/2 hours at 250°.
(Make sure this cake is done.)

title: kraut salad
directions: Heat vinegar and sugar until sugar dissolves, then cool.
Pour syrup over remaining ingredients.
Let stand at least 3 hours or longer.
Better with age.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: Melt 2	tablespoons
butter
in a saucepan.
Add finely chopped carrots and
onion	and
1 teaspoon salt.
Cook slowly for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.	Add 1/2 cup rice and 4 cups chicken bouillon.
Cook
minutes or until carrots and rice are tender.
Strain
the
soup	through
a
fine sieve or process in a blender.
Return
to
the pan and add 2 cups more bouillon.
Bring to a boil and add 1 cup milk and 1 tablespoon butter.

title: cheesy broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli until barely tender. Drain well.
Stir soup and sour cream together.
Add remaining ingredients to soup and sour cream mixture (except bread crumbs). Sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake 30 to 35 minutes in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix in large bowl and add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into 9 x 13 baking dish and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: rice stuffed zucchini
directions: Cook rice using 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cook whole zucchini in boiling salted water for 10 minutes.
Trim ends of zucchini and cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp, leaving a thin shell.
In a skillet, saute ground beef, onion, garlic and remaining zucchini pulp until beef is browned.
Stir in cooked rice, sour cream, vegetable broth and 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Mix well.
Place zucchini in shallow 2-quart casserole and stuff with beef rice mixture. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: lemon squares
directions: Blend flour, margarine, and powdered sugar thoroughly.	Press evenly into an 8 inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Beat remaining ingredients together.
Pour over crust and bake 20 to 25 minutes more.
Do not overbake.
Filling puffs during baking, but flattens when cooled.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pat 2/3 of the mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan. Save rest.
Toss blueberries, sugar and flour.
Add tapioca, lemon juice and salt.
Pour blueberries over crust.
Sprinkle remaining crust mixture on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce temperature to 350° for 40 minutes or until crumbs on top are golden.
Let cool.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.
Recipe can be cut in half and baked in 9-inch pie pan.

title: sinful strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions and bake in 2 (8-inch) pans. Cool.
Mix the sour cream, sugar
and
coconut together. Refrigerate overnight.
Do this the day or night before making your cake.
Remove 1 cup of mix and add to
an
8 ounce carton of Cool
Whip.
Blend well.
Refrigerate.
Split
each
cake layer. Spread sour cream mixture between
each
layer.
Frost top
and sides
with
the
Cool
Whip and sour cream mixture. Refrigerate. (May substitute orange cake mix.)

title: quick cocoa brownie wedges
directions: Line an 8 1/4-inch round microwave-safe cake dish with plastic wrap; set aside.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in refrigerator to chill until ready to use.
May be made a couple of days ahead of time.

title: pastrami dip
directions: Cut pastrami into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Add pastrami.
Chill in a glass bowl.
Just before serving, hollow out round loaf and save.
Cut what you took out into pieces for dipping.
Use hollowed out loaf for bowl.

title: sticky bun ring
directions: Grease a Bundt pan real good.
Mix cinnamon, instant pudding mix, granulated sugar and brown sugar; set aside.
Put chopped walnuts and raisins to cover bottom of Bundt pan.
Lay frozen bread dough balls around Bundt pan in two's.
Add mixture all over frozen bread dough balls.
Cover with aluminum foil; let sit for 8 hours.

title: crab patties
directions: Blend all ingredients and mix in some cracker meal for a dough.
Shape mixture into small patties and roll in cracker meal. Deep fry in hot fat.

title: spicy pumpkin bars with cream cheese icing
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Add pumpkin and vanilla; beat well.
Sift remaining dry ingredients and beat well.
Bake in greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove to cooling rack.
Let cool.

title: linguini salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Do not drain fruit.
Pour all your fruit and condensed milk in a bowl.
Mix it up and freeze in a pan or Pyrex dish.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Beat eggs; add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Cream together.
Add flour.
Add salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Peel and mash avocados; crush clove of garlic.
Peel, seed and chop tomatoes.
Combine all ingredients and cover and chill. Makes 4 cups.

title: pampy's peanut butter fudge(an oldie, but it's still good!)
directions: Mix sugar, milk and salt; cook until it reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; mix well.
Add vanilla; beat.
When thick, pour into greased pan.
Cut and eat!

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Mix shortening and sugar in a large bowl.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour in pans. Bake until wooden pick put in center
comes out clean, about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Loosen sides and remove from pans.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: new ranger cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Dough will be stiff.
Drop by teaspoon, about 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 9 to 11 minutes.
Cool before removing from cookie sheet.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Place chicken in a large flat dish.
Cover with buttermilk and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Combine flour and seasonings, drain chicken.
Toss pieces, one at a time in flour mixture.
Put in hot oil on medium heat.
Cook 20 minutes on each side or until juices run clear.

title: swiss cheese dip
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Sprinkle with bacon and crackers.
Microwave 4 to 6 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift the flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Mix all ingredients together except sugar-cinnamon.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll balls in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; set aside.
Drain fat from pan.
In same pan, cook and stir ground beef, onions and celery until meat is brown and onions are tender.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Stir bouillon and remaining ingredients into meat mixture.

title: cheese-pecan spread
directions: With a fork or beater combine Velveeta cheese and cream cheese, softened with Worcestershire sauce.
Add pecans, garlic salt and Tabasco sauce and mix well.
Form into a roll or ball, wrap and chill several hours or until firm.
Remove from refrigerator about 15 minutes before serving.
Roll or sprinkle lightly with chili powder.
Serve with crackers.

title: lebanese salad(tabbouleh)
directions: *Bulghur may be purchased from Andy's Deli on Park Lane or health food store.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Brown ground meat seasoned with salt and pepper. Place 2 pkg. (2 dozen) corn tortillas in vegetable oil until softened. Fill tortillas with meat, onions, and Cheddar cheese; roll up filled tortillas and place in a baking dish or pan.

title: easy chocolate lover's cheesepie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cavatini
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add sauce to this.
Put in large baking dish.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: lime pie
directions: Add frozen lime concentrate to other ingredients.
Mix together and pour in crusts.
Freeze.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots for 5 minutes.
Add all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Delicious.

title: spaghetti with chicken
directions: About one hour before serving:
Mince Prosciutto.
In small bowl, stir together Prosciutto, Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs, parsley and dried oregano.
Holding knife parallel to work surface and starting from a long side, cut each breast in half, cutting almost but not all the way through.
Spread halves open.
With meat mallet, pound chicken evenly thick.
Sprinkle each breast half with 1 heaping tablespoon Prosciutto mixture; reserve remaining mixture.
Starting from a long side, roll each breast half jelly-roll fashion.
Secure with toothpicks.
Cut core from each tomato.
Place tomatoes in boiling water for 10 seconds. Cool under running cold water.
Peel and dice tomatoes; set aside.

title: heart healthy corn cakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine milk, egg and oil.
Blend all ingredients.
Use 1/3 cup for each cake.
Bake on a hot, nonstick griddle, sprayed with olive oil cooking spray.

title: fried chicken
directions: Season chicken pieces to taste with season salt and garlic salt.
Batter with flour.
Deep fry until chicken floats to the top of the oil.

title: batter for fish
directions: Mix yeast, salt and flour.
Beat egg in hot water.
Pour into batter.
Mix in beer.

title: chicken deluxe
directions: Heat chicken broth. Add chicken pieces and thicken with flour (add enough water to make a paste). Add macaroni and cheese. Pour into a buttered pan and sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter. Add coconut, chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Pour over this 1 can condensed milk.
Sprinkle pecans over top. Do not mix.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes. Cut into squares after cooling.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a buttered casserole. Bake in slow oven (300°) for 1 hour or until set.

title: stuffed grape leaves
directions: Brown onions in olive oil and mix in rice.
Mix in nuts, currants, cinnamon, dash of salt and pepper and dill weed.
Stir in water and sugar.
Cook until rice soaks up all of the water. Cool.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and bake 30 minutes at 400° in casserole dish.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Cook 8 tbsp milk, brown sugar and butter over medium heat until brown.
The more you cook the better it tastes.
Combine milk, flour, egg yolks and pour into sugar mixture.
Cook until thickens. Put vanilla in after it cooks, then pour into 2 baked pie shells.

title: apple bars
directions: Bake in greased and floured sheet cake pan at 375° about 45 minutes.
Let cool.

title: mollye's celery seed dressing
directions: Mix first six ingredients thoroughly in blender.
Slowly add oil.

title: ice tea punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with ice cubes.

title: french apple pie
directions: Fill pie shell with sliced apples, mixed with 1/2 cup sugar. To prepare crumb topping, cream butter and brown sugar, then cut in flour.
Add chopped pecans and cinnamon.
Sprinkle crumbly topping on top of apples.
Bake at 425° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate mints
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler or microwave.
Stir to see that all are melted.
Remove from heat and let cool completely, but not harden.
Beat together:
sugar, butter and eggs until fluffy.
Do not underbeat.
Add vanilla, peppermint and melted chocolate.
Beat well.

title: hello dollies(seven layer cookies)
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle the next 5 ingredients into the pan in the order given.
Pour the condensed milk over the layers and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Yields 16 squares.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients together in order.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: 1974 honey whole wheat bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Heat remaining ingredients in a saucepan at low heat until warm, not hot.
Pour warm liquid over flour and yeast mixture.
Blend for 1 minute at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Stir by hand the additional whole wheat and white flour.

title: sunrise juice
directions: Blend all ingredients, place in freezer until almost completely frozen.
Re-blend and serve.
Serves 6.

title: hot or cold fruit drinks
directions: Mix together and serve hot or cold.
Serves 25.

title: longevity soup
directions: Heat oil in heavy bottom 4-quart pot.
Add garlic and onion; saute until soft and translucent.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon of the salt, carrots, celery, broccoli and spinach.
Add oregano, pepper and basil.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 to 8 minutes.
Add green pepper, water, tomato puree and chickpeas.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes and remaining salt; simmer 10 more minutes, then bring soup to a boil.
Add pasta and gently boil until pasta is tender, about 10 minutes.
Ladle into bowls and top with 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Add sugar and stir well.
Add juice and enough water to equal one gallon.
Freeze to make slush. Shake occasionally to make a slush.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place hash browns in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soups, onions and sour cream.
Spread over hash browns.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Melt margarine and Ritz cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until hash browns are cooked and casserole is bubbly and brown.

title: do ahead casserole
directions: Stir soup with milk; add all ingredients except eggs.
Stir; fold in eggs.
Put in greased casserole.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered.
Uncover and cook 30 minutes longer.
This is really glorified macaroni and cheese and is delicious for a do ahead meal.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: To make toast crumbs, toast 4 slices white bread.
Snip into pieces with scissors.

title: german sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Blend in vanilla. Sift together flour, powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, blending well.
Roll dough about 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured surface.
Cut with floured 2-inch cookie cutter. Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on racks.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Mix mushroom soup and water in dish until thick.
Saute onion and pepper in oil until tender.
Add ground beef; cook until no longer red.
Drain grease.
Add the tomato soup; simmer for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Cook spaghetti for about 12 to 15 minutes; drain.
Layer spaghetti, ground beef mixture, mushroom soup and cheese, ending with cheese on top.

title: beer-batter shrimp
directions: Peel and devein the shrimp.
Put the flour in a mixing bowl; add salt, pepper, nutmeg and coriander.
Gradually add the beer, stirring with a wire whisk until smooth.
Add more beer if necessary (should be consistency of pancake batter).
Brush the top of the batter with 1 tablespoon oil (this prevents gas from escaping).
Cover with plastic wrap and let stand in a warm place for 30 minutes.
Beat the egg whites until they form soft peaks and fold them into the batter with a rubber spatula.
Heat the oil in an electric skillet or deep fryer to 350°.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour and sugar together.
Add sour cream and beer.
Mix well.
Let stand in mixing bowl about 1 hour, covered.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Rub top with butter when done.
Cool on rack.

title: nutty o's
directions: In a large saucepan, heat brown sugar, corn syrup and butter until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in cereal and nuts; mix well. Spread onto greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pans.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Stir to loosen from pan. Cool completely.
Store in airtight container.

title: vegetable plenty
directions: Combine broccoli, corn, crumbs, chopped onion and 1 1/2 cups cheese and mix lightly.
Reserve 1/2 cup cheese for topping.
Layer half of the vegetable mixture and tomato wedges in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with remaining vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining tomato wedges; continue baking for 15 minutes.
Top with reserved cheese and serve.
Serves 6.

title: fluffy cooked vanilla icing
directions: Mix flour and milk in a saucepan and cook until thickened; let cool.
Beat sugar, Crisco and vanilla together, then add cooled flour mixture.
Beat until smooth.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Mix Bisquick and water.
Roll out on floured board, pat sausage on top and roll (as for jelly roll).
Chill for 1 hour. Slice in 1/2-inch slices and bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine gently all ingredients and refrigerate.
Best if you let mixture set for a couple of hours or overnight.

title: ice cream
directions: Fill freezer can with the ingredients and regular milk to fill line (under 1/2 gallon Milk) and freeze.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans; spread over bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Chill.

title: fudgy applesauce bars
directions: Combine applesauce, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Melt chocolate and butter in pan.
Combine flour with other dry ingredients and mix everything together.
Spread in a 9-inch pan and sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle chips over and spread evenly.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Put in 2 (4 1/2 x 9 1/2-inch) bread pans. I put wax paper on bottom and grease bottom and sides with shortening.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken and onions until meat is done.
Debone chicken. Cook broccoli until done.
Cube and boil potatoes until done.
Add all ingredients together in baking pan and top with Velveeta cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted (350°).

title: autumn festival fluff
directions: Combine first four ingredients and mix until crumbly.
Mix together confectioners sugar and 1/3 cup peanut butter and set aside.
Whip together cream cheese and sugar.
Fold into whipped topping and set aside.
Place 2/3 of graham cracker crumb mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 of the cream cheese-whipped topping mixture over crumbs; spread the apple pie filling over all. Sprinkle with cinnamon to taste.
Over this, spread 2/3 of the sugar-peanut butter mixture with remainder of ingredients.
Repeat layer of cheese, whipped topping mixture, then remaining cracker crumb mixture and top with remainder of peanut butter and sugar mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours or overnight.
Cut into squares and serve.
Yields 24 squares.

title: chicken in sour cream
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, paprika, garlic and pepper in a large deep bowl with a lid. Add chicken breasts and coat well.
Allow to marinate in the sour cream mixture overnight in the refrigerator, covered.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Mix together margarine, sugar and eggs.
Sift together and stir in flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Chill dough; roll into balls.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon together.
Roll balls in sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until lightly brown, 5 to 7 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: watergate salad
directions: Add pineapple to dry pudding mix.
Add other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill before serving.

title: chicken and ham bundles
directions: In a large saucepan, combine water and bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil; add chicken and sherry. Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Remove from heat.
Let chicken cool in broth 30 minutes.
Remove chicken from broth.
Wrap a cheese and ham slice around each chicken piece and set aside.

title: 5-minute chili mac
directions: Stir together ingredients over medium heat in large saucepan until heated.
Serve.
If desired, top with sour cream, pitted ripe olive slices and chopped peppers.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh fruit punch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pour over ice in bowl.
Core apple. Slice in thin rounds.
Stud apple slices with 3 cloves.
Decorate punch with apple slices and orange and lemon slices.

title: slush
directions: Boil 5 cups water with sugar until it dissolves.
In separate bowl, add 2 cups boiling water with tea bags.
Let both mixtures cool, then combine.
Add orange juice, lemon juice and brandy. Put in freezer overnight.
To serve, use 1/2 slush and 1/2 7-Up in glass.

title: almond cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Cut in butter.
Mix remaining ingredients, except almonds, and stir in.
Shape in 1-inch balls and put on cookie sheets.
Flatten balls to 1/4 inch thickness with a glass covered with wax paper.
Put an almond half in the center of each.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes about 6 1/2 dozen.

title: baked pork tenderloin
directions: On each pork chop, put 1 slice onion, 1 slice lemon, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon ketchup, in that order. Cover. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Place fruit in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cut crust off bread and cut in strips.
Place on top of fruit.
Mix sugar, flour, butter and egg.
Spoon over top of bread strips.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: buns
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together, then put this in your flour. Let set 1 hour, then pan out, then let set 2 hours in pans.
Then bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Place all dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
With a spoon, make a deep well in the center.
In this well, add all the other ingredients.
Stir carefully, just enough to dampen all the dry ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Soak and cook beans.
Drain and mash in mixer (be careful not to liquify them!).
Spoon into skillet and add pinto bean seasoning or garlic and onion flavorings and "fry" until a thick consistency is reached.
These may be used to fill tortillas along with picante sauce and some (slight) cheese.
These may also be used in tacos or chalupas (flat tacos).
These will freeze fine and defrost in the microwave.
Made this way you avoid the lard often used in store bought refried beans.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla with a mixer.
Add in flour, salt and nuts.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on cookie sheet (ungreased).
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until set.
Do not brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot and place on wax paper. When cool, roll again in powdered sugar.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Combine nuts, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat 1 cup sugar with butter until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients and beat at low speed until blended well; at medium speed, beat 3 minutes.
Spread 1/2 of batter in pan; sprinkle with half of nut mixture.
Spread evenly with rest of batter and sprinkle with rest of nut mixture.
Bake in greased 9-inch tube pan 60 to 65 minutes at 350° (until cake pulls away from side of pan).
Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes; loosen inside edge and invert from pan onto rack to cool slightly. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: savory rice
directions: Place one heaping cup of uncooked rice in bottom of a greased casserole dish.
Dot rice with butter.
Pour can of beef consomme soup and can of onion soup over the rice.
Cover casserole dish tightly with foil.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for one hour.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook bacon and crumble.
Saute pepper and onions.
Add the remaining ingredients and simmer (covered) for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water until dissolved.
Add pineapple juice. Refrigerate until slightly set in a large flat container.

title: quick corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine muffin mix, corn, sour cream, oil and egg in a bowl; mix well.
Grease 12 muffin cups with shortening.
Fill each cup 2/3 full with batter.
Bake on the center rack of preheated oven for 20 minutes or until golden. Yields 1 dozen.

title: baked gooseneck squash
directions: Bake gooseneck squash until tender.
Let cool.
Cut in half. Scoop out center.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, cook salad oil, green peppers and carrots until tender, stirring frequently.
In Dutch oven, heat to boiling vegetables, gherkins, tomato sauce, vinegar, sugar and pineapple liquid to the meat balls.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes until meat balls are tender.
Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup water. Gradually stir into mixture until thickened.
Heat.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Press on a 14-inch pizza pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Combine the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread on cooled crust.
Slice strawberries on top.

title: dream cake
directions: Bake cake mix.
Punch holes in cake when done.
Mix Jell-O and pour over cake.
Mix instant pudding and pour over Jell-O.
Chill until Jell-O is set and put Cool Whip on top. Serve. Delicious.

title: jam cake
directions: Beat sugar and oleo until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time. Sift flour and add buttermilk and the rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: speedy buns
directions: Put water, sugar and yeast in a large mixing bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add 2 eggs and Crisco; beat with mixer 1 minute.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and 2 cups flour; beat 2 minutes.
Add 2 more cups flour; beat until smooth.
Add remaining 2 1/2 cups flour.
Stir with a spoon until dough is formed.
Let dough rest 20 minutes. Shape into rolls; let rise.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes approximately 36 rolls.

title: italian potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes, then drain them.
Add 1 cup of sour cream and stir.
Add Italian dressing and Cheddar cheese (reserve some for topping), mixing well.
Top with reserved Cheddar cheese.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter, add light corn syrup, salt, vanilla and eggs. Mix well.
Add pecans.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 300° until brown and set (approximately one hour).

title: susan's lasagna
directions: Brown meat with onion, garlic and Italian seasoning, then add tomato paste, tomatoes, water and soup.
Let simmer at least 1 hour.
While simmering, shred frozen cream cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Cook noodles according to directions on box.
When sauce is done, layer with noodles, sauce and each cheese until gone. Use a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: bertha roberts' dark fruit cake
directions: Mix brown and white sugars with butter and cream thoroughly. Sift the first 6 ingredients together and set aside.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add molasses.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Dredge all fruit with flour.
Bake at 300° until done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Prepare Dream Whip as directions on package with milk. Fold in mixture.
You can put Cool Whip or Dream Whip on top of pie.
Put in 9-inch graham cracker crust.

title: poor man's filet mignon
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon; mix well.
Form into patties.
Wrap outer edge of each patty with a strip of bacon and fasten with a toothpick.
Grill to desired taste.

title: apricot bars
directions: Mix and spread about 2/3 mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with apricot jam (or other flavor).
Sprinkle remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of boiling water just till tender (about 8-10 minutes). Drain, combine with onions and green pepper in large bowl. Stir together remaining ingredients; pour over vegetables. Cover and marinate in refrigerator. Makes 5 cups.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut beef into thin strips.
Combine soy sauce, ginger and garlic.
Add beef and set aside.
Heat oil in skillet or wok.
Add beef and toss over high heat until browned.
Taste beef.
If it is not tender, cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes over low heat.
Turn up heat and add vegetables; toss until vegetables are tender-crisp (10 minutes).
If you prefer the vegetables more cooked, add them to skillet or wok while beef is cooking and allow them to cook about 20 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water, add to pan and stir and cook until sauce is thickened.
Serve over rice or by itself.

title: veggie appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 350° to 375°.

title: max's bread pudding
directions: Melt butter in Pyrex bowl.
Add eggs (well beaten), sugar, cinnamon, milk, bread and vanilla. Sprinkle top with more sugar and cinnamon.
Have oven preheated to 400°.
Put pudding in oven and immediately reduce heat to 350° .
Cook about 45 minutes.

title: orange glazed chicken
directions: Brown chicken in melted butter, remove from pan and set aside. Blend flour, ginger and cinnamon into pan drippings to make smooth paste.
Gradually add orange juice, stirring constantly. Cook and stir until sauce thickens. Return chicken to pan.
Add almonds and raisins, cover and cook over low heat about 45 minutes. Add mandarin orange slices and heat through.
Rice is a natural with this dish.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and form 6 patties.
Fry in small amount of oil until golden brown.

title: mom's pork chops with fried apples
directions: Make a batter of the egg, milk, salt, sage and pepper.
Dip chops into batter and brown in fat, turning once.
Cook slowly and until well cooked.
Place on platter and keep warm.
Draw off some drippings and make a milk gravy, using another pan.

title: chicken-rice pom poms
directions: Saute celery and onions in margarine until yellow.
Do not brown.
Blend in flour, salt and poultry seasoning.
Add milk and chicken seasoning (if not added to rice).
Cook and stir until mixture is smooth and thickened.
Cool.

title: chicken divan
directions: Grease baking dish with butter.
Mix mayonnaise and lemon juice, then layer vegetables, meat, sauce, cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Sift the flour, salt, mustard and pepper; coat the steak in this mixture.
Brown the round steak in shortening; remove to casserole dish.
Add water to frypan; stir in meat sauce.
Pour over steak.
Add onion.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dill chicken and artichokes
directions: Pour salad dressing into 9 x 13 casserole. Add chicken breasts to the casserole. Sprinkle salt, pepper and dill weed over the chicken. Cover and refrigerate for at least one hour (overnight is better). Top chicken with mushrooms and artichokes. In a small bowl, combine sour cream and chicken soup. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Place broccoli and chicken in a casserole dish.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Melt butter; pour over crumbs and toss well.
Spread crumbs and cheese evenly on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: herbed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put chicken in baking dish with onions and tarragon; dot chicken with butter.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add wine or broth.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: potato balls
directions: Mash potatoes really well, then add salt, sugar, ginger, pepper and lemon juice. Mix well. Make small (meatball) size balls. Take flour and 1\2 C. Water mix well (not to thick or thin). Dip potato in mixture coat well.
In a frying pan with oil (so potatoes don't stick). Cook till golden brown, the flour is cooked really good.

title: berks county potato filling
directions: Beat eggs; add to mashed potatoes.
Saute celery, onions and oleo; add to potatoes.
Add bread cubes.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 300°; serve with gravy.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In medium-sized pan, put onion soup mix, 6 large chicken legs and thighs and rice.
Cover pan with foil.
Put in oven.
Cook for 1 hour.
Remove foil and cook an additional hour.
Serves 6.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread rolls on round pizza pan and bake according to package directions; cool.
Mix cream cheese with Miracle Whip and dressing; spread on crust.
Top with veggies and cheese.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Blend the first 5 ingredients together with a mixer.
When well blended, stir in 2 cups chopped rhubarb.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease pan with butter and place bread in pan.
Brown sausage and drain.
Beat eggs and salt.
Pour sausage, blended with eggs, over bread.
Add cream and sprinkle cheese over.
Refrigerate overnight; remove 15 minutes before cooking.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 12; freezes well.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix hamburg, salt, pepper, nutmeg and egg. Shape into balls. Brown them.
Bring beef broth, salt, pepper and nutmeg to a boil. Thicken with flour and cold water.
Add meatballs.

title: hawaiian chicken wings
directions: Cut chicken wings into three sections; discard wing tips.
In a large plastic bag or shallow bowl, combine flour and salt.
Add wings in small batches; toss to coat.
In an electric skillet or deep-fat fryer, heat oil to 350°.
Fry wings, a few at a time, until juices run clear, about 9 minutes.
Drain on paper towels. In a bowl, combine sugar, soy sauce, garlic, onions, and jalapeno. Dip fried wings in sauce; serve immediately.

title: jimmy's favorite monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Mix cinnamon and sugar in a bowl and coat biscuit quarters.
Grease a Bundt pan and layer biscuits in pan.
Melt margarine and remaining sugar until sugar dissolves. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Invert onto a platter.
You must eat this with your hands!

title: corn relish
directions: Mix together sugar, vinegar, celery salt, salad oil, salt and pepper and heat.
Pour hot mixture over the remaining ingredients and chill 8 hours before serving.
Put in clear jar and keep in refrigerator.
Will keep for a long time.

title: potato salad
directions: In large bowl, stir mayo with next 5 ingredients; mix well. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; cover and refrigerate.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix in baking dish and bake at 350° until brown.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or chicken

title: granny's old fashioned hash
directions: Cook meat in pressure cooker until fork tender; or boil until tender.
In a large iron skillet, pour oil and water; bring to a boil.
To this add chopped onions.
When onions become translucent, add meat.
Turn on low heat and simmer until water has evaporated.
Sausage can be added as you prefer.
Use spices to your taste.

title: venison cubed steak
directions: Flour, salt and pepper steaks to taste.
Cook on medium heat, covered about 5 minutes.
Turn steaks over; cook the other side until done.

title: butternut cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Add nuts and butternut flavoring.
Cook as directed on box.
Let cool.

title: sea breeze salad
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in boiling water.
Add lemon and pineapple juices.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Combine cheese and pineapple.
Fold into jello.
Chill until firm.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake cake according to package.
While the cake is still warm, make holes all over with toothpick.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake; cool.
Mix the Cool Whip and pudding together until it looks like icing; spread over cake.
Top with coconut.

title: bubble bread
directions: Melt together last 3 ingredients.
Roll small balls of bread in warm mixture.
Drop in deep pan (Bundt pan).
Let rise 3 or more hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
May add a little more broth or water if needed.
Bake until lightly browned at 350°.

title: perogie casserole
directions: Boil lasagna according to directions.
Layer lasagna, sliced potatoes, shredded Cheddar cheese.
Saute onions (diced small) in margarine.
Pour over mixture or in the layers in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° covered with foil.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Trim fat from the steak and cut in 1/8-inch thick slices (for easier slicing, freeze the steak for about an hour before cutting). Heat the oil in a wok or large pan.
Add ginger (if fresh ginger is used, use a tablespoon instead of a teaspoon) and garlic.
Add steak slices and cook rapidly (1 minute or until the meat is light brown).
Remove the meat with a slotted spoon.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops and drain. Peel and slice potatoes lengthwise. Mix soups and sour cream together. Butter an oblong pan, arrange potatoes in a layer, place a small portion of soup mixture on top of potatoes continue layering potatoes and soup until all is used.
Place pork chops on top of potatoes. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gumdrop fruit cake
directions: Mix all fruits together.
Let stand overnight.
Add condensed milk.
Mix thoroughly with hands.
Line 2 loaf pans with heavy, well-greased brown paper.
Press mixture down.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 300°.
Decorate top with pineapple, cherries and pecans just before taking from oven (optional).

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, nuts, brown sugar and butter. Knead with hands until blended.
Save 1/2 cup crumb mixture.
Put the rest in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: super quick sticky buns
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine brown sugar and corn syrup; blend well.
Spread evenly in bottom of ungreased 8 or 9-inch round pan.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Take dough from can. Separate into 8 coils.
Do not unroll breadsticks.
In shallow dish, combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip one cut side of each coil in mixture.
Arrange sugar side down over pecans.
Sprinkle with any remaining sugar.
Bake for 20 minutes; cool 1 minute.
Invert onto serving plate.
Serve warm.
Serves 8.

title: chicken rice dish
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and put in bottom of baking dish. Arrange cut up chicken in serving pieces on rice mixture.
Over this sprinkle dry onion soup mix.
Cover and bake 2 hours at 200°.

title: deluxe chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar, chocolate and vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Spread this mixture into the baked pie shell (could use graham cracker crumb pie shell), baked is better.
Prepare pudding mix and use only the amount of 1 3/4 cups total.
Add extract (rum, if you wish). Spread this on top of chocolate mixture.
Chill.
Whip the cream until soft and fluffy.
Spread on top of pie.

title: tuna and macaroni toss
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Keep warm.
Melt butter; add onion. Cook until tender.
Stir in flour and cook 1 minute.
Stir in milk, bouillon and salt into mixture.
Cook until smooth.
Stir in tuna and pimentos.
Heat through.

title: oatmeal raisin spice cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Add cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts; mix well.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Brown the onion lightly in the margarine in a small pan over low heat.
Combine the meat, oats, egg, seasonings and cooked onion until thoroughly mixed.
With floured hands, shape the meat into 45 small balls (1-inch in diameter).
Fry them slowly in margarine in a heavy skillet until brown, turning on all sides. As browned, remove.
When all are browned, add the soup and water to the skillet drippings and stir until smooth and bubbly.
Return meat balls; cover tightly.
Simmer over low heat for 20 minutes or until done.
Serve at once or cool, chill and reheat next day or later.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: corn stix
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in medium bowl.
Add egg, milk and oil.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in onions (optional).
Coat pan with Pam.
Heat stick pan in oven at 425° until hot.
Remove pan from oven and spoon in batter 2/3 full.
Return pan to oven and bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly brown.
Yields 1 dozen sticks.
Contains 8 calories each.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bake a 9-inch pie shell and cool.
Line bottom of pie shell with cream cheese.
(Can use a little milk to soften cheese to spread.)
Fill shell with whole strawberries.
Boil sugar, cornstarch and water.
Add strawberry jello; cool and pour over strawberries.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together 1 stick margarine and the graham cracker crumbs. Press firmly into buttered long cake pan.
Beat for no less than 15 minutes the eggs, 2 sticks melted margarine and the powdered sugar.
Spread mixture over the crust.
Cover with sliced bananas and drained pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans and strawberries or cherries.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: stuffed beef tenderloin
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have tenderloin split and flattened at the market.
Lightly brown mushrooms in butter.
Add bread crumbs, celery and enough hot water to moisten.
Season and spread over meat.
Bring second half over; fasten edges together; season. Place bacon strips over top.
Roast uncovered in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: meatball oven stew
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and form into balls.
Sprinkle with flour and brown in hot fat.
Place in 4-quart casserole.
To fat in skillet add tomato juice and cook until thick.
Pour over meatballs.
Arrange vegetables around meatballs, sprinkle with salt.
Cover tightly and bake 1 hour in 350° oven. Serves 4 to 6.

title: hawaiian punch punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid with water; do not add sugar.
Add to lemonade, then add punch and soda.

title: inside out chocolate bundt cake
directions: Combine pudding, cake mix, chips, milk and eggs in a bowl. Mix by hand until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed with finger. Don't overbake.
Cool 15 minutes in pan, then remove.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit together, saving bananas until ready to serve. Chill and serve by itself or over your favorite pound cake.

title: rice, pepper and onion frittata
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a pie plate.
Beat the eggs. Beat in the cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir in the cooked rice, peppers and onions with the egg mixture.
Bake 15 to 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out almost clean.
Pour into pie plate.

title: nut brownies
directions: Cream the Crisco, sugar and eggs. Add flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt and mix well. Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar or with cocoa frosting.

title: pinto bean ragout
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon drippings.
Add onion, carrot, salt, pepper and thyme.
Cook, stirring occasionally, over medium heat until onion is tender, 5 minutes.
Stir in tomato paste and garlic; cook 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients. Crumble bacon and stir into pan; simmer 5 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: pinto bean pie
