directions: Mix well, pour into unbaked pie shell and cook at 300 degrees for about 1 hour.

title: cheese potatoes in foil
directions: Slice potatoes onto large piece of foil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Crumble bacon over potatoes.
Add onion and cheese. Dot with butter.
Wrap loosely and seal well with double foil. Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked 8-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown, then turn down oven to 250° and bake until you feel it's done (filling should be firm).

title: biscuits
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
Put the biscuits in a buttered pan, then put the pan of biscuits in the oven.
Let them cook for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Put butter and jelly on.
Serve and enjoy.

title: crab meat canapes
directions: Split muffins and place on something that fits in freezer. Melt butter and cheese together in saucepan.
Add crab meat, mayonnaise and garlic salt to cheese.
Spread mixture on muffins. Put in freezer for 15 minutes.
Remove and slice into 4 pieces. Return to freezer until firm.
Put in freezer bag and store until needed.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hoot owl pie
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Place layer of hominy in bottom, then a layer of hoot owl.
Continue layering until all hominy and hoot owl are gone.
In a pan heat soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Dot with margarine and paprika.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Using a wire whip or electric beater, mix all ingredients together in a medium size bowl. Do not use a blender to combine ingredients. If using garlic salt, use a little less regular salt. Add a little curry powder or oregano. Makes one quart.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and core apples.
Cut apples into 8 pieces.
Peel biscuits apart and flatten biscuit pieces; wrap around apples, sealing edges.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 3-inch baking dish.
Pour water in dish.
Pour butter over apples.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until golden brown.

title: crock-pot pepper steak
directions: Cut beef into strips; brown in oil in skillet.
Put in crock-pot.
Combine next seven items; pour over beef.
Cook on low for 6 hours.
Add tomatoes and green peppers and cook 1 hour longer.
Combine water and cornstarch to make paste; stir into liquid in slow cooker and cook on high until thickened.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: burger patties
directions: Toss together the potatoes, onion and parsley; mix with 1/4 cup tomato sauce.
Divide beef into 8 thin patties.
Top 4 patties with equal portions of potato mixture.
Place remaining patties over filling; pinch edges together well.
Brown burgers in hot, greased skillet.
Turn, and pour remaining sauce over them. Cover; simmer 10 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Mix in tomato sauce, taco seasoning and beans.
Pour in baking pan and top with chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: thankless peanut butter and jelly sandwich
directions: Spread lots of peanut butter on one side of each piece of bread.
This will keep the jelly from soaking through the bread. Put lots of jelly on top of the peanut butter on one slice of bread.
Jam it together and you are ready to eat.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Parboil zucchini 5 minutes. Scoop out inside, leaving 1-inch shell. Chop zucchini meat and mix with remaining ingredients. Stuff shell. Bake at 350° to 375° approximately 30 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare brownie mix and bake according to package directions in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Prick top of warm brownies at 1-inch intervals using a fork.
Mix coffee and sugar together well. Drizzle brownies with the coffee and sugar.
Let cool and then crumble the brownies.
Prepare pudding mix according to package directions, omitting chilling.
Place 1/3 of crumbled brownies in bottom of a 3-quart trifle dish.
Top with 1/3 of pudding, whipped topping and crushed candy bars.
Repeat layers twice more with remaining ingredients, ending with crushed candy bars.
Chill 8 hours.
Yield:
16 to 18 servings.

title: gourmet meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together (amount of sauce can be increased or decreased, depending on desired flavor) and shape into balls. Bake at 250° for 20 minutes, turning to bake evenly.
Drain and pour warm Yoshida's Zesty barbecue sauce or Yoshida's Sweet N Sour sauce over meatballs.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and milk in large saucepan.
Boil to soft ball stage.
Add butter, vanilla and peanut butter; beat by hand for 5 minutes.
Pour into buttered pans.
Cool about 2 hours before cutting.

title: nacho dip
directions: Fry ground beef and onion and drain.
Mix together the other ingredients with the ground beef and onion.
After cheese has melted, remove from the stove and put in a small crock-pot to keep mixture warm.
Serve with nachos.

title: jesus birthday cake
directions: Heat milk.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat eggs until foamy. Add sugar and beat.
Add salt. Stir in dry ingredients, then hot milk mixture (after cooled).
Bake at 350° for one-half hour. Double for a two layer cake.
Frost with Baker's Icing.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soup, cheese, eggs, mayo and milk together and pour over broccoli. Crumble crackers, and add melted butter.
Put on top of casserole. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 mins.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix pineapple and cherry pie filling in cake pan.
Spread cake mix evenly on top of filling and pineapple.
Cut up margarine on top of the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Take out of oven.
Put chopped pecans on top and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: baby crookneck squash
directions: Steam squash until tender.
Split lengthwise and brush cut surface generously with melted butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place squash halves in shallow baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven just until they sizzle.

title: baked sweet and sour chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In small bowl, combine marmalade, onion soup mix, green pepper, soy sauce, orange juice and Italian dressing. Spray large pan or dish with nonstick cooking spray. Place chicken breasts on pan and pour sauce over the top. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Entire recipe makes 8 servings.

title: laura ingalls wilder's gingerbread
directions: Blend sugar with lard.
Molasses blended with baking soda in boiling water.
(Be sure cup is full of water after foam is fun off into mixture.)
To flour, add spices and salt.
Sift all into cake mixture and mix well.
Add eggs.
The mixture should be quite thin.
Bake in a moderate oven for thirty minutes.

title: slush
directions: Dissolve jello in 7 cups warm water.
Mix in orange juice and lemonade.
Steep 3 tea bags in 1 cup boiling water.
Add to mixture.
Add 2 to 3 cups vodka and freeze overnight. Scoop into cup and add ginger ale or Sprite.

title: lite fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding mix with juice from canned fruit, then add this to the sliced fruit.

title: pork chops with sweet potatoes
directions: Salt and pepper chops.
Brown on both sides in their own fat in a skillet.
Transfer to a casserole dish;
add sliced sweet potatoes and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Pour apricots and juice over all and bake 50 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves four.

title: simnel cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Dredge a little flour over fruit.
Sift rest of flour with salt and add gradually.
Stir in fruit.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Add soup, chestnuts, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 to 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with dressing and additional cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.
A good company dish.

title: turkey salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and refrigerate.
Serve over lettuce or in pita bread.

title: jeanie's salmon ball
directions: Drain salmon, remove bones and flake.
In small bowl of electric mixer
put the cream cheese and blend in lemon juice, onion,
horseradish,
salt, Worcestershire, cayenne and liquid smoke.
When
well
blended,
gently
stir
in
flaked salmon. Shape into
a
ball.
Combine pecans and parsley and spread on sheet of
waxed
paper.
Turn
salmon
ball
into this mixture until well coated.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill.

title: seafood primavera
directions: Combine lemon juice, cornstarch and salt; mix well.
Add scallops and shrimp.

Cover; marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes. In large skillet over high heat, cook and stir mushrooms, carrots, garlic and thyme in margarine until tender-crisp, about 8 minutes. Add seafood mixture; cook and stir 5 to 8 minutes until seafood is opaque.
Add pea pods, onions and sherry if desired; heat through.
Serve over hot cooked pasta.
Refrigerate leftovers. Makes 4 servings.

title: kung pao pork
directions: Combine pork and 2 tablespoons soy sauce; refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining 2 tablespoons soy sauce, lemon juice, sugar, cornstarch, crushed pepper and 1/4 cup water.
Set aside. In wok or large skillet, stir-fry pork and garlic in the olive oil for 3 minutes, or until brown.
Add bell pepper and onion; stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add cornstarch mixture; cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Add nuts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt, margarine and syrup together.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into prepared pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beat in separately.
Mix flour and baking powder.
Add 1 1/2 cups of flour to mixture and then add sour cream.
Add rest of flour and vanilla.
Cook at 300 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients all together, then add butter. Add vanilla and cook until it gets thick.
Pour it in a precooked pie shell.
If you want meringue on top, beat your egg white and put on top (like on top of banana pudding).
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: brown sugar sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream
sugar,
Crisco
and
margarine.	Add eggs 1 at a time. Add
flour	which
has
been mixed with salt and baking powder. Alternate
with
milk
and	sour cream which has been mixed together.
Add
vanilla and pecans.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: baked chicken breasts supreme
directions: In a large bowl, combine sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, paprika, garlic, salt and pepper to form a cream sauce.
Add chicken, coating well with mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove chicken from cream sauce and roll in bread crumbs.
Arrange in a single layer in a large shallow pan.
Spoon 1/2 cup butter over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Spoon the rest of butter over chicken and bake for 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Combine eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to oil mixture; mix well.
Stir in grated zucchini.

title: salami bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll out thawed loaf.
If you have trouble, sprinkle water on surface and it will stick better.
Lay layers of salami and cheese over dough.
Roll like jelly roll fashion, starting at long end.
Seal ends with water.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Take out and baste with egg white mixture.
Bake for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter; blend in flour and cheeses.
Add milk; cook and stir until mixture boils.
Stir in broccoli. Place in a 1-quart casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: very quick apple butter
directions: Place all ingredients in medium size glass bowl.
Mix. Microwave on ROAST, 8 minutes, stirring twice.
Makes 1 pint. Store in refrigerator.

title: hamburger skillet
directions: Brown rice slowly in hot fat in heavy skillet, stirring frequently.
Add onion, celery and hamburger; brown well.
Pour off excess fat.
Add tomatoes and other ingredients.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender, about 45 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings. Carbohydrate 17 g, protein 11 g, fat 8 g, calories 184.
One serving = 1 meat low-fat exchange, 1 bread starch exchange, 1 fat exchange.

title: broccoli slaw salad
directions: Combine all dry ingredients first: soup, crushed noodles and flavor packets, sugar and sunflower seeds. Then add broccoli slaw and onions; mix well. Add oil and vinegar and stir well. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight. Ready for serving the next day. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: crab quiche
directions: Put ingredients into
a 10-inch pie pan.

title: "give me more"
directions: Place enough chili in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch glass dish to cover bottom. Brown hamburger and onion.
Place portion of meat and onion on tortilla.
Add some salsa and cheese.
Roll the finished tortilla in the chili in the bottom of the dish as you place them side by side. Cover all tortillas with more chili and salsa.
Sprinkle more cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(Cover with foil if cheese is added at beginning of baking period.
You may wait and put extra cheese on after baking period.) Slice through all tortillas once before serving.

title: mandarin oranges on french toast(servings:  3 or 4)
directions: Drain syrup from
Mandarin oranges, reserving 1/4 cup.
In saucepan, combine syrup with apricot preserves, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Heat until bubbly and then add Mandarin orange segments.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Beat soup and mayonnaise until smooth.
Add other ingredients. Place in greased casserole.
Top with 1/2 cup grated cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° until bubbly. Serves 10.

title: spicy buffalo wings
directions: Wash chicken wings, then season with garlic, salt, pepper and lemon-pepper.
Lightly flour chicken wings.
Fry chicken wings until golden brown and almost done.
Put fried chicken in a slow cooker, between high and medium.
Pour barbecue sauce over chicken. Let slow cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove chicken wings from slow cooker.

title: ginger-lime chicken stir-fry
directions: Cook 1 pound broccoli florets in boiling water 3 minutes; drain.
In skillet over high heat, cook chicken in oil 4 minutes. Add cabbage and pepper.
Cover; cook 4 minutes more.
In bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Stir soy sauce mixture and broccoli into chicken.
Cook 1 minute.
Makes 4 servings.

title: german chocolate cheesecake
directions: Spread over top and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: shrimp delight
directions: Dice shrimp and combine with all of the ingredients. Refrigerate.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve with crackers.
Party serving for 50.

title: shoepeg corn
directions: Melt margarine, cream cheese and milk together in a saucepan. Add corn and chilies to cheese mixture; salt and pepper to taste. Pour into a greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: meat loaf
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Press into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: barb's done buttered biscuits
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon into lightly greased "small" muffin tins.
Bake 15-20 minutes at 450°.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, onion soup mix, sausage seasoning, rice and beaten egg whites.
Crush crackers and add to hamburger mixture. Make into meatballs and place them in a large kettle of boiling tomato juice.
Cook for 1 hour until meatballs are done.
Stir to keep from sticking on bottom of pan.
Serves 6.

title: pork chop and onion rice bake
directions: Brown chops in lard or drippings.
Spread rice in bottom of baking dish (13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch).
Reserve 1 tablespoon of seasonings from envelope of onion soup mix and sprinkle remaining seasonings and bits of onion over rice.
Drain mushrooms and pimento.
Add hot water to total 3 cups liquid and pour over rice. Arrange browned chops on top of rice and sprinkle with reserved seasonings.

title: orange-glazed chicken
directions: Combine orange juice, rind, butter, sugar, mustard and allspice.
Place chicken on rack in shallow baking pan.
Top with orange slices.
Pour glaze over and bake at 375° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours, basting frequently.

title: quick shortcake
directions: Break egg in cup and finish filling cup with Pet milk.
Pour into flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Combine all ingredients and bake in greased pan at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix and bake lemon cake according to instructions.
Using a wooden spoon handle, poke holes in cake.
Mix one can of condensed milk with the lemon juice.
Mix with a mixer.
Using half of the mix, add the other can of condensed milk with the carton of Cool Whip.
Pour over cake.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Mix and sift dry ingredients except soda.
Add alternately with sour milk to cream mixture.
Add vanilla last.
Put soda in boiling water and add. Bake in moderate oven.

title: shrimp mac salad
directions: Mix everything together in a large bowl.
Chill.
Serves 24.

title: szechwan beef stir-fry(makes 4 servings in 30 minutes)
directions: Cut beef steak lengthwise into 2 strips; slice across the grain into 1/8-inch thick strips.
Combine soy sauce, 2 teaspoons oil, sugar and cornstarch; stir into strips.
Heat remaining 2 teaspoons oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add garlic, ginger and pepper pods; cook 30 seconds.
Add bell pepper and corn; stir-fry 1 1/2 minutes.
Add pea pods; stir-fry 30 seconds. Remove vegetables.
Stir-fry 1/2 of the beef strips 2 to 3 minutes and remove.
Stir-fry remaining beef.
Return vegetables and beef to skillet; heat through.

title: french toast
directions: Add the salt, sugar and milk to the slightly beaten egg.
Add a dash of cinnamon and mix well.
Dip the pieces of bread into the egg mixture.
Cook the soaked slices of bread on a well-oiled griddle.
Brown on one side; turn and brown on the other side. Serve with your favorite syrup.

title: ready-to-mix lemonade
directions: Combine sugar and juice; stir to dissolve sugar.
Add zest. Store in glass jar in icebox.
This can be stored for several days.
Mix with water to taste.

title: onion soup
directions: Brown onion in margarine; add flour and cook for one minute. Add boiling water to onion mixture and stir.
Add pepper and salt; boil for 10 minutes.
Pour into serving bowls and sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Sprinkle cheese over crumbs before serving.

title: meat loaf with vegetable gravy
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, soup mix and egg until blended.
Press into loaf pan; bake at 350° until done.
Cut into squares; arrange on plate.
Combine onion, carrots and celery.
Cook in oil until tender.
Add gravy, cooking until mixture is thoroughly heated. Serve over meat loaf squares.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican corn
directions: Combine corn, chilies and pimentos in a casserole dish or microwavable dish.
Cut cheese in chunks and place around on the corn mixture.
Cover and cook in microwave for about 5 minutes.

title: sweet pungent chicken wings
directions: Disjoint wings.
Arrange wings in long casserole dish.
Blend remaining ingredients to make marinade.
Pour over wings, cover. Marinade overnight.
The next day, preheat oven to 350°.
Bake uncovered 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender and dark brown.

title: sugarless dried fruit jam
directions: Mix all fruit in a large bowl and pour on the juice.
Let set in a covered bowl for 24 hours.
Pour mixture into blender and process until the consistency of jam.

title: fruit salad
directions: Take the juice from the pineapple and add to the pudding to make a sauce, then add 3 bananas and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Mix together and chill.

title: silver white cake
directions: Beat flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, milk, shortening and vanilla on low speed for 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed 2 minutes.
Add egg whites; beat 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done (test with toothpick).

title: red onion soup
directions: Slice onions.
Melt 3 tablespoons of the butter in a large pan.
Add onions and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally, until golden, 30 to 40 minutes.
Add wine and cook 5 minutes.
Add stock and thyme.
Cook 15 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: freeze-ahead crab appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients (except muffins and paprika); spread on muffin halves.
Freeze on baking sheet.
Cut into 6 to 8 wedges each; store in plastic freezer bags in freezer.
To serve, broil until lightly browned and bubbly; add paprika for decoration.

title: baked parmesan fillets
directions: Dip fillets in egg and milk mixture.
Coat with combined crumbs, cheese and salt.
Place in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, until fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: cornmeal muffins
directions: Mix sugar and cornmeal.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add egg, mixed with shortening and milk.
Mix well.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground chuck. Saute onion in margarine. Layer all ingredients and bake at 375° until Tater Tots are done and brown.

title: pork chops complete
directions: Reserve 4 tablespoons soup.
Combine remaining soup and milk. Add potatoes, salt, pepper and onion.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Dot with cheese.
Add beans.
Place pork chops on mixture. Spread reserved soup over meat.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake 30 minutes more, uncovered.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour and seasonings.
Add milk gradually.
Stir constantly to prevent lumping.
Bring to a boiling point and cook 3 minutes.
Arrange cooked noodles, pimento cheese, tuna fish, mushrooms and eggs in layers in greased casserole.
Pour sauce all over.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Serve hot.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl. Pour into greased tube pan lined with waxed paper. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix cocoa and oil.
Beat in sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients to batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch or 13 x 15-inch pan.

title: sopaipillas
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Gradually add water, stirring with a fork.
The dough will be crumbly.
On a lightly floured surface, knead the dough for 3 minutes or until smooth.
Cover and let rest for 10 minutes.
Roll out into a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Cut into 12 squares.
In a deep-fat fryer, heat 2 inches of oil to 375°.
Fry sopaipillas for 1 to 2 minutes per side.
Drain on paper towels; keep hot in a warm oven.
Serve with honey or dust with confectioners sugar.
Serves 6.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Butter and flour a 10-inch tube pan thoroughly.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix in half the flour, then the whipping cream, then the other half of the flour.
Add vanilla.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Set in cold oven and turn heat to 350°.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes, until a sharp knife inserted in cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool thoroughly.
Wrapped well, this cake keeps several days.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Mix Jell-O, sugar and 1 cup water.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Whip Milnot at high speed and pour in mixture.
Mix at medium speed.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Boil noodles and drain.
Add all ingredients and mix well. Pour in baking dish.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Dot with butter and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: amy tran's vietnamese soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and boil until vegetables are tender. Serve over white rice, if desired.

title: baked squash ring
directions: Wash and dice unpeeled squash.
Cook in small amount of water uncovered until tender.
Mash well or force through a food mill or sieve.
Add other ingredients; blend well.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart well-buttered ring mold.

title: coconut balls (mounds)
directions: Combine milk and coconut.
Rub hands with butter.
Roll mixture into small balls.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Use toothpicks to roll balls in chocolate.
Place on cookie sheet with wax paper. Set in refrigerator for few minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Bake corn bread and let cool. Crumble. Add other ingredients. Mix and let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Dice and boil potatoes until fork-tender (do not overcook). Cut bread into cubes and chop green pepper and onion.
Combine all in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with parsley, salt and pepper to taste.
Melt together Velveeta and butter.
Pour on top, then top with crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seafood a la carr
directions: *If bay scallops are not available, use sea scallops; simply cut in smaller pieces.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together margarine and sugars until light and fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
In another bowl, combine flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add to the margarine mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats.
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 6 to 9 minutes at 375°.
Makes 9 dozen.

title: nutmeg coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend sugar, flour and oleo into crumbs.
Reserve 3/4 cup.
Mix sour cream and baking soda.
Stir eggs, nutmeg and sour cream mixture into remaining crumbs.
Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and reserved crumbs.
Bake for about 40 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Spoon cherry pie filling evenly in the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Spread pineapple over pie filling. Sprinkle dry cake mix over pineapple. Pour melted butter evenly over all. Sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 325° about 1 hour.

title: german style cabbage(serves 6)
directions: You also need 1 large frypan and 1 large spoon or spatula.

title: fried rice
directions: Steam rice in rice cooker.
Let rice cool after it has steamed. In hot pan with 2 tablespoons of oil (canola oil is monosaturated), put in chopped onions and stir.
When onions are transparent, drop in rice and stir until uncrumpled and hot.
Add eggs and stir. (One to two eggs, this gives a yellowish color and protein.)
Add green peas, carrots and green pepper (chopped) if you like vegetables in rice.
Add thinly sliced meat (your preference, chicken, shrimp, pork or beef).
Stir until hot.
Add oyster sauce or soy sauce.
(I like the taste of oyster sauce and this is what I usually use, about 3 tablespoons.)
Stir in.
Add chopped green onions on top of rice for garnish look.
Serves a family of 5 with big appetites.
I hope you like it.
I don't have exact measurements for this recipe, but I have listed the ingredients. You can put as much or as little as you like according to your taste buds.
If you try it and it doesn't come out just right, let me know and I'll be glad to taste it for you.
(Smile!)

title: pork chops, onion and rice
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Spread rice in bottom of dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole).
Reserve 1 teaspoon onion soup.
Sprinkle remaining soup over rice.
Drain mushrooms; reserving liquid. Spread mushrooms and pimento over rice.
Add hot water to reserve mushroom liquid to equal 3 cups liquid and pour over rice.
Top with chops and reserved seasoning.
Cover lightly with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove foil and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: apple torte
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake in a flat pan 35 minutes at 350°.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato (no salt), let cool.
Mash up fine.
Mix potato, vanilla and powdered sugar until thick enough to roll out.
Roll out 1/2 of mixture between 2 sheets of wax paper until 1/4-inch thick. Cover with peanut butter.
Roll up and slice.
Let dry 1 hour.

title: spiced tea
directions: Add 2 teaspoons mix per cup of hot water.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Mix raw sausage with Bisquick.
Add cheese and form into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet in oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: nice and easy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together and pour over melted butter.
Add vanilla to sweetened fruit and pour over top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian pizzelle cookies(recipe makes approximately 30 cookies)
directions: Beat eggs, adding sugar gradually.
Beat until smooth.
Add cooled, melted margarine and anise (or vanilla).
Sift flour and baking powder and add to egg mixture.

title: church cabbage salad
directions: Boil, then simmer 15 minutes.
Pour over cabbage.
Will keep for several weeks in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent roll dough out flat on large cookie sheet, making an edge up sides.
Bake as directed on package; cool.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend milk in cream cheese and mix in remaining ingredients. Serve with your favorite chips.

title: filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions and fill paper lined muffin tins 2/3 full.

title: beef oriental
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients very well, then pour on beef strips.
Mix well; marinate for at least 3 hours.
In hot oil (about 3 tablespoons), saute just enough marinated beef strips to cover pan for 5 minutes.
Transfer to a covered serving dish.
Cook the rest of the meat this way, adding more vegetable oil as needed.

title: potato surprise
directions: Fry first 3 ingredients until almost done.
Add mushrooms and ham.
Cook until done.
Top with black olives and cheese.
Serve when cheese is melted.

title: wild rice and ham casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Put in bottom of well-greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Partially cook the broccoli, using the juice from the mushrooms.
Drain and lay broccoli on top of rice.
Layer ham, mushrooms and Cheddar cheese in dish.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise and mustard.
Pour on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: matrimonial bars(christmas)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add flour and soda.
Mix.
Pour in oats.
Mix well.
Take half of the mixture and press into a well-greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Press hard to make crust.
Spread jam softly not to break oat mixture.
Sprinkle remaining mixture. Gently press together for top crust.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°. Cut into bars.

title: cherry delight
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and cream of tartar. Crush soda crackers very fine.
Fold into egg whites.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all with mixer.
Put in graham cracker shell.
Spread the other 1/2 of the Cool Whip on top of pie.
Refrigerate.

title: barbecue chicken sauce(enough for 10 chickens)
directions: Melt oleo.
Add salad dressing, mustard and vinegar.
Heat slowly.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Keep hot.

title: macaroni and cheese or cheese spaghetti
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water until tender and drain. Blend margarine, flour, salt and pepper over low heat. Stir until thick and bubbly. Add cheese, stirring until cheese is melted, then stir into cooked macaroni. Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with paprika (optional) and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream frosting
directions: Put eggs or yolks plus whole egg, sugar and sour cream in double boiler.
Stir and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add almond extract.
Frost cooled cake.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: teresa's brown rice
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish and cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cheese-pickle-onion sticks
directions: Cut cheese into 20 (3/4-inch) cubes.
Place cheese cube, pickle slice and onion on each toothpick.
Chill.
Serves 20.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Set oven at 450°.
Mix potatoes with the butter or magarine, cinnamon, allspice, salt, sugar and honey.
Beat until foamy.
Add eggs and cream or evaporated milk.
Pour into the lined pie pan. Bake 12 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to moderate, 350°, bake 20 to 30 minutes longer.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Bring potatoes to a boil, drain juice.
Add sugar and margarine, mixing well.
Let cool, then form into egg size balls, roll in coconut.
Bake at 325° to 350° until warm.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in
hot water.
In blender use two cups cold water to
chop
fresh
cranberries.
Add to chopped cranberries the sugar and pecans.
Add Jell-O to cranberry mixture and add marshmallows.
Chill;
stir when starts to jell to mix well.

title: ham spread
directions: Separate ham with fork. Add pimento cheese, mayonnaise and onion. Mix well; spread on crackers or bread.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can of onions.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish (buttered). Bake, covered, 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese and onions and bake, uncovered, for 5 to 10 minutes, until cheese is golden.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Delicious served with dried beans or peas.

title: club cracker delights
directions: Melt the butter and brown sugar in a microproof container. Add the nuts.
Stir.
Place Club crackers on greased cookie sheet. Put the melted butter mixture on the crackers.
Bake at 350° for 4 minutes.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Mix according to directions on package and bake in layers at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Place in large casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients together except for onions and pour onto broccoli.
Top with onions.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all together and add 2 teaspoons or desired amount to each cup of boiling water.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook turkey one day ahead.
Remove skin and bones.
Cube into 1/2-inch pieces.
Cook spaghetti, drain and rinse.
Saute celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Add green pepper and pimento. Salt to taste.
Add pepper.
Simmer a few minutes.
Add spaghetti. Mix lightly.
Add turkey, cheese and soup to spaghetti mixture. Mix. Put 2 1/2 gallons in each of three 12 x 20 x 2 1/2-inch lightly oiled pans.
Mix bread crumbs and butter.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle 3 cups over each pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 96 servings, 32 per pan.

title: chow mein
directions: Spray pan or wok with Pam and then heat hot or heat hot and add peanut oil if used.
Add meat and stir-fry until lightly cooked.
Remove from pan.

title: caramel dumplings
directions: Heat sugar, butter and water.
Boil 10 minutes.
Mix flour and 3 tablespoons butter with pastry blender.
Add nuts, milk and vanilla;
mix.
Drop by tablespoon into boiling caramel sauce. Simmer, covered, 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not uncover while cooking! Makes 10 to 12 dumplings.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Use small, tender dandelion leaves.
Wash well; soak in very cold water for 1 to 2 hours.
Cook hard-boiled eggs (1 per serving).
Drain and toss with favorite dressing.
Serve with sliced hard-boiled eggs.
Add bacon bits.

title: 3-bean casserole
directions: Cut Spam into 8 slices.
Partially cook lima beans, drain and mix with other beans.
Combine other ingredients and mix with beans.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart round casserole.
Arrange Spam slices on top in spoke fashion.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: turkey roll ups
directions: Make stuffing according to directions.
Put 1 slice of meat and cheese and spoon some stuffing on top and roll.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with turkey gravy and bake at 350° about 1/2 to 1 hour or until heated through.

title: easy brownies
directions: Crush graham crackers with a rolling pin.
Blend all ingredients in a bowl.
Put into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan and bake in a moderate oven for about 20 minutes.
When cool, cut into squares.
Easy recipe for children!

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In mixer bowl, cream sugar and cream cheese until light and fluffy. Beat in mashed bananas and eggs. Add Bisquick, pecans and vanilla. Stir well.
Pour into loaf pans, 4 small or 1 large pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: blueberry bars
directions: Mix together crushed graham crackers, melted butter and 1/2 cup white sugar.
Pat into bottom and along sides of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, eggs and 1/2 cup white sugar well and spread over crust.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.
Spread with a can of blueberry pie filling.
Top with whipped cream if desired.

title: hanky panky's
directions: Brown beef and sausage together and drain well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until cheese is melted.
Spread on thick slices of French or rye bread.
Warm in a 350° oven for 10 minutes or use deli bread for small appetizers.
Freezes well.

title: date bars
directions: Combine the eggs with all of the remaining ingredients, except powdered sugar, and mix well.
Bake in a greased or oiled pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch) in a moderate oven at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cut into strips about 2 5/8-inch x 1 1/8-inch and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 18 date bars.

title: frozen yogurt pie
directions: Fold
yogurt into topping well.
Add fruit.
Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm (4 hours).
Remove 30 minutes before serving (for softer texture).
Garnish with fruit and serve.

title: pecan fudge southern style
directions: In a medium saucepan, heat sugar, butter, cocoa, milk, vanilla and salt.
Heat over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Spread into buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Saute hamburger meat until it is pink.
Boil peeled and diced eggplant in a small amount of salted water for about 10 minutes. Drain and add rest of the ingredients.
Put mixture in greased Corning dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned chocolate icing
directions: Stir cocoa and sugar together.
Add milk and stir.
Drop in stick of margarine and stir over medium heat until melted.
Bring to boil and cook 2 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Beat or stir while cooling.
Frost a 2 layer cake which has been split in half to make 4 thin layers.
Icing will be thin.
Enjoy.

title: sugar pie
directions: Place in 9-inch pie shell, after you stir it to creamy consistency.
Dot well with pieces of butter or oleo.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in 350° oven until outer edge is real bubbly.

title: french green bean casserole
directions: Cook all ingredients until thick.
Grate in small box of American cheese.
Grease dish.
Add green beans.
Pour sauce over beans.
Sprinkle a can of onion rings and almonds on top.
Bake 30 minutes in 250° oven.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes its own crust.

title: garlic pretzels
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Mix with a bag of pretzels in a large covered bowl.
Mix every hour until dry (approximately 3 to 5 hours).
Bag after drying.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix butter, shortening, sugar and eggs. Blend in separate bowl the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Mix into butter mixture.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, cream cheese and margarine together.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add flour a little at a time as you add each egg, mixing well.
Pour batter in floured and oiled tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Cake will be golden brown when done.

title: chalupas(one-dish meal)
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Add seasonings and tomatoes. Simmer until meat is done.
Heat 2 packages of flat, crisp tortillas.
Chop the green onions, tomatoes and lettuce.
Also, can be served with guacamole, sour cream and hot sauce.
Each person fixes his/her own.
Serves 8.

title: cheese danish
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Spray tortillas with Pam. Sprinkle each tortilla with a scant 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Turn over and repeat.
Cut each tortilla into 4 wedges. Stand rounded edge of each tortilla wedge in bottom of muffin cup curling sides to fit cup.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients over low heat.
Stir until thickened; pour over sliced fresh strawberries, already prepared in baked pie crust.
Let chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: best ever corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir together.
Bake in a greased 8 x 8-inch casserole dish in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.

title: tomato and lima bean salad
directions: Combine the tomatoes and lima beans.
Mix the yogurt with the mayonnaise.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add to the tomatoes and lima beans and mix thoroughly.
Serves 4.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Mix the night before:
Cream margarine and sugars, add eggs and blend.
Mix dry ingredients together and add alternatively with buttermilk (mix baking soda with buttermilk).
Mix 1-2 minutes. Spread in a greased and floured 9x13 pan.

title: orange fluff
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sherbet while still very hot to melt sherbet and mix well.
Add oranges.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill until firm.

title: taco casserole(microwave)
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet, stirring until crumbly and drain.
Add cheese, soup and sauce, mixing well.
Place corn chips in glass baking dish; pour beef mixture over chips.
Microwave on High until cheese is melted.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Mix all together; put in casserole dish.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and butter or margarine and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased). Dough will be stiff. Beat together confectioners sugar, eggs and cream cheese, and pour over cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool before cutting.

title: crackling corn bread
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Pour into a well-oiled 8-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients (eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla).
Add crushed pineapple and grated zucchini; mix well. Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into 3 medium 4 1/4 x 8 1/2-inch greased bread pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
This freezes well in foil.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle pecans and coconut over bottom of pan. Prepare cake mix as directed on box. Pour batter over nuts and stir in melted margarine and vanilla; beat until smooth. Pour over top of cake batter. Bake in 325° oven 40 to 45 minutes or until cake tests done. Turn cake out upside down. Leave pan over cake a few minutes to allow topping to loosen from pan.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put 1 can of beans in bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the onion and pimento.
Cover with 1/2 of the cheese.
Add 1/2 can of soup on top of cheese.
Repeat with second can of beans and remaining onion, pimento, cheese and soup.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.
Cover with bread crumbs and crumbled bacon. Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: gingerbread
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening.
Add sugar, molasses and well beaten egg.
Mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in waxed paper lined 8-inch square pan at 325° for 35 minutes, or until done.
Serve with whipped cream or Dream Whip.

title: canned vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large container, put over heat and bring to a boil.
Lower heat to medium and continue to boil for 30 minutes.
Stir to prevent sticking.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Beat in sugar.
Add vanilla.
Beat well. Sift dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture.
Add zucchini, nuts and raisins.
Put in greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
Makes 2 loaves.

title: imitation crab dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese with mixer until smooth.
Add sour cream and seasoning; then imitation crabmeat. You can add 1 tbsp. of milk to make the consistency for a dip instead of a spread. Serve with crackers or rye bread.

title: easy strawberry cake
directions: Cut angel food cake in half. Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese, and powdered sugar. Spread on bottom half cake. Spoon 1/2 can of pie filling on top of mixture. Top with other half of cake. Spread remaining mixture on top of cake, letting it dribble down sides. Spoon remaining filling on top.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix with sugar.
Stir in milk to make batter.
Melt butter in baking pan and pour batter over butter but do not stir.
Pour over this the peaches which have been sweetened.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
(Drained, canned peaches may be used instead of fresh peaches.)

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, jello, flour, eggs and water; beat mixture 2 minutes.
Add strawberries and beat mixture 1 minute.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: brandy nut cake
directions: Combine fruit and nuts in a large bowl; set aside. Combine flour, sugar, salt, and baking powder. Add to fruit mixture; mix until well coated. Beat eggs until frothy; add 2 tablespoons brandy. Pour egg mixture over fruit and flour mixture; mix well. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 300° for 1 3/4 hour. Cool in pan. Wrap in brandy soaked cloth; wrap again in foil. Let stand for 2 days. Add remaining brandy to cloth as needed for moisture.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, vanilla and oil; beat until creamy.
Stir in flour mixture, then zucchini, nuts and raisins.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Let cool before turning out of pans.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Let cabbage stand in cold water for 10 minutes, then shake off water and place in shallow 4-quart casserole.
Sprinkle grated carrots over cabbage.
Pour milk over all, then sprinkle with salt.

title: fried zucchini slices
directions: Fry in Crisco and brown on both sides until crisp.
Lay on paper-towel to drain.
Soak slices of zucchini in salt to draw out excess liquid 2 hours before frying.

title: easy pickled beets
directions: Bring to a boil the liquid drained from beets, vinegar, sugar and seasonings.
Pour over beets; stir.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: dumplings for 60
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add eggs.
Pour into cooled broth and stir to make dough.
Roll thin on floured surface.
Cut into thin strips.
Drop into boiling broth or drop by tablespoon into boiling broth.
Stir gently to fully cook. Broth will thicken to make its own gravy.

title: play dough
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook over medium heat until it all clumps together.
Store in airtight container.

title: no bake chocolate peanut nuggets
directions: Microwave chips and peanut butter in large bowl for 2 1/2 minutes. Stir and blend until smooth.
Add cornflakes; mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour before serving.

title: cheese dip
directions: Saute onions in butter. Dice cheese add cheese to onions and melt. Add can of rotel and jal. Stir well.

title: tiger bark
directions: In 2-quart microwave bowl, melt chocolate at medium 50% power 5 to 8 minutes.
Stir in peanut butter.
Spread mixture on wax paper coated cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate chips at Medium, 3 to 5 minutes.
Drizzle over peanut butter mixture and with knife or small spatula, swirl.
Refrigerate until firm, then break into pieces.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat to boiling over high heat. Reduce heat and cook 20 to 30 minutes more.
Stir occasionally. Brush on meat the last 20 to 30 minutes of cooking/grilling. (Serve extra sauce on the side.)

title: bananas and peanuts
directions: Mix sugar and mayonnaise into a syrup.
Peel and cut bananas in half, then roll bananas in mayonnaise syrup, then roll in crushed peanuts.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients until partially blended.
Put butter or margarine on top of dish.
Microwave on High 2 minutes. Stir vigorously until smooth. Blend in chopped nuts.
Pour into waxed paper lined 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Chill 1 hour.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix well.
Bake in muffin tins at 400° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on top.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and mix with pudding.
Fold Cool Whip into pudding.
Add pineapple and marshmallows.
Keep in refrigerator.
Chill before serving.

title: koulourakia(greek cookies)
directions: Whip butter and cream together with sugar. Add baking powder to flour. Add to butter mixture. Mix in eggs and vanilla. Shape into braids/twists. Sprinkle sesame seed. Brush tops with egg yolk beaten with 1 teaspoon of water. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: austrian cream cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups of flour, brown sugar, cinnamon and butter or margarine.
Beat at medium speed about 2 minutes or until crumbly and well blended.
Press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 12 minutes.

title: shrimp dip(a nice appetizer!)
directions: Cream together cheese, mayo and French dressing.
Chop other ingredients and blend in.

title: dill pickles
directions: Peel garlic pieces.
Pack clean jars with clean cucumbers. Add dill seed and peppercorns to each jar.
Cold pack for 10 minutes.
Delicious.

title: easy penuche icing
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar.
Boil over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk.
Stir until it comes to a boil.
Cool to lukewarm.
Gradually add the powdered sugar; beat until spreading consistency.
If icing becomes too stiff, add a little hot water.
Great served over spice cake.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches with 1 cup sugar.
Put butter in a 2-quart casserole and set in 350° oven to melt.
Stir up batter of 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Put peaches on top.
Bake for 1 hour or until crust is golden brown.
Batter comes to top during baking.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in oil.
Arrange in a slow cooker the onion, green pepper and tomatoes.
Sprinkle tapioca over vegetables. Place pork chops over vegetables.
Pour barbecue sauce over meat and vegetables.
Cover and cook on low setting 6 to 8 hours or until meat and vegetables are tender.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over the dates and baking soda and let sit while preparing the rest of the recipe.

title: special macaroni
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring 6 cups of water to a boil.
Stir in macaroni and 1 tablespoon butter.
Boil for 10 minutes on high. Drain macaroni and pour into an 8-inch casserole dish.
Mix together 1 stick butter, soup, sweet milk, salt and pepper in small saucepan.
Heat on low until warm and pour over macaroni. Sprinkle a little cheese on top and bake for 20 minutes.

title: italian zucchini pie(surprise)
directions: In skillet, melt butter. Add zucchini and onion.
Cook until tender (about 10 minutes).
Stir in parsley, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano.
In a large bowl, blend eggs and cheese. Stir in vegetable mixture; set aside.
Separate crescent rolls and place in ungreased 10-inch pie pan.
Spread crust with mustard.
Pour veggie mixture evenly onto crust.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. For firmer pie, turn oven down to 300° and bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: eclair cake
directions: Heat water and butter to a boil.
Stir in flour over heat until ball forms.
Remove from heat; add eggs and beat well until smooth.
Spread in lightly greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes until golden brown; cool.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine; make a batter of next 4 ingredients. Pour batter into baking dish of melted margarine.
Do not stir. Pour 2 cups blackberries into center of batter.
Do not stir.
If blackberries are unsweetened, sprinkle 1 cup of sugar over them. Do not stir.
Bake 45 minutes in oven at 375°.

title: brown betty
directions: Peel apples, slice and cook to consistency of applesauce in 1 tablespoon of water.
Sweeten with sugar (3/4 cup).
Cool.

title: butter balls
directions: Combine flour, vanilla, walnuts and melted butter.
Roll in small balls. Place on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Melt 1 Tbsp. butter in a deep large skillet.
Add onions, saute until golden and tender.
Stir in paprika and wine vinegar. Add 1 more Tbsp. of butter.
Wash chicken pieces, pat them very dry, place them in skillet, saute on both sides just until golden, not browned.
Salt chicken while they are sauteing.
Set chicken pieces aside, add the last Tbsp. of butter.
Blend in 2 Tbsp. flour with wooden spoon.
Add chicken bouillon, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Return all chicken pieces to the pan, spoon a little sauce over them, cover and cook over very low heat 3/4 hour.
Remove chicken pieces when done.
In a small bowl blend together 1 1/2 Tbsp. flour and 3/4 cup sour cream.
Add 3-4 Tbsp hot gravy, mix well.
Pour mixture to skillet, cook stirring until thickened.
Return chicken pieces to the gravy, and heat through.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Add sugar and salt.
Add eggs one at a time and stir well after each addition.
Add vanilla. Sprinkle 1/2 of the flour over batter, then the nuts and then rest of flour.
Stir well.
Bake in Pyrex dish 35 minutes at 350°.
Do not bake longer than 35 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Toss lightly.
Place lightly in an oven proof dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and potato chips.
Bake in very hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes. Serve 5-6.

title: quick brunch casserole
directions: Brown and crumble the sausage.
Press rolls in a 3 x 9-inch pan.
Put in sausage and layer with cheese and the remaining ingredients.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: 6-cup salad
directions: Mix fruit and marshmallows;
stir in sour cream.
Chill and serve.
Good with cookies.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook, peel and slice potatoes.
Cut bacon in small pieces and fry with onion.
Add flour to bacon and onion.
In small bowl mix water, sugar and vinegar.
Add this to bacon; stir, will thicken. Pour bacon mixture over potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: parslied potatoes
directions: Peel a strip of skin from around the middle of each potato; place potatoes in cold water.
Set aside.

title: pasta and broccoli with honey-dijon dressing
directions: Cook shell macaroni according to package directions; drain. Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.
In large bowl, toss cooled shell macaroni with oil.
Add broccoli, carrot and onion; mix well.
Cover and chill, stirring occasionally.
Serve salad on lettuce.
Spoon dressing over top.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: foil burgers
directions: Shape hamburg into 4 patties; salt and pepper.
Place on a piece of greased heavy-duty tinfoil; top each with slice of onion, then layer of potatoes until foil is full and top with 1 tablespoon butter.
Seal packages.
Cook 30 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Great for cooking on a barbecue grill.

title: cheesy chalupas
directions: In a 2-quart glass mixing bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Cook on maximum power, uncovered, for 5 to 6 minutes or until heated through, stirring twice.
In 10-inch skillet, brown tortillas one at a time in a small amount of hot oil until crisp, about 1 minute on each side.
Drain on paper toweling. To serve, place two tortillas on each plate and pour about 1/4 cup hot cheese mixture on each.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and onions.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add eggs, vanilla and oil.
Add bananas and nuts.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
If batter seems too dry, add a little milk.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Pour into bowl and mix; refrigerate.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Mix Stove Top stuffing according to directions on box and set aside.
Slit boneless pork chops to make pockets to hold stuffing; fill pockets with stuffing and layer bottom of glass casserole dish with remainder of stuffing.
Place pork chops on top of stuffing in casserole dish and pour mushroom gravy over all, 1 or 2 cans according to size of dish.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: mom's lemon pie("old-style")
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add salt, egg yolks and lemon juice, then add butter and grated lemon rind.
Last, add hot water and cook until thick.
Make a meringue of egg whites and brown in oven.
This makes 2 pies.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together sugars, peanut butter and margarine.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Shape dough into rolls, 1 1/2 x 6-inches.
Dough can be frozen or kept in the refrigerator for several days.
When ready to bake, slice thin and put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix vegetables carefully.
Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate, covered, at least 2 hours.
Keeps up to three weeks.

title: chinese chicken with spaghetti(low calorie)
directions: Prepare spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain. In a large skillet cook chicken, mushrooms and onions in margarine until chicken is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Meanwhile, stir together water, bouillon and cornstarch.
Add to chicken mixture along with cooked spaghetti and remaining ingredients; mix well. Heat through.
Serve with additional soy sauce if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine all ingredients together in baking dish.
Use grated crackers or bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 50 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef; pour off excess fat. Add soup and other ingredients except for sour cream; heat through. Just before serving, stir in sour cream. Serve over cooked noodles.

title: cole slaw for freezer
directions: Mix salt with cabbage and let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze out liquid.
Add carrot, onion and pepper.

title: "mock" lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In skillet, combine beef, onion, garlic and green pepper and cook until meat is no longer pink.
Drain grease.
In large pan, combine all ingredients, except macaroni, and simmer for 15 to 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain water and add to other ingredients.

title: quick skillet
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Stir in water and next 5 ingredients.
Add macaroni.
Mix well and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally and cook until macaroni is tender.
Makes 5 servings.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in large casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: skillet casserole
directions: Melt drippings or butter in a saucepan or skillet.
Add onions, green pepper, beef and Minute rice.
Cook and stir over high heat until lightly brown.

title: crab rangoons
directions: In a food processor, chop the crab.
In a large bowl, mix the crab, cream cheese and garlic until well mixed.
Place a small dollop of the mixture into the center of the wonton skin.
Fold one tip of the wonton to its opposite tip, making a triangle.
Dab your finger in the water and run around the skin to seal the seams.
Then pinch together the 2 points and fold down the top point of the triangle.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: tropical coconut rice
directions: Bring water and coconut milk to boil. Stir in rice and ginger. Cover. Reduce heat to low and simmer 20 minutes, until liquid is absorbed. Transfer to bowl. Remove ginger. Add pineapple, shredded coconut and cilantro to rice and stir to combine. Heat olive oil in saut pan. Add red bell pepper and onion and saut until softened. Add to rice. Last, add cashews to rice; stir well. Serves 6.

title: me-ma's dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: yellow squash
directions: Steam squash 2 minutes; drain.
Mix cheese, 1/2 cup butter, and 1/2 cup bread crumbs in dish with squash.
Mix 1/2 cup bread crumbs and 1/2 cup butter and put on top of squash.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: simply heavenly strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie crust by directions on package.

title: sausage sauerkraut casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: anise candy
directions: Boil sugar, water and syrup until candy thermometer reaches 300°.
Remove from heat and add 1 tablespoon red coloring.
Then add 1 teaspoon anise flavoring.
Pour and dent as it cools.

title: fat-free chicken waldorf salad
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package.
Mix in mayonnaise.
Mix apple with lemon juice.
Stir into rice mixture with remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, nutmeg and water in a heavy saucepan; stir well.
Peel and slice peaches; add to sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Cool; stir in almond extract.
Pour in baked pastry shell.
Chill and serve.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into 13 x 9 cake pan. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil. Add cornstarch and stir constantly until thickened.
Add green pepper and pineapple; stir several times.
Use as a dip.
Can be refrigerated or frozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: opal's rhubarb jam
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar in glass bowl or crock and let stand overnight.
Next day slow boil mixture for 3 full minutes, stirring often.
Add gelatin.
Bring to boil again.
Pour into hot sterile jars.
Seal.
Let cool.
Freeze.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream softened cheese and peanut butter. Add sugar and blend well. Fold in Cool Whip. Fit into pie shell and chill.

title: california scotch broth
directions: Over medium heat, brown ground lamb in a heavy skillet, breaking into small pieces.
Salt to taste and drain off all fat. Put well drained browned meat into a 4-quart kettle or pot.
Add 2 quarts of water and bring to a boil over medium heat.

title: finger juices gelatin
directions: In a 1-quart square casserole dish, sprinkle gelatin over juice.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Microwave on High for 1 minute; stir.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Remove; stir until completely dissolved.
Chill until firm (approximately 3 hours). Cut into blocks.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together (beat well).
Add Cool Whip; pour in pie shell and top with 1 can of cherry pie filling.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Fry onions and oil until brown.
Add paprika and pepper. Place chicken on onion mixture.
Add salt and small glass of water.
Cover and cook approximately 1 1/2 hours.
When completely cooked, add sour cream.
Serve with dumplings.

title: lemonade cookies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add all remaining ingredients and chill 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onion in salted water until tender.
Drain. Soak bread pieces in milk; add beaten egg, cheese, salt and pepper, then mix with squash.
Pour all into a greased 1-quart casserole. Top with Ritz cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients; put in oven or microwave and cook about 20 minutes.
Sometimes water is needed.

title: kentucky turkey salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding more mayonnaise if desired. Add fresh lemon juice to enhance flavor.
Makes 10 sandwiches.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter. Add eggs, vanilla, and melted chocolate. Blend thoroughly. Sift together flour, soda, and salt. Add dry ingredients and buttermilk. Bake in greased tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Let stand 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: party sandwiches
directions: Heat Velveeta cheese in the microwave until melted.
Add cooked and drained meats.
Stir well.
Serve on cocktail size rye bread.

title: choklit cac
directions: Put water in a pan.
One cup.
Buy carrots, tomatoes, onions, celery, corn, peas and chicken.
Put in water pot.
Add 2 cups water.
Put on stove and turn on oven.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Stir soup.
Add salt and pepper, about 6 ounces.
Check to see if soup is warm.
If not warm, cook for 1 more hour. Take off stove. Turn off stove.
Then eat it with grilled cheese sandwich for lunch.

title: hugs and kiss pretzels
directions: Preheat oven at warm (150° to 225°). Put wax paper on a cookie sheet. Arrange pretzels so they do not overlap. Unwrap Hugs and place in the center of the pretzel. Put in oven 2 to 5 minutes or until soft. Be very careful, the Hugs will burn. Take out and carefully push 1 M&M in the middle; the Hugs will cover the pretzel. Let cool for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli - ham casserole
directions: In large bowl, blend cheese, soup and milk.
Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add onion, broccoli (cooked), ham and uncooked rice and Worcestershire sauce to soup mixture.
Turn into 3-quart casserole.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 400° (covered) until bubbly.

title: chicken a la johanna
directions: On bottom of greased 9 x 12-inch pan place 1 cup uncooked rice.
Shake onion soup package and pour 1/2 over rice.
Lay chicken over rice.
Sprinkle other 1/2 of onion soup mix over chicken.
Mix mushroom soup with water and soy sauce and pour over chicken.
Bake at 320° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dilly beans
directions: Pack beans, lengthwise, into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
To each pint, add 1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper, 1 clove garlic and 1 head dill.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to boil. Pour boiling hot ingredients over beans, leaving 1/4 inch head space.
Remove air bubbles.
Adjust caps.
Process pints and quarts 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yields about 4 pints.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Put in 2-quart casserole with chicken, celery, green pepper and almonds.
Heat soup, milk and salt, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and stir until melted. Pour cheese sauce over noodle mixture; mix thoroughly.
Top with buttered bread crumbs (1/3 stick butter and 1/2 cup crumbs).
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1/2 hour if baked immediately.
If kept in refrigerator for a time, bake 1 hour.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Set ice cream out to soften.
Mix jello with 1 cup hot water and set in refrigerator until it starts to congeal.
Break angel food cake into 2 inch chunks.
Pour partly congealed jello over cake.
Add strawberries.
Fold in softened ice cream.
Pour into large pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Freeze and serve.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly. Sift together flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt; stir into other mixture.
Form dough into balls about the size of walnuts.
Roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: granny's candy
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, butter, sugar, coconut, pecans and peanut butter in large mixing bowl.
Roll into 1-inch balls.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Blend sugar, eggs and salt well.
Beat in whipping cream and milk.
Beat well.
Pour into cold freezer.
Fill freezer to 1 inch from top.
Add additional milk if needed.
Pack salt and ice around.

title: quick chili con carne
directions: Heat oil and brown onions.
Stir in ground beef and brown.
Add kidney beans, tomatoes and spices.
Cover and simmer over low heat about 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar, water and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and pour on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake 12 or 15 minutes at 375°.
Turn out on dish towel.
Spread with jelly, then roll and wrap in dish towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix strawberry jello according to package directions.
Add frozen berries and let set until they thaw in jello; add chopped pecans and chopped bananas.
Divide mixture in half.
Place first half in refrigerator and let congeal.
Cover first layer with sour cream.
Slowly pour remaining mixture on sour cream.
Congeal. Top with Cool Whip and garnish with fresh strawberries and pecans.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic; drain.
Add picante sauce, spinach, tomato sauce, tomatoes, pepper, lime juice and salt. Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Arrange 6 tortillas on bottoms and sides of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, lightly greased, overlapping as necessary.
Top with half the meat mixture.
Arrange the remaining tortillas on top.
Spread sour cream evenly on top and top with remaining meat mixture.
Bake for about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Yield:
8 servings.
Garnish with lettuce if desired and olives.
Serve with additional picante sauce.

title: broccoli and cheese
directions: Cook broccoli.
Put on bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover broccoli with 8 slices of cheese, then put the crushed crackers on top of cheese.
Pour the melted oleo over the crackers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, oil, vanilla and eggs.
Add flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix in the rest of ingredients.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes.
Makes large amount.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix shortening, egg, sugar and molasses until light.
Add rest of ingredients.
Roll in balls, dip in sugar and sprinkle with a little water.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Melt margarine in large iron skillet at 400°.
Mix all other ingredients in bowl.
Add melted margarine, leaving 2 tablespoons in pan.
Stir all together and pour into pan.
Bake approximately 40 minutes.

title: pineapple-apricot souffle
directions: Combine gelatin and water. Let stand for 5 minutes. Beat egg yolks slightly in top of double boiler. Stir in lemon peel and juice. Add sugar and salt. Cook over boiling water, stirring until the mixture is thickened. Remove from heat and add gelatin, stirring until dissolved. Add pineapple and apricots. Set aside to cool until slightly thick (about 30 minutes). Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Fold egg whites and whipped cream into cooled fruit mixture. Pour into lightly oiled ring mold. Chill overnight. Unmold on serving plate and fill center with pineapple chunks and apricot halves. Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy cherry cobbler
directions: Spray a casserole dish with Pam. Spoon in and spread around the cherry pie filling. Use 1 or 2 cans, depending on the size of the dish. Sprinkle the dry cake mix on top of the fruit, spreading evenly. Drizzle the melted margarine over the cake mix. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or longer, if necessary. Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: impossible bacon quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie pan. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pie pan.
Beat biscuit mix, milk, eggs, salt and pepper in blender for 1 minute.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake at 400° until top is brown (about 35 minutes).
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: pumpkin date bread
directions: Combine the flour, sugar, soda, salt, baking powder, cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Beat in the eggs, oil and pumpkin. Fold in the dates. Bake in loaf pan for 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: pigeon pie
directions: Line 6 to 8-quart baking dish with pastry.
Season hens with salt and pepper.
Put 1 tablespoon butter in each cavity and fit into dish.
Surround with pieces of steak and a combination of two of the artichokes, bamboo shoots, mushrooms or chestnut pieces. Sprinkle with egg yolks.
Add water or broth.
Seal top with pastry.
Cut slits in pastry.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrots vichy
directions: Pare carrots; slice paper-thin, horizontally.
Place in medium saucepan with 1/4 cup water, butter and salt.
Cook over low heat, tightly covered, 20 minutes or until carrots are tender and all liquid evaporated.
Serves 3.

title: cheese dip
directions: With ingredients at room temperature, mix until fluffy.
Put in deep round bowl.
Chill in freezer 3 hours.
Set bowl in hot water and invert on dish.
Put pecans on top if desired.
Keep refrigerated.

title: dump bars
directions: In a double boiler stir over boiling water, butter, brown sugar, vanilla, eggs and salt to keep eggs from cooking in lumps. As soon as butter melts, remove from hot water.
Stir in flour, baking soda, 1 cup of mixed bits and nuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
When cool cut in bars.
Serves 12.
Keep chilled.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar for approximately 2 minutes.
Add the eggs, one at a time.
Add the lemon extract and flour, mixing well.
Gently fold in the 7-Up soda.
Pour into a cake pan.
Cook at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: mother's parker house rolls
directions: Heat the milk and shortening together.
Mix the sugar and yeast cakes together until liquid.
Add salt and egg.
Add lukewarm milk mixture.
Add flour until right consistency.
Let raise 15 to 30 minutes on a warm place, until double in bulk. (Grandma used to put it on the radiator.)
Roll out about one inch thick.
Cover with melted butter; cut with a glass.
Fold cut roll.
Place in pan side by side.
Let raise in warm place again for 1/2 hour.
Bake in hot oven about 20 minutes or until well done.

title: new york cake
directions: Bake white cake mix as directed in larger than a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.
Mix 1 large and 1 small instant vanilla pudding. Beat in the cream cheese.
Spread over cooled cake.
Drain pineapple and spread over pudding.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: thai fruited rice
directions: Stir-fry in 2 tablespoons of oil.
Toss in wok while cooking. Can keep warm in low oven.
Good served with chicken, pork or fish.

title: mint-glazed carrots and peas
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water, enough to cover, for 5 minutes. Drain and set aside.

Combine butter, sugar and mint sauce in medium saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, 1 minute or until sugar dissolves. Gently stir in carrots and peas. Cook over low heat. Cook, uncovered, for 6 minutes or until carrots are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into a serving bowl. Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.
Yields approximately 6 servings.

title: winter stawberries
directions: Cream together the cheese and jello powder. Chill for 1 hour. Mold mixture into strawberry shapes with your hands, roll in sugar sprinkles. Use frosting to make leaf shapes at the appropriate end of the strawberry. Keep refrigerated until use.

title: old fashion custard
directions: Break 1 whole egg into mixing bowl.
Separate 2 eggs; put whites aside for meringue.
Beat whole egg and yolks with sugar until light, then add flour.
Mix until smooth.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° until custard is set.
Spread with meringue and continue baking until meringue is brown.

title: apricot slush
directions: For each drink, put in a wine glass, 3 ounces cranberry juice and 1/2 ounce Cointreau or Triple sec or Grand Marnier.
Add a few ice cubes and fill glass with champagne.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets. Peel and slice.

Cook soup, milk, pimentos and Cheese Whiz until cheese melts. Put half the potatoes into a greased casserole. Salt and pepper them. Cover with half the cheese sauce. Put remainder of potato slices on top of the sauce. Salt and pepper and cover with remainder of cheese sauce. Cook at 350° for 25 minutes with casserole lid on and 20 minutes without lid.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fresh tomato bake
directions: Heat
tablespoons
butter;
add onion and brown. Set aside. In
tablespoons butter, lightly brown bread crumbs; set aside. Mix tomatoes, salt, pepper, sugar and basil.

title: joan coleman's three bean salad
directions: Rinse beans and drain (do kidney beans separately and drain). Mix and add onion, celery and green pepper.
Heat vinegar and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Add oil, salt and pepper. Mix thoroughly.
Pour over bean mixture.
Mix gently.
Store in refrigerator at least overnight before serving.

title: pistachio delight
directions: Mix flour, nuts and melted margarine in pan.
Press to bottom of pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 4 ounces Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Beat pudding and milk.
Spread on top of cream cheese layer.
Beat remaining Cool Whip and spread on pudding.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: apple upside-down cake
directions: Put 1/4 cup butter and brown sugar in a shallow baking dish in oven to melt butter.
Add apples, nuts and raisins.
Cream remaining 1/4 cup butter with white sugar.
Add eggs and blend well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Pour over apples and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Turn out so apples are on top.

title: chicken 'n dumplings
directions: Boil fryer until tender with butter, salt and pepper.
Make stiff dough of water and flour.
Knead until ready to roll.
Roll thin.
Flour and let stand for 10 minutes.
Then roll again.
With chicken at full boil, drop dumplings in and push down with a fork. Do not stir.
Boil 5 minutes.
Cut off heat and let stand until ready to serve.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage over medium heat until done, stirring to crumble well.
Drain on paper towels; set aside.
Spread each slice of bread with butter; cut into cubes.
Place bread cubes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with the sausage and top with the cheese. Combine remaining ingredients; beat well and pour over mixture in pan.
Chill at least 8 hours.
Remove from refrigerator and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: country chicken and dumplings
