directions: Place chicken in a Dutch oven.
Add water, celery and 1 teaspoon salt.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until tender.
Remove chicken from broth and cool. Discard celery.
Bone chicken and cut meat into bite-size pieces. Set aside meat and 3/4 cup broth.
Bring remaining broth to a boil.

title: chicken crescent wreath
directions: Arrange crescent rolls on a 12 inch pizza pan forming a ring with pointed ends facing the outer edge of pan with wide ends overlapping.
Combine remaining ingredients, spoon over wide ends of rolls.
Fold points over filling and tuck under wide ends (filling will be visible).
Move the rolls in a bit from the edge of the pan so filling does not cook over edge of pan.
Bake 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat margarine in saucepan; add onion, green pepper and rice. Cook and stir over high heat until lightly browned.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add 1/2 pound ground beef if desired. Serves 4 to 6.

title: shortcut caramels
directions: Line a 9 x 9-inch or 8 3/4-inch baking pan with foil, extending foil over the edges of the pan; butter foil.

title: fluffy boiled icing
directions: Boil sugar, water, syrup and salt together until it spins a heavy thread or forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water. Beat egg whites stiff and pour syrup over whites.
Beat until cooled.
Add 2 tablespoons xxxx sugar.

title: rich rice
directions: Spoon half of the rice in a buttered, shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Melt the butter in a large skillet with onion, mushrooms, lemon juice and seasonings.
Cook over medium heat until onion is soft.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream.
Spread mixture over rice.
Cover with spinach.
Top with remaining rice.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Dust with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until heated.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meringue drops
directions: Heat oven to 250°. Beat egg whites in medium size bowl until frothy. Add salt and cream of tartar. Beat until soft peaks form. Continue beating, gradually adding granulated sugar until meringue is stiff and glossy. Butter and flour baking sheet. Spoon meringue into pastry bag fitted with large star tip. Pipe out stars 1-inch apart onto prepared baking sheet. Sprinkle with decorating sugar. Bake in 250° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until firm but not browned. Transfer to wire rack to cool.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to package directions. Cool. Beat cream cheese and milk and add pudding. You may slice the cake in half, making two layers. Spread pudding mixture on bottom layer, then lay some of the pineapple slices on top. Add the top layer and frost with the rest of the mixture. Place remaining pineapple slices on top, sprinkle with coconut and put a cherry in the center of each pineapple slice.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms after washing.
Chop stems and onion and put into glass bowl.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Mix in cream cheese.
Freeze bacon night before so you can cut strips into small pieces.
Cook on stove until 3/4 done.
Crumble into first mixture.
Add bread crumbs.
Stuff caps and put into glass pie plate.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Microwave 2 minutes; turn and microwave 2 minutes.
Careful, steam is hot.
Yum yum.

title: ham and cheese pie
directions: Saute onion.
Beginning with cheese, alternate layers of cheese and ham in pie shell.
Beat the 2 eggs with the sour cream; add onion and pour over pie.
Bake for 30 minutes at 425°.
Cool in oven 15 minutes before cutting.

title: halloween beef soup
directions: Cut top from pumpkin and clean out.
Brown beef and onion. Add green pepper and garlic.
Cook 1 minute longer.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spoon into pumpkin.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Do not parboil pumpkin or brush outside with oil.
Cook with top off.

title: chocolate mint cookies
directions: Combine the flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Over hot water (not boiling), melt 1 cup morsels.
Stir until smooth. In bowl, beat butter and sugar until smooth.
Add melted morsels and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in remaining mint morsels.
Bake at 350° after shaping dough into 1 inch balls and rolling in powdered sugar.
Bake on ungreased sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute
onion and butter.
Add the broccoli, rice, soup, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Bake in a greased casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ritz surprise
directions: Spread peanut butter on one cracker.
Cover with another cracker. Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Allow to get very thin. Using tongs, place crackers into chocolate.
Cover both top and bottom; roll to cover sides.
Place on cookie sheet covered with wax paper.
Continue until all chocolate is used. Place tray in freezer for 15 minutes to set.
Store in cool place.

title: cheesy biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and shredded cheese until a soft dough forms.
Drop 10 to 12 biscuit dough onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 450° until golden brown.
Mix melted butter and garlic powder and brush over biscuits when taken out of oven.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and salt; set aside.
Bring to a boil margarine, water and cocoa.
Add to dry ingredients; mix well.
Mix together 2 eggs, vanilla, buttermilk, vinegar and soda. Add to other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let set in refrigerator 24 hours before serving.
The longer the better.

title: curried shrimp(quick and tasty)
directions: Mix soup, undrained mushrooms and seasonings.
Add shrimp and refrigerate.
To serve, heat in top of double boiler until piping hot.
Add nuts.

title: wacky chocolate cake
directions: In an 8 x 8 x 2-inch cake pan, sift together flour, sugar and cocoa.
Make 3 holes.
In one hole, put soda and salt.
In second hole, put vanilla and vinegar.
In third hole, put oil.
Pour water over all and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost with desired frosting.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until done.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish with chicken.
Slice eggs over chicken and add peas and carrots.
Mix soup with broth and bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Add onion if desired. Mix flour, oleo and buttermilk. Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes and then bake at 450° for 20 minutes. (Suitable for freezing.)

title: applesauce cake with caramel frosting
directions: In
a
large mixing bowl, combine oil and sugar.
Beat. Stir in hot applesauce.	Add sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in raisins and
nuts.	Use
2	well-greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pans. Bake	in
a 400° oven for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 375° for 15 minutes. If using a tube pan, bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage goulash
directions: In a large kettle, brown sausage, ground beef and onions. Drain off all the fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except cabbage; mix well.
Stir in cabbage; simmer for 30 minutes, or until cabbage is tender.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with cut-up vegetables.

title: soft and chewy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, soda and salt; mix well with a wire whisk and set aside.
In a large bowl, blend sugars, using an electric mixer set at medium speed. Add butter; mix to form a grainy paste, scraping the sides of the bowl.
Add eggs, peanut butter and vanilla; mix at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add the flour mixture; mix at low speed until just mixed.
Do not overmix.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet, 1 1/2 inches apart.
With a wet fork, gently press a crisscross pattern on top of cookies.
Bake for 18 to 22 minutes, until cookies are slightly browned along edges.
Transfer cookies immediately to cool surface with a spatula.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: sinful salad
directions: Combine jello and boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Cool. Add bananas, pecans, strawberries and pineapple to jello and stir to combine.
Divide in half.
Pour 1/2 mixture into a 12 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until solid, about 1 hour.
Keep remaining jello at room temperature.
Spread sour cream evenly over partially set jello in pan.
Pour on remaining gelatin.
Cover and refrigerate until set, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: ham and chicken special
directions: Place rice in 4-quart casserole dish.
Cover with sliced ham, then layer on the sliced chicken.
Mix together soup and sour cream.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over casserole.
Then cover with Swiss cheese slices.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked caramel popcorn
directions: Melt butter, sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Add baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and divide into two baking pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Add nuts (Macadamia nuts, almond slivers, etc.). Enjoy!

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and pimentos.
Add mushroom soup. Add cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Add mayonnaise.
Pour over cooked macaroni and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with more cheese, if desired.

title: peaches and cream cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle over top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve slightly warm.
May reheat.

title: katie's cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, salt together in small bowl, set aside. Using electric mixer on medium speed, cream butter, peanut butter, both sugars, and vanilla until light and fluffy. (about 1 1\2 min.) Stop mixer twice to scrap bowl with rubber spatula. Add egg and beat on medium speed until well blended, (about 1 min.) Scrape the bowl. Add dry ingredients to peanut butter mixture on low speed until well blended, (about 15 sec.) Scrape bowl and mix several seconds more. Place dough in a small covered bowl and refrigerate for hours or overnight. Fifteen min. before baking Preheat oven 350°. Line several cookie sheets with parchment paper of grease lightly with butter or oil.
Measure out heaping tablespoons full of dough. Roll into balls. Place on cookie sheets 2 inches apart. Bake for 15 min., until dark gold around edges and slightly puffy.
Allow cookies to cool on the cookie sheets.

title: oven pancakes
directions: Melt butter in iron skillet.
Mix eggs, flour, cinnamon and milk.
Pour over butter in skillet.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and serve with syrup.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Take skin and bones from chicken; cut meat into 1-inch pieces. Mix chicken with rest of ingredients, except cheese and onion rings, and turn into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or casserole.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle onions over all and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 12.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Place cabbage and onion in dish.
Pour 1/4 cup melted margarine over cabbage and onion.
Combine egg, soup and mayonnaise.
Pour over the top.
Combine cracker crumbs, rest of margarine and cheese.
Sprinkle mixture on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: gazpacho
directions: Heat juice to boiling, add bouillon and stir until dissolved. Put all other ingredients in blender until like thick soup.
Chill several hours.

title: italian casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 inch pan with cooking spray.
Empty package of pasta into pan (uncooked).
Brown ground round.
Mix together with all other ingredients except parmesan cheese.
Cover and leave in refrigerator 16 - 24 hours.
Bake at 350 degrees for one hour. Uncover, sprinkle with parmesan and bake another 10 minutes. Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: wasp nest cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk together.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cake mix with spoon.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Add morsels and pecans to top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers lengthwise and remove seeds.
Mix beef, rice, onions, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Put into pepper halves; top with cheese.
Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over peppers.
Cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in each tube into 4 or more pieces.
Roll in the sugar and cinnamon.
In a lightly greased deep pan, lay the pieces of biscuit.
Put in the biscuits close together.
Level on top.
Mix the second 3/4 cup sugar, cinnamon and butter and heat these ingredients to a boiling point.
Pour over the biscuits slowly, letting the syrup sink down.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Cool a bit, then turn out on a platter-upside down.
Do not cut or slice.
Serve to guests who wil use their fingers to pull off individual pieces.
Leftovers can be reheated in foil.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa well in a large bowl.
Make a well in the middle. Pour in milk and melted oleo.
Put in microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Mix well. Add vanilla and nuts and mix.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan and put in refrigerator.

title: spicy rice and beans
directions: Spray a large saucepan with vegetable cooking spray. Add onion.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Stir in garlic and green pepper. Cook 2 minutes longer, stirring frequently.
Add stewed tomatoes, broth, cumin and chili powder; bring to a boil. Add rice.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 18 minutes or until rice is almost done. Stir in beans. Cook until heated through.

title: strawberry dream cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries and set aside.
Crumble 1/2 of cake in bottom of sheet pan.
Pour 1/2 of strawberry mixture over cake, then 1/2 of Cool Whip and the rest of the cake crumbs.
Add remaining strawberry mixture.
Top with balance of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serve in squares.

title: confetti chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large mixing bowl at medium speed of mixer until well blended.
Beat in egg.

title: stir-fried beef
directions: Partially freeze the round steak; thinly slice across the grain into bite-size strips.

title: the bible cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat honey and eggs until frothy. Add milk, mixing well.
Add to creamed mixture and beat thoroughly.
Sift flour with butter and add to first mixture. Chop figs; sprinkle with a little flour.
Add to raisins along with spices.
Beat 5 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and place in casserole dish. Mix 1/2 stick melted margarine and 2 cups corn flake crumbs together and place over top of hash browns.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off grease.
Drain whole kernel corn.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a casserole dish.
Cover with cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° until bubbles and melts cheese.

title: jackpot noodle casserole
directions: Brown ground beef. Boil noodles.
Cook to directions on package.
In a large casserole dish, layer cooked noodles.
Top with portion of ground beef.
Spoon portion of tomato soup over beef, then a layer of corn.
Spread a layer of Velveeta cheese over corn.
Repeat layered procedure until you wind up with top layer of cheese.
Bake at 350° with casserole dish covered for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve with glass of white wine and fresh French bread.
Enjoy.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: dressing a'la claire
directions: Mix and serve on fresh greens.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, flour and dash of salt.
Gradually add water.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat, until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat, cook and stir 2 more minutes.
Remove from heat.
Separate eggs and set aside whites for meringue.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Stir about 1 cup hot mix into yolks.
Return mix to saucepan and bring to gentle boil.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and lemon peel.
Gradually stir in lemon juice, mixing well.
Pour hot filling into baked pie shell.
Spread meringue over.
Seal and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, until golden.
Cool.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Mix fruits, nuts, spices and baking powder in flour.
Mix soda in applesauce.
Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Stir in flour mixture with applesauce.
Grease angel food pan or loaf pan.
Pour mixture into pans.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
Test for doneness.

title: escarole and beans
directions: Clean escarole thoroughly. Put escarole into boiling salted water, cooking until tender, drain.
In medium saucepan, saute about 4 pieces of garlic in about 1/4 cup cooking oil.
Let cool. Add cannellini beans and escarole.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder,
Cook on medium to low heat for about 20 minutes. Look out for the garlics, they resemble the beans!!
Before serving, hunt them down!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice; wilt or saute onion and celery in oleo (fry). Place broccoli in colander over boiling water; strain.
(May omit this step by letting broccoli thaw.)
Mix all ingredients together and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Put crushed pineapple in a bowl, not drained.
Then sprinkle pudding over and add all the other ingredients.
Be sure to drain the diced pineapple.
You could use drained fruit cocktail here instead.
Mix and chill.

title: scalloped pineapple cake
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add the milk and sugar; mix well.
Add butter and undrained pineapple.
Mix well.
Add bread to coat.
Put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crispy waffles
directions: Combine egg yolks, milk and oil.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and sugar.
Beat well.
Fold in egg whites. Bake in hot waffle iron.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Beat sugar and Crisco until light and creamy.
Add dry ingredients to sugar-Crisco mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each.
Start in cool oven.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: beef and cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly oil a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Saute beef until brown; drain fat.
Add tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, sugar and salt.
Remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream and cream cheese.
Add onion and green pepper.
Spread half of noodles on bottom of baking dish.
Spoon a little of the meat sauce over the noodles.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Top with remaining noodles.
Spoon on remaining meat sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes or until bubbly hot.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill at least 1 hour.

title: knox blox
directions: Mix jello and gelatine before adding water to prevent lumps. Add 4 cups boiling water and stir until jello dissolves.
Pour into a large shallow baking dish.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 100 one-inch squares.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients, and mix as any cake.
Pour in buttered pan, 9x13x2.
Bake 40-45 minutes at 300°.
Take out of oven and spread Marshmallows evenly over cake.
Bake 5-10 minutes more.

title: ham and cheese pockets
directions: Roll each sheet of puff pastry out to a 12-inch square on a lightly floured board or pastry cloth.
Cut into nine 4-inch squares.
Repeat with remaining sheet of pastry.

title: pecan dreams
directions: Melt butter and pour over pecans; let stand while mixing other ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients with the nuts; drop from a spoon onto wax paper and store in refrigerator until thoroughly cold.

title: savory beer bread
directions: In large bowl, combine the flour, sugar and beer.
Stir until all ingredients are moistened and a sticky dough forms.
Cover the bowl with a damp cloth and place it in a warm place for 90 minutes.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into prepared crust.
Chill for 3 hours or until set.
Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salt water following package directions. Drain and add oregano to spaghetti sauce.

title: nola's pink stuff
directions: In a large bowl, pour 3 cups boiling water over Jell-O mix. Stir until Jell-O is dissolved, then add soft ice cream to Jell-O until all ice cream dissolves.
Pinch angel log cake into small pieces and add to the Jell-O and ice cream mixture and stir. Refrigerate to set.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Make a well in your bowl with flour and mix with pastry or dough tool.
Roll out on floured board ready for pie tin.

title: brownies
directions: Grease 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Blend butter, sugar and vanilla together.
Add eggs using spoon.
Beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt gradually.
Blend in egg mixture. Stir in nuts.
Spread in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: petticoat tails
directions: Mix together thoroughly butter, sugar and flavoring.
Sift together and stir in flour and salt.
Mix thoroughly with hands. Press and mold in long smooth roll about 2-inches in diameter. Wrap in waxed paper and chill several hours.
With thin, sharp knife, cut in slices 1/8-inch to 1/16-inch thick.
Place slices a little apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: joan's snack crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients, stir in crackers and let stand one hour before serving.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush or blend cookies; set aside.
Cream butter, cream cheese and condensed milk.
Blend in milk and pudding mix.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Starting with crumbs, layer in 8-inch flower part, alternating with pudding mixture, ending with crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, plant silk flower stems.
Add granola rocks and gummy worms.
Serve with garden trowel.

title: cherry hill chicken
directions: Mix all together and place in a 3-quart casserole, greased.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and beat 1 minute.
Put cocoa in 1 teaspoon vanilla and make a paste. Add salt.
Put 2 teaspoons vanilla in the buttermilk and add slowly to mixture along with the flour.
Put vinegar in soda and mix well.
Pour into two round prepared pans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate nut toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Reserve 2 tablespoons margarine.
In a large mixer bowl, beat remaining margarine and sugar until fluffy. Add flour and cocoa; mix well.
With floured hands, press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: hershey's(cow pies)
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a saucepan and cook for 2 minutes after it comes to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and spoon onto wax paper.
Wait to harden and serve.
It only takes 20 minutes to 1/2 hour to cool.

title: turkey treats
directions: Carefully separate each cookie, leaving cream filling on one side. Set cookie halves without filling aside.

To make the turkey body, attach or "glue" a red cinnamon candy (turkey head) to each malted ball (turkey body) with a dab of chocolate frosting. Attach a turkey body to center of each cookie half with cream filling using a dab of chocolate frosting. Spread chocolate frosting on the inside of each cookie half that does not have cream filling. For the turkey tail, arrange candy corn on chocolate frosting cookies with wide end of candy along outer edge.
Attach each turkey tail behind a turkey body using chocolate frosting.
Store assembled turkeys in the refrigerator. Yields 42 cookies.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Use 12 rolls.
Place
frozen the night before in bottom of a Bundt pan.
Mix the brown sugar, dry pudding, chopped pecans and cinnamon.
Sprinkle mix over rolls.
Pour over all the melted margarine.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Bake in morning at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.
Flip upside down on plate and serve.

title: herbed spinach bake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quick quiche
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, add 1/2 amount of cheese to egg, salt, flour, milk and pepper.
Mix and pour into well greased 8-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and meat.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and sugar.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
Add eggs and oil, stirring only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in berries and pecans. Pour in greased loaf pans.
Makes two loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar, shortening, salt, baking powder, vanilla and egg until light and fluffy.
Fold in cake flour.
Add chocolate chips, stirring just to mix evenly.
On plastic wrap, shape into two 2-inch in diameter rolls.
Chill thoroughly.
To bake, cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: college cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients, except cereal and chocolate chips.
Stir in cereal and chocolate chips.
Drop 1 teaspoon of cookie dough on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Using an electric mixer, beat margarine and shortening until creamy.
Add sugar gradually and beat well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift flour, soda and salt together, and add alternately with buttermilk still using an electric mixer.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into three greased and lined 9-inch cake pans and bake in 350° oven for approximately 30 to 35 minutes.
Test for doneness with a toothpick.
Remove cake from oven.
Set on wire rack to cool before removing from pan.

title: german chocolate frosting
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients over medium heat until thickened, stirring all the time, about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut and nuts; mix well.
Cool until spreading consistency. Spread on 2 layers of chocolate cake.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs
until foamy, then add all other ingredients, mixing well.
Split
batter into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done in center.

title: cauliflower-ham au gratin
directions: Arrange cauliflower in an ungreased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with ham.
Beat soup and milk with a hand beater until smooth.
Pour over ham.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly; sprinkle over soup mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake until topping is golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: dried fruit cordials
directions: This needs to be made 6 weeks before needed.
Mix all ingredients.
Stir well.
Put in glass container.
Cover tightly. Set aside 1 week at room temperature.
Stir once daily for the first 3 to 4 days.

title: apricot sweet potatoes
directions: Drain sweet potatoes and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Set aside drained
apricots,	saving	1 cup apricot juice.
Place sweet potatoes
in
an 8-inch
Dutch
oven.
Mix brown sugar, cornstarch,
salt and cinnamon in a saucepan.
Stir in apricot juice and
bring
to
a boil.
Stir in apricots and margarine. Pour over sweet potatoes and bake for 30 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add seasoning mix, olives and water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Arrange rolls in 10-inch round Pyrex for pie crust.
Sprinkle 1 cup corn chips on top of rolls.
Add meat mixture, then spread sour cream on top of meat.
Cover with cheese. Add other cup of crushed corn chips.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: not too sweet pancake syrup
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in pan.
Gradually stir in water.
Cook until clear, 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add brown sugar, margarine, vanilla and maple flavoring.

title: breakfast treat
directions: In microwave, melt butter in a 9 x 9-inch casserole or micro-pan.
Add brown sugar and stir.
Spread evenly in pan. Sprinkle with the nuts (optional).
Cut biscuits in fourths and lay over sugar mixture.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes, turning each minute.
Serve hot.

title: salmon surprise cups
directions: Drain liquid from salmon into measuring cup, adding water to make 1/3 cup.
Flake salmon in bowl and add rest of items, except milk and larger soup items, mixing well.
Spoon into 5 greased custard cups.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Crumble crackers.
Add butter; put in an 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over crackers and bake 20 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Brown bacon until crisp.
Combine salad oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and catsup.
Put in blender.
Pour over spinach.
Crumble bacon over top.
May also add water chestnuts, hard-boiled eggs and red onions to salad.

title: angel rolls
directions: Mix together.
Pour into greased muffin tin and bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Dip chicken in melted butter, then into bread crumbs. Lay flat and put cheese on top. Roll like you would an egg roll. Fasten with a toothpick. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes. Place on cookie sheet covered with foil for baking.

title: rice pudding
directions: Boil rice in 1/2 gallon milk until done.
Boil raisins for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Add to rice the eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Top with cinnamon and bake about 1/2 hour until done at 350°.

title: all vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Stir Ritz crackers into melted margarine.
Spread that on top.
Bake in a 350° oven about 30 minutes.

title: christmas meatballs
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, chocolate and milk.
Heat to boiling and cook for 3 minutes, then remove from stove.
Add butter, peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Mix all together thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump all ingredients in order as listed above into an 8 x 12-inch ungreased baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Do not mix at any time; just dump in layers.

title: whole wheat bread(amish)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let stand for 10 minutes.
Add to remaining ingredients.
Using mixer, beat together until well mixed.
Using a large spoon, work in 5 more cups of all-purpose flour.
Knead about 5 minutes.
Place in a large greased bowl. Let rise 1/2 hour.
Turn out onto lightly floured board and knead just enough to work out air bubbles.
Let rise 2 more times for 1/2 hour periods.
Knead to work out air bubbles after each rising period.
Be careful not to work in too much flour when kneading. Shape into loaves.
Place in greased loaf pans and turn over so tops will have oil on them.
Bake 1/2 hour at 325° until well browned.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In large bowl on low speed combine cake mix, 1 egg, butter, pumpkin pie spice, and mix till crumbly. Press into bottom of 15 X 10 pan. In large bowl beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in eagle brand and add 2 eggs, pumpkin, spice and salt, mix well. Pour over crust, sprinkle with nuts. Bake 30-35 minutes until set. Cool. Cut into squares and store in refrigerator.

title: play dough #1
directions: Mix together.
After cool, store in airtight container.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients well and serve with crackers.

title: toffee bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar, butter, egg yolk and vanilla.
Stir in flour and salt.
Press into greased oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Brown the chops in the butter or margarine.
Place chops in baking dish.
Cover with cooked rice.
Add diced carrots, minced onion and minced green pepper.
Salt and pepper.
Pour a small can of tomato soup and a can of water over all.
Bake covered in 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: surprise cupcakes
directions: Mix cake as directed and place in cupcake pan, 2/3 full. Cream the cheese and sugar, then beat in egg and salt. Stir in chips, then drop 1 tablespoon of mixture into each cupcake. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° and test for doneness.

title: dilly dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: cheese cake squares
directions: Mix and spread in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan which has been greased with butter or Crisco.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Cut small bread rounds from the bread.
Brush with butter and bake at 350° until golden brown.
Mix the cream cheese, onion, Tabasco sauce and mayonnaise.
Place mixture on bread rounds. Place Parmesan cheese in a dish.
Turn cheese topped bread rounds upside down in the Parmesan cheese. Freeze on a cookie sheet 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° until top is brown (15 to 25 minutes).
Good for parties.
Can freeze ahead of time.

title: lettuce layered salad
directions: Tear up lettuce into small pieces in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Add the next 6 ingredients in layers in the order they are listed. Add sugar to mayonnaise; stir and spread on top of salad. Sprinkle cheese on top. Garnish with additional bacon. Refrigerate 8 to 10 hours before serving. Serves 15 or more.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Boil broccoli in just enough water to cover broccoli.
Keep water.
Add chicken cubes or soup base.
In frying pan saute onion and flour.
Add to cooked broccoli and water.
Also, add milk, Cheddar cheese and garlic salt.
Cheese melts fast.
Soup finished.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Add all ingredients to roast.
Add more if a large roast; depends on moistness desired.

title: stromboli
directions: Grease cookie sheet; spread dough to cover sheet lengthwise. Put alternating layers of meat, cheese and seasonings.
Fold over. Make sure all sides are sealed, even the ends.
Sprinkle the seasonings on top.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: rhonda's yeast rolls
directions: Follow steps exactly:
Mix boiling water, sugar and margarine. Stir this until margarine melts.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water. Add to sugar mixture.
Add eggs, then flour.
This will start to get stiff.
Roll, cut or drop by spoonfuls in muffin pans.
This needs to rise 2 hours in warm place.
Brush with melted butter before baking.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place green beans in baking dish.
Add undiluted soup and top with onion rings.
Thoroughly heat at 325° to 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken and spinach
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in skillet. Add onion and saute lightly, then add mushrooms.
Saute until liquid evaporates.
Stir in cooked spinach.
Add garlic, bacon and tomato puree.
Cool.

title: delicious chili con carne
directions: Saute ground beef with onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Simmer over low heat, 30 minutes.
Serve with corn bread.
I double or triple the recipe. It freezes nicely.

title: stella neal's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Sift flour 3 times.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add coconut, vanilla and lemon juice.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: humus - chickpea dip(garbanzo beans)
directions: Blend all ingredients together in food processor.
Serve at room temperature with warm wedges of pita bread.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix eggs, sugar and oil; add to flour mixture and beat well.
Fold in pumpkin and mix well.
Pour batter in a greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on the package.
Let cool.
Pierce top of each layer with a fork.
Spoon crushed pineapple on each layer, spreading bottom layer also with cream cheese frosting. Place cake in refrigerator overnight.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet, stirring to break up.
Drain fat off meat and transfer to 2-quart casserole.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese, to meat.
Mix lightly.
Cover and bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and spread cheese over top.
Return to oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: pineapple surprise cake
directions: Cut cake horizontally into 3 layers.
Drizzle with mixture of pineapple juice and almond flavoring.
Combine crushed pineapple and pudding mix in bowl.
Mix well.
Fold in whipped topping. Spread between layers and over top and sides of cake.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Makes 16 servings.

title: chicken delight
directions: Boil chicken until tender, then pull off into small pieces. Add sour cream, cream of chicken and margarine.
Pour into baking dish and crumble Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: irish cream
directions: Blend all together in blender.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water in large bowl.
Fold in strawberries and juice, pineapple, banana and lemon juice.
Put half of this mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm, about 1 1/2 hours.
Spread sour cream mixed with pecans evenly over top of congealed Jell-O.
Gently spoon remainder of Jell-O mixture on top of sour cream.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares or dip into all layers to serve.
Make the same day as serving.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in 1 egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt. Chill several hours or overnight.
Drop by teaspoon into powdered sugar and shape into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen.

title: fish batter
directions: Stir the water and egg into the flour. Beat with mixer or blender until foamy. Dust fish with flour and dip into batter. Fry in hot oil until golden brown and crispy.
Also use for onion rings and chicken.

title: "lo-cal" candy-frozen chocolate truffles
directions: You will also need wax paper.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Slice 1/8-inch thick.
Add salt, pepper, onion, vinegar and oil.
Pour hot broth over potatoes. Mix gently.
Let stand at least 1 hour at room temperature.
Mix again before serving.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus; reserve liquid.
Sprinkle 1/3 of crumbs in bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with layer of asparagus.
Spread 1/2 of soup evenly over asparagus and sprinkle with 2 teaspoons of asparagus liquid.
Repeat layering, ending with crumbs.
Dot with butter and sprinkle bacon on top.
Bake in 320° oven, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry rhubarb pie(microwave)
directions: In a 4-cup glass measure, combine rhubarb, tap water, gelatin and sugar.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High 4 minutes or until mixture boils and rhubarb is almost tender.
Add strawberries, re-cover and microwave on High 1 minute. Add ice water and chill rhubarb mixture until syrupy.
Pour chilled pie filling into cooled pie shell. Refrigerate until
set.

title: kookoo-e-sabzi
directions: Wash herbs and rinse thoroughly.
Chop finely.

title: cheri's famous bread dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together (not bread).
Serve in hollowed out bread round and use pieces of bread center to dip with.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Beat eggs, gradually adding sugar and then other ingredients. Mix well with nut mixture.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan in 300° oven for about 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: bite size pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mash flat each biscuit and place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Spoon spaghetti sauce on each biscuit.
Spoon on cooked meat.
Place on mushrooms or olives. Cover each with cheese.
Cook about 10 minutes or until biscuits look done around edges.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Remove 1 cup cake mix; set aside.
Mix remaining cake mix with 1/2 cup margarine and 1 egg.
Pat mixture into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine pumpkin, 3 eggs, brown sugar, milk, cinnamon and vanilla; pour over first mixture in pan.
Mix the remaining 1 cup cake mix with 1/4 cup margarine and sugar; crumble over top of pumpkin mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping.
